review: This is a keeper-we all loved it. I did put this under the broiler so the skin to get crusty. Served this with recipe#420690 and recipe#71739

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Yum!  This is so good!  I used half the rice and mixed everything together.  I only had one tomato, so I used that and a can of regular diced tomatoes drained.  I didn't use the jalapeno because I served it to people who don't like their food too spicy.  Really flavorful and I've already got some good ideas on how I'm going to use this recipe again.  Thanks!

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: Oh my goodness!  This was terrific!  A definite keeper.  I served this on my Recipe #358515 that made into rolls.  I used a mixture of equal parts of mayo and sour cream; then spread on the bottom of the roll along with onion slices and banana pepper slices.  I topped the meat mixture with a sprinkling of shredded yellow cheese then the top of the roll.  An outstanding recipe that I can't wait to serve again.

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: Tweaked a bit by using whole milk instead of skim, and 3 Tbsp. flour instead of cornstarch.  Also made on the stove top, stirring constantly with a wire whisk for about 15 minutes.  Refrigerated for two hours.  Delicious.  I disagree with other reviewers that say this isn't sweet enough as is.  I would add slightly more vanilla, but only b/c vanilla makes everything better!!  Thanks for posting.

name: perfect pasta with no watching and no sweating
review: It was really hot the other day and the air conditioning was doing its best so I thought I would give it a break and make my pasta this way. I used a whole wheat fortified rotini and this worked great. I forgot and left it on the burner just turned it off and it still worked out great. I will do this from now on. Thanks.

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Yummy! This recipe worked perfectly and made a lovely tall country style loaf of bread - lovely soft interior and crisp crust. I'm going to revisit this the next time I bake rolls. Delicious!

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: This was great!  I only made the tomato basil topping, as I wanted it to serve with some flat bread, but I will definitely make again.  Great combination of flavors, and very easy.

name: old widow walker s ziploc omelettes
review: Wow! My 30-year-old totally dug these! ...oh wait - that's me. Hehe. I put chopped ham, chopped mushrooms, and a chopped slice of American cheese in mine. I don't ever remember doing these in girl scouts (though we could have - we cooked all kinds of things unconventionally, usually involving de-barked tree branches and fire...LOL), but I am always making omelettes like this now! I ALWAYS have trouble turning them so they look nice, timing when to put the veggies in, overcooking them, and...well, you name it. These come out fluffy and restaurant-style looking (13 minutes cooked it perfectly). Plus, you can make a bunch at once if you have family or company over staying the night! I might start carrying a Bowie knife too, but always asking for my husband to cut stuff with his knife is working good so far. ;) Thanks for this AWESOME recipe/method!

name: zucchini salsa  canned
review: Another 5 star review!  My boys said this was their favorite salsa yet!  An there goes a bunch of zucchini.  Thanks for sharing.

name: spiced sweet roasted red pepper   feta hummus
review:
Excellent, didn't change anything. Made it exactly to directions.
I made it for friends going on a long road trip, so it was perfect to snack on. Sent some veggies and (to make it simple pita chips). Easy and great!
Definitely make this again. I've made my own in the past, but this was just a nice combination of flavors.
Thx again, Kim

name: italian chopped salad in shells
review: I catered a bachlorette party yesterday and made these.  I didn't have fresh basil, so I used a sprinkle of dried basil.  I made half of the batch veggitarian and then added grilled chicken breast and hard salami to the second half.  I could not find roasted garlic vinaigrette, so I used an Asiago vinaigrette. I also had about 1/2 c of parmasaan cheese to use up, so I added that. I will be using this recipe many more times to come.  The modifications to the ingredients are endless.  Thank you for sharing your recipe.  I also only got 24 shells.

name: strawberry cheesecake trifle
review: Very good dessert and very pretty, too! I think next time I might try it with shortcake instead of angel food cake. Thanks!

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: I had a butternut squash in my pantry for about 2 weeks and everytime my grandson would see it he'd say, "Why you have Jerry?" I'd think who the heck is Jerry?!? Come to find out he's a cartoon character. Well, I loathe the thought of telling him, Jerry's now a goner. On a happier note, this recipe is magical. Turns squash into candy.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: This was my first time making corn on the cob that doesn't come from the freezer section.  It was awesome!  So easy to  make and the corn turns out delicious.  Add some butter and salt and fresh ground pepper to the steaming cob and its heaven.  I'll definitely be making this again!

name: tiramisu
review: My DH is Italian so this was something I just had to try making.  It was quick to make and so great tasting that my DH now wants me to make it all the time!  Thanks!

name: brown sugar bundt cake
review: Amazing!  Made this for a baby shower & it was a hit.  Made a couple alterations.  It's already been requested again!  Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: Very good.  Even my picky kids enjoyed it!

name: tilapia
review: My new favorite way to make fish! Very flavorful and easy.

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: Perfect pancakes! I used 1/2 tsp of salt because we use sea salt, but everything else stayed the same. Thanks for the great recipe! Update: we made these with 1 tbs of baking powder and a little more milk and they were even better! Not crumbly at all, but not as fluffy - but we like them better this way. Thanks again for the great recipe!

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: I gave this a five star even though it had a few things that we didn't like...I will be making this again but will use less pasta, I used a 16 oz package of angel hair pasta and it was just entirely too much...much it was very good once we were able to taste it beyond the pasta.  Thanks for sharing.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: Wow!  This is a wonderful dish worth keeping.  I used Recipe #59635 for the salsa, prepared chicken using Recipe #234465, whole wheat tortillas & sauteed onions (in place of green onions).  It was delicious!  I had a little chicken filling leftover & we ate it cold topped on Ritz crackers...yes, that was yummy, too!  Surprisingly, I had one chimi leftover & ate it cold for lunch...delicious, again!  Told my son this would be a great thing to put in his lunchbox for school lunches.  Thanks for this great, versatile recipe.  Tried & true, indeed!

name: emeril s essence
review: I can't judge how good this is against the original as we don't have it in Australia, but I can tell you that this mix contributed to the best chilli con carne ever! Thanks very much for posting.

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: I've made this a few times now, and seems each time I've varied the recipe a bit.  Nevertheless, it has always turned out great.  The last time I made it, I used half n half, as I was out of he whipping cream.  No one could tell any difference...the dinner table was silent apart from forks grazing plates, slurping noodles and a few "mmmms" thrown in for good measure.  It's very easy to prepare and well, even tastes good the next day, if you are lucky enough to have any leftovers.  Served with Recipe #170438 and salad.  Great dish.  Thanks!

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: Fast, easy, not running to the store, delicious!  What else could you want you have a chocolate craving and you only have cocoa powder on hot day?  We looked in the freezer only to find vanilla ice cream, which is good but not helpful when you want chocolate.  I offered to make a sauce and took this one as it only needs 3 minutes, but it tastes much better than that little time and work.  Thanks, both DH and I loved it.

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: We all enjoyed this casserole. I used very lean ground round and low fat soup and 2% cheese. I had to sub black beans - I thought I had a can of refried beans, but I didn't. It worked okay, although I think the refried would be better. I used chipotle taco seasoning. The guys really liked this, will make again.

name: dad s casserole
review: ALERT, ALERT casserole snobs - this recipe is real Southern comfort food.  Yum!  Easy to prepare, easy on the budget and should be served at anyone's table. I used ground turkey, added a little more garlic and was short on quantity of sour crm and crm cheese, so I supplemented Queso Fresca, heated red and white mixtures together, stirred in noodles and topped w/ cheddar. Baked for 20 mins. Thank you for sharing :D

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: We all liked this recipe.  Instead of wrapping the bacon around the chicken, I cut it into thirds and layered it on top.  Broiling at the end helps crisp the bacon up.  I have made this several times, but we have always eaten it for dinner and I haven't had a chance to freeze any yet, so I can't comment on how well they work as a make ahead meal.  Thanks for the recipe!

name: breakfast burritos  once a month cooking
review: I will be making my second batch of these tomorrow. I just did the baic recipe with no frills. I had never done OAMC recipes and I was happy this came together so quickly. Thank you.

name: almost white castle hamburgers
review: I made a batch for a friend of mine and a batch for my son. I love the fact that they are quick and freeze very well.

name: creamed ground beef sos
review: This made for a very, easy meal.  Quick to make on a busy night.  The kids really liked it.  We served it over biscuits with some green beans.

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: Tasty & simple.  Made some white meat with this at the same time as the thighs- both were delicious, though the thighs were a little better.

name: tsr version of chili s chicken enchilada soup by todd wilbur
review: A very tasty and filling soup.  I would add more chicken next time.  Maybe a bit more enchilada sauce too.  Thanks!

name: the easiest  bestest focaccia bread ever
review: This really is delicious... so good that I made it twice in the last three days.  The first time I made it, I used 1/3 whole wheat flour and it was great.  Today I made it with 1/2 whole wheat flour and it was great (I like to see what percentage whole wheat I can use without sacrificing great flavor and texture).  I am not a big cheese lover, so I cut the mozzarella to a scant cup... that was fine.  Tonight I cut the pieces in half through the center for sandwiches (roasted red peppers, tomatoes, and red onions as well as raw spinach... roasted mushrooms would be great too... I used an aioli that was delicious: http://italian.food.com/recipe/tapas-177s-rosemary-a-oli-383193 .  Mmmmm, restaurant quality.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: Just yummy Miss Nezz! Another winner here. I added a little less water because I had fewer potatoes. I used portugese linguisa sausage instead of kielbasa and it gave it just enough spiciness. Will be making again I am sure and also want to make it with sliced jalapenos added as my hubbie just loves them.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: This recipe was great! My husband, especially loved it. I'm pretty sure that it would be at least nearly just as good to just stir fry the meat to cook it rather than going to the trouble of frying it.  I'll try it that way next time. The sauce was excellent! I added just a sprinkle of red pepper flakes for some heat.

name: potato salad with chipotle peppers a man s salad
review: EXCELLENT.  I made this with what I had on hand.  Red onion, red pepper, lots of celery and fresh parsley   chipotle peppers. Skipped the bacon, only had one egg and used idaho potatoes.  Didn't have black beans.  You probably are wondering how the heck the salad was?  Just awesome.  Thanks so much for this.  Next time will try to make it more like the recipe calls for, but in a pinch you have to use what you have on hand.  TRY THIS.  IT ROCKS.  Thanks!

name: buttery shrimp and pasta
review: This was tasty, simple and everyone enjoyed it.  I'll make it again.  After reading the reviews about the sauce not thickening, I replaced the half-and-half with 1 1/2 cups of milk and 4 ounces of cream cheese.  That worked well.  I also used 4 garlic cloves and some lemon pepper and salt.

name: best grilled pork chops
review: This is a 10 star recipe. I made it as written and had them sit overnight.  They were so moist and tasty.  I can't wait to do them again.  Thank you for the best way to grill pork chops.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: I thought this was really good, but my mac-n-chs FANATIC son (adult) was non-plussed. Darn those box mixes. They've ruined the point of mac-n-chs. Thanks!

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: Not for us, but clearly we are the minority! I like the idea of baking and may try my normal egglplant prep with the bake instructions. Thanks, anyway.

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: What can I say that has not been said already......?I gave this recipe a try on Monday, I love eggplant so I was anxious to try this recipe. It was very easy to put together I made it with beef for it was what I had at the moment, but I'm going to give it a try also with the lamb, which I'm positive it will be wonderful. You can never  go wrong with this fantastic lady's recipes, the one's Ive tryed so far are all absolutely wonderful!!!!!!!!  Thank you Kittencal for another GREAT recipe.

name: easy baked potato wedges
review: Not sure what happened, but these didn't work for us. Too greasy for our tastes. Perhaps I did something wrong, but I'm an exp'd cook, and this is not at all complicated. Bummer!

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: So easy and so excellent! There is no need to make pudding from a mix ever again!  Thank you!

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: This sauce is awesome!!!  I couldn't say enough good things about it!  Chicken Teriyaki Stir Fry is one of our favorite meals but I don't make it all that often because the Teriyaki sauce we like we have to buy from a restaurant on the other side of town.  No more! I will be making this often. Thank you so much for posting!!

name: denny s style french toast
review: I thought that this was good, not great. I had to use the mixer to get rid of the flour lumps and I wish it had more vanilla and cinnamon. I didn't really taste a difference using the flour and sugar.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: This is an amazing cake! It's just about the best chocolate cake I've ever had! Very easy to make and it's just so delicious! I highly recommend anyone thinking of making it. It's so moist! I chose to make a filling for this and it turned out absolutely wonderful!!Thanks, Marg, for a wonderful cake, my new favorite! This is definately a keeper!

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: Delicious.  I used  canned peaches in water to cut back on the sugar.

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: I made this in my bread machine and made it as a loaf instead of the rolls.  The bread was nice and hearty.  Soft on the inside and chewy on the outside.  I cant say it was the best white bread recipe that Ive made in the bread machine, but it was still delicious.  It seems like a lot of reviewers like this recipe as the dinner rolls.  So I will have to try that out next time!  Thanks for the recipe!

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: So yummy!  I made this on a Saturday morning with the idea of eating off it all week.  Planning to put it with cous cous to take to work for lunch, with crostina for side dish one day for dinner, and just eat it as suggested with some grated parm.  It was done to our liking after about 5 hours and when I tasted it...wow!  I almost (almost) wish we didn't have plans to go out tonight because I want to eat it all up now.

name: easy cole slaw
review: So easy and tasty.  I used broccoli slaw and cut the sugar back almost half.  It was plenty sweet enough for me.  Thanks for the recipe, I'm sure I'll make it all summer.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: This cake is so good! When I took my first bite, I was pleasantly surprised with a burst of chocolate, the old fashioned devil's food cake chocolate. The recipe is easy to follow, the times are right on, and I definately will be making this again! Thanks for posting!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: I made a half recipe because I didn't have the full amount of blueberries that was called for.  I also used another chef's recommendation for a struesel topping - * 1/4 cup all-purpose flour * 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon * 1/4 cup firmly packed light brown sugar * 2 tablespoons unsalted butter, slightly softened. The muffins were very good.

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: This was a HUGE hit at the lake this weekend!  I did add some chopped up salami and alittle dill relish.  The longer it chilled the better flavor it got.  I liked how easy it was to make too.  This will go into my favorites for future times.  Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: perfect pasta with no watching and no sweating
review: Awesome!  This is the only way I'll make pasta now!  As I generally use chunky whole wheat or whole grain pasta, I let it sit for 20 minutes rather than 15, and it worked out perfect.  Not only did it not require watching, stirring or steam up the kitchen, the pot didn't need any scrubbing, either!  Thank you SO much for posting this gem!

name: blender quiche   or whatever you have in your kitchen leftover
review: I made this with spinach, mushrooms, and zucchini.  I got carried away with the veggies as I always do, so I reduced the ham to keep the total volume of veg   meat the same.  It didn't fly.  I like my meal proportions to lean heavily to vegetables, so that wasn't the problem.  I think this recipe works best with tastily-spiced leftovers, not starting with unseasoned fresh ingredients.  Still, what I made was good enough to eat, and tasty enough to try variations on it later.  Cheese on the bottom ended up a lot like crust ... I could see mixing everything (but more heavily seasoned, possibly with less baking mix or none if veggies are well-drained) and pouring it in a crust for yummy!  This recipe is a framework, so it should always be a work in progress; and for that, it's a great start!

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: Only found Pillsbury cake mix, but worked fine.  I did make larger balls, and got 30.  Started baking at 8 minutes, then added 2 more, twice, before I thought the center was "set".  As suggested, let the balls sit a few minutes before rolling in sugar, and they all had a lovely cracked appearance.  I don't think I will make these for Christmas batches, since the sugar was absorbed overnight, and the cookies lost their "fudgy" consistency, but would be wonderful for dessert the same day.  Thanks for posting, Karen.

name: basic batter waffles
review:
These were the first waffles I've ever tried & they turned out great! I made them on my new George Foreman grill that came with waffle plates and they cooked up wonderfully. They didn't stick (I don't know if that had to do with the recipe or the non-stick spray I used), the outside got nice & golden brown and just a tad crusty while the inside was oh so soft- just like we like them! The kids loved them and hubby even ate 2 (which was a surprise.)

I used what I had on hand for the recipe- which was 2% milk & only vanilla extract. (I'm definitely going to pick some up for next time b/c I have a feeling it'll make it a five-star recipe then!) I also added a few dashes of cinnamon to the dry ingrediants. The batter was really lumpy which worried me, but after I cooked them it didn't make a difference. This recipe made 6 big waffles on my George Foreman G5 grill.

I think next time I'm going to try and make it healthier by using some wheat flour & possibly wheat germ or flax seed. I also want to try and find a way to cut back on the oil by substituting some of it with something healthier. No matter if I make them as recipe stated or slightly healthier- I will be making these again.

name: thick  soft  and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: Perfect cookie!  The best I have ever made....This is my favorite recipe for chocolate chip cookies....

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: Spot on! Easy to make, easy to follow recipe and using the wrap instead of pastry was a great idea, so much lighter than pastry. Thanks for sharing!

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: This truly lived up to all expectations!  I made this exactly as posted (except I used buttermilk instead of half-and-half or milk) but tripling the ingredients for the dressing.  I ended up with more than enough dressing to use on quadrupled salad ingredients, with plenty left over.  I added some halved grape tomatoes to the salad (for color) and brought this to my annual church picnic.  It was a real hit!  I will definitely make a batch of the dressing again to have on hand!  Also, instead of using grated parmesan on the salad, I used some nice shredded parmesan.  Thanks for another perfect recipe, Carol!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Great cake!  Pretty easy to do.  I did the freezer trick and the cake was very moist.  I also don't think this is like frosted banana bread - the texture is very cakey and not at all like the banana breads I've had.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: It looks like I'm in the minority here, but no one in my family cared for this.  We found it very bland even with the good cheddar cheese.  Also very thick and gloppy.  Many other recipes that are much better in my opinion.

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: Very good fish.  It has plenty of flavor.  Made it exactly as written.  Will use this one again for sure.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: It was an ok stew

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: This is a great broccoli salad.  I didn't have purple onion so I used a spanish onion.  I diced it instead of slicing it in rings.  For the dressing, I used half sugar (1/8 cup).  Perfect like that.  I used light mayonnaise.  So yummy.  Thanks Christine :)  Made for cookbook tag game

name: breakfast casserole supreme
review: This turned out great! I baked 1/2 recipe in a 9x9 inch pan. I baked in the time stated, and it didn't turn out watery for me as some have said. There are so many possibilities for this recipe but the basic is really delicious. The only thing I might change the next time is to defrost the hashbrowns as I think they may turn out more crispy that way..but I ain't complaining, it was really good! Thanks for posting!

name: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
review: Simple to bake, and gobbled up by my family!  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: weight watchers general tso s chicken
review: This was so easy to prepare, other than cutting the recipe in half I followed the directions exactly and didn't change a thing.  Served over steamed jasmine rice and it made a complete meal for DH & myself. We did use the pepper flakes for that added spice and it was perfect.  Couldn't tell this from our favorite resturant, looked impressive and less calories and fat too.  No wonder it has so many 5 star reviews - I'll be making this often

name: linda s cheesecake stuffed strawberries
review: These really were delicious!  I loved the filling.  It was so good with the strawberries!  Instead of coating the outside with crushed nuts, I used up some crushed chocolate graham crackers that I had.  Anything would be good on the outside, nuts, melted chocolate, crushed cookies...yum...it could be endless.  Thanks so much for the recipe.  Im sure to make again!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: I have never made biscuits before, but I must say these were so easy I'm wondering why I ever bought them in a can.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: I had a hard time waiting for the 10 minute cooling period before prying one of these out of the pan.  They smelled so good.  I gotta say, these are really good!

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: This is good and easy to make. I followed the recipe as written.

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: I'm new to the world of cooking squash as I didn't grow up eating it, but was curious enough to try this recipe. I cut the ingredients in 1/2 for 2 of us. I followed the directions to cook for 20 minutes, and mine came out quite mushy, but very delicious! Looking at the photos, I think I'll cook it for maybe 15 minutes next time to preserve the shape. Very tasty and so simple!

name: thai coconut rice
review: What a flavorful side dish!  I made it to go with some Thai Grilled Chicken Wings.  Excellent addition to our meal!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: Great marinade for steak or pork!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: I went out and got balsamic vinegar,just so I could try this. I had to omit the chili pepper so DDs could enjoy it as well. DD is down with a stomach flu,barely puts anything in her mouth,but she asked for more rice with "sauce". I had my parents over and they gave this a five star as well. I'm in love with Empress chicken recently,but I realy enjoyed this too.A couple more garlic cloved didn't hurt at all. Made as a recipenap for Aussie swap.

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: Lovely yeasty rolls.  Among the best I've ever had.  The only thing I might try next time is to let them rise a little longer before going into the oven.

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: Quick and easy meal with lots of flavor.

name: easy cole slaw
review: This is so simple.  We loved it.  I had half cabbage to use up so I shredded my own but otherwise followed the recipe.  I plan on storing this recipe close to pull out again.  We eat alot of coleslaw and this one is the best.  Not only is it easy to prepare, it tastes great too.  Thank you for sharing.

name: kittencal s spinach parmesan rice bake
review: This was amazing! I put fresh spinach, onions, cheese ( swiss and parmesan),and eggs in the food processor.Then added the rice and the rest of the ingredients. This was definately a "WOW" recipe. Go easy on the salt if you use a lot of parmesan, tho. 1,000 stars!

name: baked ziti
review: This was easy to make and tasted good.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: I was looking for a recipe to use up some ingredients in my pantry and came across this one.  After combining the melted shortening and chocolate I was a little concerned that the mixture would be too thick after adding the flour as the eggs were the only "liquid."  I needn't have worried.  The batter turned out perfectly.  I used an 8" x 8" pan so the brownies would be a little thicker and adjusted the cooking time accordingly.  These turned out fantastic -- not dry or cake-like, but chewy and fudgy -- just the way we like them.  Thanks for sharing this recipe -- I already have requests to make it again!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: I used 1/2 cup half and half instead of the cream and next time will probably leave it out altogether -- as well as cutting the sauce ingredients (cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper in half.) It was very good, but very rich!

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Really, really good salad!  I tweaked the dressing a bit since there wasn't enough of a vinegar taste to me, so mine ended up being 1.5 parts vinegar to 1 part olive oil, but otherwise I followed the recipe with great results!

name: zucchini chocolate cake
review: Great recipe.  Very moist and flavor was great.  Made into muffins, which I had a horrible time getting out of the muffin tins despite using my usual product which works great with other recipes.  Will make again, next time with muffin tin liners!

name: classic baked ziti
review: This was very tasty!  I made it vegetarian by using imitation ground beef.  Easy and delicious!  Thanks!

name: crock pot chicken vindaloo
review: This was really good. I thought the amount of vinegar was just fine. In the future I may add some more heat. I used a cut up chicken instead of boneless skinless breasts and it worked well.

name: kittencal s spinach parmesan rice bake
review: Excellent recipe!  I divided the dish into to smaller casserole dishes....enough for 4 people.  It was enjoyed by all!!!  My only comments would be to spray your casserole dishes with spray as the egg mixture does get stuck to the dish.  Kudos, Kitten on another winner!!

name: simple tomato sandwich
review: Bliss!  I got fresh tomatoes & multigrain bread from our local farmer's market.  I had one for lunch today, then went back and made another.  I plan on eating it for dinner, too.  Wish I hadn't waited so long to try this recipe!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: Pie shells normally do not intimidate me!  That being said, I found I had to use more water....the crust very hard to roll out and it kept cracking.  The taste was the only thing that saved this recipe.

name: chickpeas with spinach  greek
review: Very tasty and flavorful!  I am going to use fresh spinach next time.  Thanks for sharing!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Great recipe, neat flavor. I spread the lite mayo on the breasts then sprinkled on the pepper & garlic - I also added a hot & spicy mix.  I held off sprinkling the  cheese on until the breasts were half cooked.  Then sprinkled it on and it was golden when the chicken was cooked  - We enjoyed our dinner thanks

name: cinnamon swirl quick bread
review: What a lovely bread.  I made this today exactly (almost) as stated....I didn't have buttermilk so I mixed a tblsp. of vinegar into the milk and it turned out great.  The cooking time was a bit longer (probably my oven) but the result was a very moist and delicious loaf. I know I will be making this again as it was very easy to put together and made my home smell heavenly !

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Simply delicious! I didn't have any lemon pepper so I used coarse black pepper and lime and lemon zest. I was also in a hurry, so I cut them in half and they were perfectly done in about 15 minutes. My mother, that does not like Brussels sprouts period, LOVED them.

name: roast  sticky  chicken
review: For us I used garlic salt instead of plain salt, left out the cayenne, used about 4 T (if not more) of dried onions along with the other ingredients which I zapped in the food processor.  I also used a lime chopped up along with the onion which I stuffed inside the chicken.  Cooked on a rack basting often and it cooked up beautifully.  Great recipe, thank you.

name: kittencal s milk boiled corn on the cob
review: Absolutely delicious.  I'll never microwave corn on the cob again!

name: cajun style oven fries
review: Very tasty fries.  A nice change from plain old french fries!  Thanks for posting this.  Made for Healthy Choices ABC.

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: This dish is just packed with fantastic flavour. I used 1/2 of the oil and added 1/2 finely chopped onion. I served it with little bowls of crumbled feta and grated parmiggiano so people could add cheese or no cheese to their liking. People were just raving about it.

name: greek style turkey burgers
review: This was an outstanding recipe! I never tried a turkey burger, and I wasen't expecting it to be that great...but this was delicious! We will be making these often! Thanks for posting!

name: uncle bill s microwave potato chips
review: These are really good. I save 5 stars for recipes that knock my socks off. They did take longer to crisp up for me. It seemed that my microwave just steamed off so much liquid. It is definatly a good thing. And will be very handy for when I want a quick snack so I will not consume quick to eat sugars.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: We really enjoyed this recipe. It was easy to put together & tasted great. I don't think I've ever tried the Alfredo at Olive Garden so I can't compare the two, but this one was good.

name: cream cheese cinnamon crescents
review: Discovered this recipe through a friend and then on Recipezaar. Decided to try it out tonight, but cut it in half. I forgot to use less butter and added some more cinnamon but other than that they were just perfect. My family gobbled up half the pan right away, I guess I will have to make some more. This sounds like a great recipe to also use to make cream cheese cinnamon rolls, just roll up the dought after dipping it in cinnamon and sugar and place a layer of cream cheese inside. Yum!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: These muffins are delicious!  My husband and I are thrilled with how they came out!  I added walnuts to the batter.

name: chewy granola bars
review: I used a combination of rice krispies and raisin bran for the cereal and doubled the entire recipe.  These granola bars are absolutely amazing.  I also added a couple scoops of peanut butter to these delicious bars.  Thank you for posting a great granola bar.  I will be making this recipe again!

name: chicken garlic bites
review: We used these for a graduation party.  They were very well received.  I did add some cornmeal, garlic and canned parmesan cheese to the coating.  Thanks for posting!

name: low fat banana bread
review: This banana bread was so easy and turned out great!  I substituted brown sugar and splenda for the white sugar and added some mini chocolate chips.  I cooked in small loaf pans and the flavor and texture was just right.  Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: Another great recipe by Kittencal. We had never had Moussaka before and are now Moussaka lovers. I did go the traditional route and added a light sprinkle of ground cinnamon over the top layer of eggplant. Could not find ground lamb so I bought some leg of lamb and ground my own. Can't get any fresher than that! It states 4 servings, but you can easily get 6 - 8. I cooked mine in a 13 X 9. Will make again. Thanks.

name: classic pie crust  idiot proof step by step photo tutorial
review: This crust was worth not dumping a crust out of a box! Now that I have this crust in my arsenal, I think I'll never do that again. I rolled this out in a gallon sized ziploc bag so I wouldn't have to worry about tearing it (my rolling pin is too small to fold the crust over). I used this for my first cherry pie, ever and it was perfect. I had a little dough left over so I made and impromptu free-form apricot tart and that was delicious, too. Thank for a simple and delicious crust that I will use again and again!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: This chicken is the BEST! It really does melt in your mouth. Each of my family members went back for extra so I'm happy that I made extra. I covered the chicken breasts in the mayonnaise mixture rather than just brushing it on top. I didn't change a thing with the ingredients although I used 6 chicken breasts instead of just four without having to change the amount of ingredients. I'm amazed how you wouldn't even know there is mayonnaise on this chicken. My kids thought it was a breading and I thought it tasted like it too. Truly delicious and going into my tried and true recipe book. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: zucchini salsa  canned
review: Very tasty!  I followed the recipe with the exception of adding 5 good sized jalapenos and cutting the sugar back to about a half a cup as we don't care for really sweet salsa's.  Nice balance of hot and sweet, hubby didn't know there was zucchini in it until I told him. Made 5 pints which I processed and a small tub to snack on leftover.    Love the use of zucchini past the typical bread/cake! Absolutely a keeper for next summer.

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: I cut this in half and used an 8x8 pan. I also used wild rice instead of brown and left off the cheese. I baked it at 325 for 1 hour 10 minutes and then uncovered 20. It worked out great. I used the italian seasoning and garlic powder but next time I think I'll try other seasonings. Thanks for a new way to eat lentils.

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: I thought these were great but my husband said a little too bland, so I "averaged" our ratings for this one.  They stayed moist throughout the cooking.  I did flip them once during cooking as well as during the broiling to better brown the bacon.

name: easy taco stew
review: Really good and easy! It was eaten up!

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: Great recipe! This is one I definitely need to remember. Easy and fast to put together. Makes a great appetizer, but my family would have been happy to eat it as a main dish. I thought the chicken was best when cut into smaller pieces than indicated. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: These were good and easy to prepare.  My husband didn't think the flavors permeated the potatoes enough, but I thought it was fine.Cooking times were perfect for my potatoes to get done.

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: I skipped the cheese and the baking (still cooked the bread), and this was still incredible! We had a little left over that I put in a pan with some leftover spaghetti for lunch the next day -- it too was great! Thank you!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: Made as written and marinated the chicken overnight and grilled the next day.  We can't identify any specific reason but this just didn't really do it for us.  While it had a "fresh" taste from the herbs there just wasn't much else going on and didn't meet our expectations.  Thanks for sharing though!

name: our favourite lemon loaf
review: Not as moist as i would prefer. Good basic recipe.

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: An excellent marinade! I did not use quite enough garlic though, and used less oil, which was fine. Everyone loved it! Thanks!

name: cajun style oven fries
review: These were very good but one side burned, so would either turn down my oven or turn over half way through cooking time or both.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: These were great!! I taped the recipe by the flour, since I usually have all the ingredients. I ended up freezing some and bought some blueberry syrup for them ( since I know that will be FANTASTIC!). Thanks so much!!

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: This is comfort food at its best!  I used Louisiana Hot Links, frozen hash browns and added some garlic and onion powder to the white sauce.  So good!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: I don't usually like cooked vegetables of any kind but this is perfect with the garlic and rosemary!  I eat it cold with avocado and tomato chunks.  It makes a perfect summer lunch!  Thanks for sharing, Rita!

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: This smelled wonderful while cooking, gotta love that liquid smoke. I made as directed, but halved the recipe and it wasn't very thick... perhaps I confused the directions and used too much broth. However, it was still delicious! I've never liked soups, much less bean soups, but this was fantastic. I look forward to making it often in the winter!

name: hawaiian chicken kabobs
review: I will use often. All the flavors work so well together. Great textures. Love the marinade.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Nice recipe. I'd suggest cutting back on the hoisin sauce, as the sauce was a bit too strong for me. The beef was very tender!

name: crazy crust pizza
review: I have tried some of the other Crazy Crust Pizza on this site, but we actually liked this recipe better as the dough doesn't fill you up on one slice of pizza.  Next time, I would take the comment of Cajun Baby and maybe pour the dough onto a hot pizza stone because once cooked up, the middle does stays a little doughy, especially if you have gone a little overboard with the toppings (like we all do!!)  I used SAMS_Club's Ultimate Pizza Sauce (114392) and used 6 small fresh mozzarella balls and about 6 fresh mushrooms, sliced.  I don't do fresh onions or garlic very well well, so I used about 1 cup of onions and 3 garlic minced, sauteed into Italian sausage.  DH and I really enjoyed it, but being just the two of us, I am wondering if I could cut the recipe in half.  The crust seems pretty flexable, so next time I will cut the recipe in half, top it with shredded chicken, pizza sauce, mushrooms and cheese...all done on a pizza stone.  Thanks for the posting and the idea.

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: Full of flavor. Fast and easy to make. My toddler ate what I gave her and asked for more.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: This was really good marinade for chicken fajitas. Thanks.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: This was a full bodied pizza sauce...probably enough for 3 pizzas.  I did forget to add the parmesan cheese, but that didn't hurt the final taste.  I was thinking that I might have to take my blender to the final product, but everything just "melted" into the sauce wonderfully.  Definately use the fennel and bay leaf...it makes the sauce.  I used it on Karen's Crust Pizza (29002).  Great taste, great flavor!!!

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review: I imagined myself anywhere in France with DH at an off-street cafe with wine, cheese, toasted bread and French Dip.

name: kittencal s beef or pork marinade and tenderizer
review: I had some half price rib eye steaks in the freezer that were starting to get freezer burn.  Used this marinade minus the meat tenderizer (they were rib eyes after all!)  Absolutely fabulous.  The flavor complemented the steak without overpowering it and it wasn't too sweet.  Will use again with a tougher cut of meat and the tenderizer.  Another great recipe KittenCal.  Thanks for sharing.

name: the best ever waffles
review: I subbed the eggs with 1 Tbs flax seed each. They took a long time to cook relative to other waffles I've made -- coming out more of a pale yellow-cream than that nice golden-brown, but they tasted really great. Very buttery, we actually really liked them with a topping of preserves better than the usual butter syrup.

name: chicken legs grilled
review: Tasted good and easy to make.  Thanks.

name: auntie s delicious soft pretzels  amish recipe
review:
Perfect!
I was worried at first as my mixture seemed so dry to start, even when I added an little extra water it still seemed not quite right but after proving it came together and was easy to roll into ropes. I salted some, others I brushed with melted butter when they came out the oven and rolled in cinnamon sugar. YUM!

name: parmesan zucchini
review: This was so easy and delicious! A wonderful way to use the zucchini from our garden. I added some cherry tomatoes and slices of bell pepper as well. It made for a really colourful side dish. Thank you!

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: Great frosting recipe.  I used this recipe to frost DD's cake she made and this recipe worked wonderful.  It held its own when decorating which was exactly what we were looking for.  Yummy tasting frosting too.  Thank you for sharing.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: Made for double crust blueberry pie - excellent results.  Used white whole grain flour and everyone liked it.  Pressed bottom crust in pan and then rolled top between 2 pieces of waxed paper.  Easy, flaky and delicious.  Will certainly make again and again.  Thanks!

name: greek style turkey burgers
review: I subbed the turkey with chickpeas for a veggie burger. They didn't stick together at all, making for a sloppy meal, but were pretty good -- a very unique veggie burger. I look forward to trying this in a veggie pita wrap, too.

name: streamlined chimichangas
review: These are very easy. I did not find the flavor outstanding, however. I added cheese inside each chimi and served with sour cream. I bet a little refried beans inside each one would be delicious.

name: weight watchers mexican chicken breasts
review: Love how simple this is and how yummy it turned out. Served with Spanish rice and refried beans and chips. Thanks for sharing!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Ours stuck to the pan really bad, not sure why -- made for more of a hash-brown side dish after I scraped 'em all off. Yummy anyway, and worked well with the one sweet potato I threw in (sweet potatoes are healthier, so we'll probably make them that way from now on). Great side, look forward to making it again and hopefully having them come out in one piece.

name: cinnamon muffins
review: I would say these are Good Not Great. I used half oil, half butter as well as half milk, half buttermilk. I also left out the nutmeg and added a whole tsp. of cinnamon to the batter. I made sure not to overbake them based on other reviews. They were done in just under 20 minutes and were not too dry. My husband couldn't stop eating them with butter and jelly...

name: basic batter waffles
review: I was craving waffles, this hit the spot!  Easy and quick, thanks a bunch!

name: ground beef gyros
review: Really good.  Used extra garlic.  Skipped the sugar.  I used ground turkey.  My entire family loved it.  Thanks.

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: Perfect!  This was easy and came out tender, juicy, and even made for amazing leftovers.  I've never done tenderloin before but I will cook it more often using this recipe.  Thanks!

name: dad s casserole
review: This casserole sure was delicious!  Very easy and fast to whip up.  It made great leftovers as well!  I didnt have enough egg noodles, so I used penne pasta.  I did think the tomato mixture needed more seasonings during cooking.  So I added in some garlic and onion powder, italian seasoning, a little more sugar, and basil.  Also I thought the hamburger mix was a little dry so I added in a thing of diced tomatoes to give it more sauce and texture.  Put all together and baked, this was great!  I cant wait to make again and have some crusty garlic bread with this.  How much easier can this be!  Thanks for the recipe!

name: thai coconut rice
review: Great coconut rice.  I made half a recipe and served with Recipe #159238 and  Recipe #203074.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: SO good and SO easy.  Loved the buttery taste this sauce had.

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: Great pie for the hot days of summer. Used Recipe #116887 and Recipe #73863 to make this delicious pie.  I also used three regular limes for the juice.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Very similar to PF Changs! I didn't use mushrooms, simply because i didn't have them and it still tasted great.  We also only needed about half the special sauce the recipe makes.  Thanks for posting!

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: I made it last week and the chicken turned out so good me and my BF love balsamic vinegar and this one was a winner.It is so easy to prepare.Thanks for the recipe will be repeated again.

name: scrum diddly umptious vegan brownies
review: These were very easy & my husband said they were perfect!  I couldn't find vegan choc chips so I skipped them and they were fine.  Thanks so much for an easy treat to satisfy the sweet tooth!!

name: soft  spicy  heavenly ginger cookies
review: My husband loved these!!!   I also gave the recipe out to a friend after she tried them.  They both said they were soft, perfect spice, and very tasty!!  I did skip the raisin (DH doesn't like them) and used a bit more fresh ginger.  Thanks so much!!

name: fajita seasoning mix
review: I have never made fajitas before and did not want to use one of those little pkgs you buy at the grocery store. This is so easy to make and we loved it. Thanks for the recipe.

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: This is my new food obsession...it's perfect! Summer on a plate!

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: This is fantastic. I used 1 tsp chili and 1/2 tsp of cumin and tostitos in place of the tortillas. We loved it. This is easy to make  too. Thanks for the recipe.

name: wholesome homemade honey whole wheat bread
review: Wonderful light bread.  I have made this several times as it freezes so nicely.

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: Very, very good.  I don't think my sauce got as thick as it appears it did for others but it didn't matter because the taste was wonderful.  Simply and tasty.  Great for a weeknight meal.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: My Husband and I liked this recipe.  I added a little extra cheese on top.  And the sour cream sauce was delicious. Thank you!

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: I'll see this recipe pop up constantly but never got around to using it; so I was SUPER excited when I finally had the time to try this, and let me tell you, this was just SO delicious. I had skinless chicken thighs (bone in) and marinated them for over 24 hours, and the chicken ended up so moist and full of flavour! And the sauce was to die for! I think next time, I'd reserve the marinade after putting the chicken in the oven, then cook it on the stove top to help reduce it a bit more and get a nice, thicker consistency. Also I think the only other minor thing I'd do next time is to maybe reduce the brown sugar just a tad, but other than that, this was perfect! Thank you!

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: I've never made split pea soup in the crock pot before and was so surprised at how well it turned out.  I didn't even have to puree the peas like I ususally do.  The flavor was spot-on too.  I halved the recipe for just my husband and I and it turned out great!

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: Fabulous easy angel food cake. I loved the use of both almond and vanilla extracts.  It had such a great density while still being so light! I will be making this again and again.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: Let me join the hordes who have given ths the top possible rating. Unbelievably simple. Just put some canned chicken breast on top and had a memorable meal.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Very nice salad.  I only had a 12-ounce package of rotini so I scaled back the amounts of the other ingredients accordingly.  The dressing is sweeter than other pasta salads I've had, but I rather liked it and it seemed that my guests did too!  Thanks!

name: chicken legs grilled
review: These were absolutely fabulous!  Great flavor!  I did grill them for 40 minutes.  Served with grilled asparagus, fruit salad and rolls.  The entire family loved this.

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Excellent recipe. Followed the recipe for Dinner Buns and they turned out perfect.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Good base recipe though a little bland.

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: I think this is a good recipe to have around the house for making a quick dessert for the kids; however, it is very crumbly (in a moist way, not a dry way) and only average in taste, so I wouldn't use this recipe for company or if I were taking a cake to someone.  I do see why this recipe garners so many high reviews, though.  It is nice to be able to mix and bake everything all in one pan.  I also see the advantage of this recipe for those who can't/won't eat eggs or milk.  And I didn't note any odd taste, as some other reviewers have noted.  I didn't taste the vinegar or baking soda at all in this.  The cake is good for a quick and easy dessert at home, but if I need something to serve to guests or to take to friends, I will use one of my other recipes that yields a better result (with slightly more work and clean-up).

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: As far as meatloaf goes, this was a pretty good recipe.  My husband, a meatloaf connoisseur of sorts (sadly) enjoyed it very much.  The four star rating is due to the fact that we both have had/made meatloaf recipes before that we liked more.  I also felt like my meatloaf was kind of flat compared to other recipes I've made.

name: best baked potato
review:
Oh my God! It works!

After years of stiff, hard baked potatoes, I am happy to say that I have produced restaurant-quality ones, thanks to this recipes. I poked 2 large russets 6 times each, then nuked them for 3 minutes, placed them on a plate and drizzled them with olive oil. Then I sprinkled them with garlic salt and put them in the toaster oven for about 35 minutes. I did the recipe's method of opening the potatoes, and it was like magic (just rip a paper towel in half--one side for each hand--to protect your hands while you are pushing the potato open). Fantastic! I will make these constantly.

name: the best pasta salad
review: What an easy and light summer pasta salad!  I didn't have black olives, and had to substitute a different dressing, a balsamic vinaigrette, but it was still delicious.  This is one recipe where you can easily add and subtract different veggies and it will work.  Thanks for sharing this winner.

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: So easy, yet so good.  1/2 inch was just the right thickness for the slices to end up with a lightly crispy crust and a soft center.  I did have trouble with mine sticking to the pan, despite oiling it generously.  After baking, I topped each slice with some sliced garden tomatoes which had been sitting in a bit of olive oil and chopped basil; then a slice of provelogne cheese.  I turned off the oven, but put the whole pan back in to melt the cheese.  To serve, I stacked 2 slices on each plate and accompanied it with a bowl of cold Lebanese Cucumber Soup.  Yum!

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: Excellent bruschetta! Everyone loved it!

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: Who would have thought that baking powder would sofen up eggs and make them fluffy.  These were good.  Will do again for sure.  I used the 1/4 tsp of baking powder. Used fat free half and half as that is what was here.  Thank you.

name: cheese tortellini pesto pasta salad
review: I did not care for this at all. And it did not go over very well with everyone who ate it. I had one person that absolutely loved it. I think that I might have enjoyed it more if I made my own pesto. The mozzerella did not really add anything to it and could have been left out.

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: Very tasty.  I almost forgot the Worchestershire, tasted the salad and then realized that I hadn't added it -  It really popped the flavor.  Great recipe to use up that bit of left over chicken

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: This was VERY good.  Next time I'll take your advise and double the sauce recipe.  Thanks kitten!

name: hawaiian chicken kabobs
review: These were attractive with the tomatoes, pineapple and capsicum making a lovely, colourful skewer. The flavour of the marinated chicken was surprisingly mild and quite enjoyable. The only thing I regretted was using tinned mushrooms instead of fresh as they didn't have as much flavour as they could have. A good recipe to impress company with.

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: We're trying to incorporate fewer meat meals in our diet.  The important thing when selecting a dish is that it's hearty enough that you don't miss the meat.  Not only did I NOT miss the meat, I adored the fusion of flavors and texture.  Fantastic.  I'm coming back to this one.

name: the best belgian waffles
review: HOLY PERFECT WAFFLES BATMAN!!!! I have tried a few other belgian waffles without getting that perfect light as air texture, this recipe nails it! I subbed vanilla rice milk, as it was all I had on hand, and they still came out perfect!!!! I served with fresh strawberries and a very light drizzle of real maple syrup. Absolute breakfast perfection!

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: Quick, easy, yummy! Used frozen spinach but otherwise followed the recipe - made for a great lunch soup along with a few pieces of crusty bread! Will use slightly less rosemary the next time as it really dominated the overall taste, but I've had that problem before with the batch of rosemary I have now, so I think my overly potent rosemary was to blame! Thank you for sharing!

name: tsr version of carrabba s bread dipping spice by todd wilbur
review: This is excellent!  I was amazed that it tasted exactly like the bread dipping sauce at Carrabba's!  We loved this and used it on lots of things, including toasted tomato sandwiches, BLT's, and more!

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Made the way my mother used to make.  I omitted the nutmeg and used 1/4 t. cloves (my own preference).  I also doubled and put into a 9x13" pan.  Thanks for sharing!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: I do have to say "unbelievable" is perfect in the title for this recipe!  I have made baked wings for years, recipe after recipe, until I finally gave up and decided frying was the only way to get a perfect buffalo wing.  When I first saw this recipe, I noticed the method right away was different than all the others.  Boiling them in water, then broiling them in the oven sounded unusual, but I thought what the heck lets try!  I could not believe the end result!  They came out plump and crispy on the outside.  Everytime I would make baked wings, they always seemed to shribble up and never would crisp up very well on the outside.  I tried several different methods and recipes and it always was the same.  Not this recipe!  I was so surprised that a baked wing recipe could compare so close to the fried ones.  Absolutely the best, and I will always use this recipe from now on when I want to bake them.  I am a wing fanatic, so when I say this recipe is great, I mean it!  Cant wait to try this method with different sauces.  Thanks for the great recipe and giving me my hope back on baked wings!

name: harvest pumpkin apple bread
review: This was really good. I only got one loaf, so I don't know how mini loaves would work. I suppose it would depend on the size of the loaf pan. Easy to make, tastes great, and a great way to use up my last can of pumpking before I stock up again. Thanks for posting!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Yummy!  I used 6 chicken legs and 6 thighs so I increased the sauce by half so I would have more to drizzle over the jasmine rice I served with it.  I don't really think I needed to; there would have been plenty and it took longer to cook down.  You're right though, waiting for it to cook down was definitely worth it!  So simple, not too many ingredients, things you would have on hand, and you didn't have to pay much attention to it while preparing the rest of the meal.  Lovely for company -- everyone loved it.  Thanks so much!

name: chinese pot stickers
review: Amazing.  I loved these and so did my BF.  Thank you for posting.  I didn't have tops for my skillets so I transferred the pot stickers to an electric skillet.  It worked out great.  I used all the ingredients called for and am glad I did.  I think that the shrimp added a wonderful dimension to these pot stickers.  I will be making these again!

name: wholly guacamole
review: This was very good! It was just the 2 of us so I only used 1 avocado and left out the cilantro. Thanks for a great guacamole recipe.

name: gumbo
review: I've only made Gumbo from a mix...decided to try this recipe, and it really turned out well... the family really enjoyed it...thanks for sharing it...will be saving this one.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: I have made this recipe so many times I can't even count.  I always halve the recipe and the muffins turn out perfect!  I agree with the others who say they taste more like a blueberry cupcake instead of a muffin, but, hey, I'm not complaining.  :)  I have also used chocolate chips instead of blueberries and those are great as well, in fact my sons like the chocolate chip muffins better.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: This was good but I found that the measurements were off. I didn't think that there was enough sauce for all of the pasta plus the sauce was really thick and too salty. Luckily, all I had to do was add more milk and a little broth and everything was fixed! I added sauteed veggies (mushrooms, broccoli and tomatoes) to liven the dish up and make it healthier.

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: There is a very good reason why this recipe has 130 reviews, all 5 stars.........it is delicious and so easy to make! I used a very fat pain (French bread) and we both gobbled it up with our soup today for lunch.............naughty but VERY VERY nice! I made it exactly as posted and used fresh parsley from the garden with fresh local butter, divine thanks Kitten! Merci encore for another wonderful recipe. (Photos to be posted, here with watermarks or on your blog) :-) Karen/FT

name: perfect southern fried chicken
review: Great recipe--my husband said it reminded him of the fried chicken he ate while growing up.  I especially liked your method of covering during the first five minutes--worked great!!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: This is the recipe my daughter-in-law makes and everyone always raves over it.  I finally made it myself and couldn't believe how easy it was to make.  I used COKE instead of ginger ale because that is what I had on hand.  I cooked it about 11 1/2 hours then shredded and added BBQ sauce as directed but put into the fridge overnight.  The next day I cooked it another 3 hours and it was to-die-for!!  Ummm some good cole slaw on top would be the perfect sandwich.  Thanks for sharing a great recipe!!

name: soft italian breadsticks  abm
review: These were super easy and really good!  I halved the recipe and made the recipe by hand instead of using my bread maker.  I was always told that garlic put into the dough would keep it from rising... well no problem here with the garlic powder. After baking, I brushed with a mixture of butter, garlic powder and parsley flakes.  These were WONDERFUL!!  Thanks for sharing Marie!

name: healthy honey oatmeal cookies
review: Delicious. I added sunsweet antioxidant dried fruit blend. It has Blueberries, Cherries, Cranberries, and Plums. Turned out great and I will make them again.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: This is the 448th 5-star review.  Ok, I didn't really check, but if anyone gave this anything less, they are crazy.  This is the perfect muffin! I almost sat in front of the oven and watched the muffins puff up. Barely could wait ten minutes to let them cool. And having a really hard time with just eating one.  So good!  The topping is excellent, I think it makes a little more than you'll need for 12 muffins, but it turns the muffin tops so crunchy and sweet, don't leave it off. Love this recipe!!!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: This was amazing! Far better than any alfredo sauce i've made. I omitted the salt as recommended by others (i agree, it doesn't need it) and used half & half instead of cream since that's all i had on hand.  The half & half worked great but you do have to be careful to not leave it on the heat too long!  The only thing I would change about this next time would be to change the chicken to sauce ratio.  I felt I could almost double the sauce or half the chicken, depending on if i wanted leftovers or not I suppose.  Thanks so much for posting, we'll be making this again and again!

name: mama iuliucci s famous meat a balls  italian meatballs
review: YUM!! My kids gobbled them up, which is more than 5 stars in my book!!! They were so easy to put together, and just full of flavor! I baked mine instead of frying them, that is just a personal choice. Loved, loved, loved these! Thank you for sharing your wonderful recipe!

name: vegetarian  meatballs
review: I subbed out the eggs for 1 Tsp ground flax seeds mixed with 3 Tsp milk for each egg. I also couldn't find powdered veggie broth and so used one of those dried vegetable mixes for dips. They completely fell apart cooking in the water/broth, so I'd skip that step if I make these again. In the end we all decided the onion soup mix was too much, too salty, so I'd also cut that in half or cut it out altogether. Great idea, just didn't suit our tastes.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: Made this the other day and we both loved it. I didn't change a thing. Spicy, but not too spicy, so it suits all tastes. Husband took some to work and thankfully left some for me for lunch the next day.

name: breakfast burritos  once a month cooking
review: These are really great!  The filling possibilities are endless, and a great way to use up leftover ingredients languishing in the fridge.  I like to make them at the end of a big OAMC session to use up my "leftover" chopped ingredients that I had prepared in advance and didn't need all of.  Thanks!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: These were great.  I was out of buns and needed some for supper. I made these in the KA so they were very easy to make too. Thanks for the recipe.

name: zucchini salsa  canned
review: This is wonderful!!!  I have made 1 batch each night the past 2 nights.  It is really easy, cut it up the night before and the next day after lunch finish it up.  I'd leave a cup of two out so we could have it with chips.  Everyone just loves this recipe and what a great way to use up my extra zucchini!  Thank you for posting!  Made for Healthy Choices ABC Tag Game ~ Summer 2010

name: kittencal s famous coleslaw
review: Wonderful recipe!  I threw together a bag of pre-made cabbage and broccoli slaw...did 1-1/2 times the amount for the dressing.  I would make this one again!!!  Thanks for the posting, Kitten!!

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: This was one of the tastiest spinach salads that we have had.  All the ingredients were right on.  Thanks for posting this magnificent spinach salad.  We will use it a lot I'm sure.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: I wasn't sure if I would like this, but it was awesome!  I marinaded my chicken for about 9 hours. yum!

name: pan fried onion dip
review: Wonderful recipe!  I cut the recipe in half as I was only serving to 4 people.  The only thing I did different was add 2 garlic chopped.  I really liked the sour cream/cream cheese/mayo ratio.  Kudos on a great posting!

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: This is a delicious, but so quick to make, tuna casserole.  I sauteed the celery, onions and used fresh garlic.  Also, I grew up on the tuna casserole with peas so I added those.  I loved the flavor of the sauce with the soup, sour cream and milk.  This is one tasty casserole!  I loved it.  Thanks for yet another great recipe.

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Very good!  Made this to go with Recipe #388539.  I don't usually have teriyaki sauce on hand, so this was a good go-to recipe.  Thnx for posting, JuniperNW.

name: chicken pasta milano
review: Very good!  I especially liked this because it was easy to make vegetarian, for my non-meat eating daughter.  My sauce didn't thicken too much, but it sure was delicious!!!

name: momma s fair funnel cake
review: These were very good.  Easy to make.  Thanks for posting.

name: kittencal s easy one bowl vanilla cupcakes
review: Just made for a charity cup-cake drive. They came out large and fluffy and the taste was divine. Thanks for an very easy but wonderful recipe.

name: southern fried chicken
review: Simple and crunchy, though next time I may re-dip into the egg mixture and flour mix for an even crunchier coating.  I did cut back on the hot sauce in the egg mix and feel like I should have cut back to 1/2 c instead of just a few Tablespoons.  Chicken turned out golden, crisp and the meat was SO juicy and tender.  Only tweak I would make to suit my own taste would be to add the seasonings into the flour for more of a punch.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: This was so good, I made it as written but used yellow mustard instead of the whole-grain (DH hates whole-grain). I also added 2T liquid smoke and let marinade for 6 hours. It was a huge hit, everybody loved it. Thanks so much, this is going in the "go-to" folder.

name: allrighty then scrambled eggs   paula deen
review: Delicious! DH raved on about how much he liked these eggs. They were light and fluffy with a nice well balanced flavor. Made as written cutting down to serve two. Thanks so much for the post.

name: cheesecake factory carrot cake cheesecake
review: This recipe does not deserve 5 stars. It deserves 10 stars. I may be partial because carrot cake and cheesecake are my 2 most favorite desserts so putting them together put me over the edge in happiness.  It was delicious.  Next time I will play a little bit more with the time and temperature.  I think I will go a little lower on the temperature and bake it for a little longer.  The very, very middle of the cake was very soft but I couldn't leave it in any longer or the top would have developed cracks. I suggest adding a dash of salt to the cream cheese frosting.  This is a winner of a recipe.

name: cheese tortellini pesto pasta salad
review: My whole family absolutely loved it.  DH repeated more than once, "this is a keeper"; and when he's impressed, I KNOW it's a keeper!  This does make a lot, however.  We ate it for days.

name: turn your crock pot into a smokehouse chicken  smoked chicken
review: Three words sum up this recipe:  TO-DIE-FOR!!!!  So good!!!  I sprayed the crockpot with cooking spray, put 1 1/2 large onions, sliced, on bottom of the crock, then added the chicken that I had coated well with kosher salt,coarsely ground pepper and McCormick's 'Grill Mates Montreal Chicken Seasoning'.  (Rubbed some of the salt & pepper under the skin of the breast and also sprinkled inside the cavity).  Used about 1 or 2 T. Worcestershire Sauce 1/4 c. hickory flavored liquid smoke, 1/4 c. water and then squeezed 1/2 a lemon over top and then stuffed it into the cavity. Cooked on LOW for 12 hours.  YUM-O!!!  Thanks for this wonderful cooking technique ThatBobbieGirl!!  It's a keeper.  NOTE:  This was not overly "smoky" or bland at all!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: The most delicious potatoes I've ever had.  I took these to a cookout tonight and my hosts meat didn't turn out.  No problem, we all gorged on potatoes!  Yes, they are that good!!!

name: betty white s chicken wings
review: Made these wings for a movie night I hosted and they were a huge hit!  They were super easy to make, I like that you marinate and cook them in the same pan.  I used low sodium soy sauce and minced garlic.  After cooking them for 70-75 minutes in the oven I transferred the wings to a crockpot and kept on warm for serving throughout the evening.  I will definitely be making these again!  Thanks for posting!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Made as posted but subbed marjoram for basil. Tasty no-fat low-cal healthy soup! Great to have on hand in the fridge for a quick snack. I will make this often and will try different veggie combinations. Thanks for posting dageret. Made for I Recommend Tag.

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: We thought that this was just ok. It seemed like just too much meat - and we are meat eaters! Thank you for something easy and different though.

name: slow cooker macaroni   cheese
review: My kids are very picky when it comes to Mac n Cheese and they all loved this recipe.  As recommended I omitted the eggs.  This is a keeper!

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Very yummy!  I halved the recipe and would have like to have more apples and less crumble.  Next time I'll use 4 apples and half the crumble.  Thanks for such a simple and delicious dessert!  UPDATE:  I made this for friends using 5 apples and slightly less nutmeg than called for and we devoured it with vanilla ice cream.  So Good!

name: paula deen crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: My kids are very picky when it comes to Mac n Cheese and they all loved this recipe.  As recommended I omitted the eggs.  This is a keeper!

name: broiled tilapia with thai coconut  curry sauce
review: So very yummy!  Nex time I will double the sauce and certainly serve it with plenty of rice.  As good as any restaurant.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: I do love Olive Garden's alfredo, but despite all of the reviews on this one it just didn't quite have enough flavor. I think maybe some yellow onion added with the garlic, some garlic salt and fresh ground pepper helped too. Thank you for giving us a good one to try.

name: beef barley soup
review: This is very good. I made it with sheep. As I put everything in the crockpot, I realized I didn't have any barley in the house so I cooked it without. Then, when it was almost done, I removed 4 cups of liquid, brought it to a boil in a stockpot, added the barley and cooked it separately. Then, I added it all back to the stew. It was yummy and filling.

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: Really good. I don't have a rack, but I poured off the grease halfway through. There was way more sugar/chili mixture than needed; I did add an extra tablespoon of chili powder, which was flavorful but not at all spicy. We had them for dinner and enjoyed them thoroughly!

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: Delicious! Loved it! Thanks for posting!

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: Loved this!!  I used recipe #96988, "Turn Your Crock Pot Into a Smokehouse Chicken" (about 1/2 of the prepared smoked chicken that had been deboned) and chopped and mixed it up in the recipe with about 1 T. dried minced onions and 1/4 t. cumin and added it to the rest of the seasoning called for in the recipe.  Cooked it 1 hour, added the cheese and let it sit for awhile to absorb the rest of the liquid. So flavorful!!  Thanks for sharing..it's a keeper.

name: easy peezy pizza dough  bread machine pizza dough
review: This was really easy crust to make, and I can't complain...but next time I may add some seasonings to add a bit more flavor. Thanks for posting!

name: chicken garlic bites
review: Great coating for chicken! Loved it! Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Yummy way to cook chicken breasts. Nice and garlicky, reminded me of chicken kiev.

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: This was very good. My glaze did not thicken. Because many people here have mentioned having the same problem, I think I would add cornstarch as a thickener if I make it again.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: I left out the potato, subbed the margarine for oil, use 4 c. rice cooked in veggie broth instead of the chicken, and subbed the chicken broth with veggie broth and the half and half for soy milk as well. We were pretty happy with this, though I may add in more pepper and other spices next time and swap out 1 c. of the rice with another veggie -- peas probably. Thanks for sharing!

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Delish! A great way of using up stale bread. I'm a big garlic lover though so I would have ampted up the garlic and I found mine only needed to cook for about 8 minutes. Will make again!

name: strawberry julius
review: Very good.  My strawberry loving kids loved it.  I have two kids who don't like strawberries so they didn't try it.  I used fresh strawberries and I used ice instead of water.

name: beef patties in onion gravy
review: good for a really fast recipe

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: Awesome recipe, thanks!

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: These were simple and tasty. I was feeling lazy and didn't clip the wings. We ate these as an appetizer and they were really enjoyed. Thanks Marie for sharing the recipe. Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: Like all the many others who have tried this recipe, I really like it!  I had some fresh spinach that I needed to use quickly while it was still fresh, and I looked at many recipes.  This one seemed the easiest and sounded really good, and it was both easy and good.  Thanks for inventing this good spinach pie!

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Sauteeing the onions prior to boiling them to make the soup would definitely make it taste richer, but even without this step, the soup still cooked up delicious. After smashing the potatoes, the soup thickened considerably so that not much stirring was needed upon adding the cream cheese to it. Easy preparation. This was inhaled by my children. Thank you for sharing.

name: basil pesto
review: Very Nice Pesto!  I used 2 cups of basil leaves, upped the oil to 1/4 cup, added 1 teaspoon salt  and used roasted sunflower seeds over the pine nuts.  Great color, love the lemon bite and will be using this recipe all summer as I have 4 basil plants that are over 2 and a half feet tall.  Thanks for posting, Di ;-)

name: white almond sour cream wedding cake
review: the kids and my husband enjoyed it. i only chose this recipe because i was looking for a recipe to use 8 egg whites i had. didn't want to throw it away so found this. should've just made fried rice w/ the left over egg whites because of course this recipe makes a ton. but i shared some w/ the neighbors and they loved it too.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: Excellent! Quick and yummy.  I didn't even have enough cheese and they still tasted great! I will be making these again!

name: homemade rice a roni
review: YUMMM!!  I added garlic and onions and some seasonings such as italian seasoning.  I think that this is one of these recipes that is open for interpretation.  My boyfriend was so excited to get homemade rice a roni.  I am so glad I found this recipe.  Thank you!!

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: So delicious!  I added 8 oz. of sliced baby bellas that I sauteed with the onions.  I also added extra garlic since we are garlic lovers!  Thank you so much for sharing!  YUM!!!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: Having some pork cutlets to use up ,I decided to use this recipe. I baked them for  half the time without the sauce and when adding the sauce I baked them for 30 minutes. I did add a bit of dill to the soup mixture. They were wonderful and a dish I will make again soon. I will use pork chops next time. Thanks for sharing this great recipe.

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: the first evening we made 30 mini muffins for youngest daughter church night doing the recipe as is......the next night we made 2 mini loaves and 2 med loaves using 1/2 cup marg and 1/2 cup applesauce.....very moist and very tasty and very very good!!
