review: I have made this for years and everyone always loves it.  The only difference is I use cake mix with pudding.  If you do this then omit the package of pudding and decrease the water to 1/4 cup.  Also for a little different taste you can use Coconut Rum and a lemon cake mix.  Thanks for posting.

name: gumbo
review: This was crazy good! It wasn't so spicy my 2 and 4 yr old couldn't eat it.  They loved it too!  My husband and I added a dash of tabasco to ours to spice it up.  Next time I make it, I'll use butter to make my roux, only because I love the taste.  I added okra and instead of a red pepper, I added a can of diced tomatoes because we like a tomato base.  This was awesome and will now replace my old recipe.  Thanks!

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Wonderful! I did follow the advise of other reviewers. I omitted the butter, used 1/2 pint of sour cream, I did use cream of mushroom (that is what I had), and stirred 1/2 way through cooking time. Better that Cracker Barrel's!!

name: kittencal s marinade for grilled steak
review: This is an outstanding marinade for steaks! I used it for a dinner with guests and everyone thought it was better than a steakhouse marinade. Thanks for another winner, Kitten!

name: oreo balls
review: You can't beat these!  Love them!!  We just used Ghirardelli dark chocolate and white chips to dip in and they worked just great.

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: So - Potatoes, cream cheese, butter, sour cream, chives, green onions and a bit of other things?!  What is not to like?  These were, of course, yummy.  Convenient to be made ahead and brought to a party and reheated (microwave....)  They were even good being made into potato patties in the skillet the next day....

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: THIS needs 100 Stars!  This is the best Spaghetti Sauce I have ever had, including restaurants!  We had company over for dinner and everyone wanted the recipe.  My son was going fishing, and I had him taste the sauce (just as I put it on to simmer) and he stayed home to eat!  NOTHING has ever kept him from fishing, need I say more!

name: perfect turkey in an electric roaster oven
review:
EXCELLANT!!!!! Outside of a smoked turkey, this is THEE best I have ever eaten, BAR NONE!!!
I used olive oil & seasoned with LAWRY'S Chicken & Poultry Seasoning. A 9 lb. turkey, stuffed in my 12 qt. NESCO roaster took 3-1/2 hours on the button! The meat was VERY moist & fell off the bone. THANK YOU for this detailed recipe idea!!!!!! MERRY CHRISTMAS to you & yours!!!

name: kittencal s famous coleslaw
review: Wonderful coleslaw.  I had to use bottled lemon juice (would have been better with fresh) and used homemade mayonaise.  Definitely a keeper.  Thanks Carol

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Used a pork/beef mixture.  Used kittencal's sauce cooked in the crockpot.  Topped with meatballs and cooked on low 12 hours.

name: the best snickerdoodles i have ever eaten
review: Easy to make and very tasty! Made as posted and this will be made often now. Thank you GloriaAnn.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: Not that this needs another review but I just have to give it a glowing one! This bundt cake was so so so moist and chocolaty. I'm usually not a fan of using box mixes but this didn't taste too synthetic. Definitely a keeper - especially when I need to thow something together last minute or need a quick chocolate fix!

name: awesome baked ham
review: I made this for the second time (can't believe I didn't review this last year!) for Christmas dinner and it was so amazing!  Last year I used a whole ham and got rave reviews.  This year I used a 12 lb half ham and my "foody" nephew told me it the best thing he'd ever eaten!  So easy to make and the results make you look like "super chef".  I cooked for about 3 hours and let it rest for another hour or so without uncovering.  I can tell you now that this will be the only way I'll be making ham from now on!  Thank you for posting!

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Super delicious! I made these for Christmas dinner. I love brussel sprouts, but hate it when they are soggy.  I've made this recipe 3 or 4 times now and just love the way the outer leaves get nice and brown, and the inner part stays a little bit crispy.  I used 20 sprouts and couldn't fit them all in the pan cut side down, so I did it that way with as many as would fit, then just threw the rest of them in on top.  They eventually all got browned and I left the garlic in the pan - love it when it gets all carmelized!  At the end of the night, there were only about 6 halves left - and brussel sprouts are one of those things that not everyone likes!.  Thanks for posting this great recipe!

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: These were very good but not excellent. We thought they were a little on the dry side.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: This was wonderful! Used the frozen salmon filet portions (thawed) from Costco, Panko, and dried parsley but otherwise followed exactly. Regular bread crumbs would probably have been better, but this is the best salmon I've had outside the roadside stands in Alaska!

name: crunchy granola
review: Easy and yummy. What more can be said? Made with dried cherries, apples and cranberries. Given in Christmas baskets this year, and I'm sure will be on the list for next year as well. Thank you!

name: peanut butter cup cookies  tarts
review: This was a great addition to my cookie platter.  It was incredibly easy and so darn good!  I don't think you could go wrong with this one. I was a little surprised that I had to bake the cookies for the  full 10 minutes, I often find that most things are done in my oven on the low end of the time line.

name: uncle bill s method for cooking turkey
review: I considered trying this recipe for Thanksgiving, but did not. A few days before Christmas, I bought a fresh turkey on sale (Butterball natural) for 49 cents per pound and decided that this would be a good time to test the recipe.  Boy, we were impressed!  Crispy skin, tender meat, relatively easy directions...who could ask for more?!!  Thanks Uncle Bill!

name: amazing white trash puff balls
review: These are really the ultimate blank canvas for appetizers. I used the garlic butter flavored cresent rolls and stirred in some shredded parm to the cheese mix. They were a big hit, the whole time I stuffing them in my face I was thinking of other stuffing add ins that would be good! (chopped bacon, green onions, cheddar, horseradish...

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: Despite all of the rave review this didn't do it for us. I was looking for something else...thank you though.

name: famous challah
review:
I made this for our traditional Polish Christmas Eve dinner and everyone loved it! I know it is a Jewish bread, but Poles serve it (called chalka) as part of the traditional dinner on Christmas Eve. My husband and father-in-law were particularly happy with it as it brought back memories of their grandmother and mom who made it every year.
Although I bake bread often, I was so impressed with how this turned out---it was beautiful and delicious. It was not difficult to make either. This will definitely be my "go to" recipe for challah--it made me look like a rock star in the kitchen. Thanks for posting!

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: To save time I used whole boneless, skinless, frozen chicken breasts and increased the cook time. About an hour before it was finished I took the chicken breasts out and shredded them and returned them to the pot. I also added a can of corn (drained) and a can of white beans (drained). We loved it!

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: Brilliant recipe - very tasty and creamy.  Best part was being able to make earlier in the day along with the turkey stuffing and then letting them stay piping hot in the slow cooker until Christmas dinner was ready to be served. Added a bit of butter just before serving - still smooth and creamy even after hours on warm in the slow cooker. Made my day in the kitchen so much easier - thank you!

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: Good recipe, our pork turned out a tad dry. We liked the herbs and onions. Thanks for posting.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: My husband liked this alot. I thought it was an average tasting mac and cheese recipe.

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: Just what I needed to use up some ripe bananas and some homemade canned blueberries.  Easy recipe and very delicious!

name: hello dollies
review: I made this to have with coffee at my family's Boxing day get together.  I cut into smaller pieces - just big enough to pop into your mouth & not need a plate. They were soooo good.  We don't have Hello Dollies here in Australia....so it was nice find a sweet that none of my guests had heard of before  Thank you for sharing.

name: chicken pesto
review: This has quickly become our favorite way to do chicken breasts. I made it for the third time tonight and it is absolutely delicious.  I could not find packaged pesto either and used a jar of it instead and also use the entire package of provolone, 2 slices each breast.  So good and impossibly easy to prepare.  This is a great beginner cook's recipe to impress friends and family with.  A simple side of asiago stuffed ravioli and we ate like royalty tonight.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: I guess I'm a detractor %u2014 I found this frosting TOO stiff and too sweet. I piped it on cupcakes. Not my favorite!

name: microwave poached eggs
review: Another good one Paula.  So easy.  My DH loves poached eggs and until this way, I hated fooling with them.  Thanks for posting.

name: kittencal s chinese chicken balls with sweet and sour sauce
review:
This is a great recipe--well, great two recipes! I've used the batter for onion rings and shrimp and the sauce is amazing (used pineapple juice). I made the full recipe and cut the white sugar to 1/2 c and it was perfect to my tastes--if the amount of sugar is an issue start with less and keep track of your own preference as you adjust/add more to suit your tastes.

I know the takeout sauce is clearer but the flavor is right so I usually double it up and freeze some for when I make egg rolls and fried rice. Going to use the batter for Sweet and Sour Pork also. My friends mom used to make it and with her dish in mind I will add sliced blanched carrots, chopped green bell pepper, chopped sweet onion and pineapple tidbits to the sauce and it will be like her dish:)

I season the chicken before battering it w/ Paula Deen's House Seasoning (salt, pepper and garlic powder).

name: ciabatta  italian slipper bread
review: Love this bread. It's very forgiving as far a timing goes, and it comes out perfect every time. I rarely make white breads, but when I do, this is usually the one.

name: chocolate  chocolate  chocolate  bundt cake with chocolate glaze
review: Followed the recipe; it was very easy to make and had most of the ingredients on hand.  The cake was nice and moist and the chocolate glaze%u2026 over the top tasty.  If you like chocolate, you will love this recipe.  I will definitely make this wonder bundt again!

name: better than sex cake iii
review: Good cake, makes a lot of servings, 15 I would say.  I needed to 'baste' the top of the cake to get all of the sauces into it and wound up using a bigger diameter spoon handle.  Otherwise, very easy.

name: white pizza or pizza blanca
review: I make this suing biscuits from a can pushed together and made into a crust.  Also good with any other pizza crust.  Always a crowd pleaser, fast, and easy.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: This is so easy to do.  And the taste is great.  Probably that next time I'll use only 1/2 tsp of salt.  It was a little bit too salty for our taste.  Thanks LAURIE :)  Made for Holiday tag game

name: mashed sweet potatoes
review: Wonderful! I followed recipe with the following additions: a tsp of Gran Marnier and a 1/4 tsp of ground ginger. Loved them!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: tasted good although I messed it up a bit. I used cheddar-jack cheese mix and a bit of fontina (all I had at the time), so the taste was very mild. I also used 1/2 cup heaving whipping cream  1 1/2 cups 2% milk (also what I had). I had a problem when adding cheese to the bechamel. The whole thing became too thick and a bit separated (small amount of oil oozed out of the sauce). I suspect that I may have reduced bechamel sauce too much. I flavored the dish with 1/2 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp black pepper. I will try with sharp cheddar cheese next time. In addition, I think I can go for lower calories version by using 3 tbsp butter with 3 tbsp flour.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Very good!  I made just a couple small changes, to suit my family's taste.  I increased the garlic powder to 1 teaspoon (one can never have too much garlic!) Added 8 oz. sliced mushrooms along with the broccoli and onion, and added chopped roma tomato and water chestnuts near the end of cooking.  I'll definitely be making this again.  Thank you for posting this here.

name: 100  whole grain wheat bread
review: Terrific bread! Tasty and toasts well too. Rather than using regular whole wheat flour (hard red wheat), I used white whole wheat flour, which is milled from hard white spring wheat. It yields a lighter, milder loaf. I also added a couple Tbsp of vital wheat gluten. Thanks for posting.

name: impossible peanut butter cookies
review: What an easy and delicious cookie this is.  I used 1/2 Xylitol sweetener in mine to cut back on the sugar and the cookies were super.  Hubby loves these and I'll make them again, thanks for a really great recipe!

name: mom s chocolate cupcakes
review: A nice, spongey cupcake. I will use milk next time--and maybe chocolate chips!--for a richer cupcake. Thank you for posting.

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: Excellent rolls! I make a lot of yeast rolls and these were fantastic. Light, wonderful flavor, and the dough is very easy to work with. Only change I made was to use regular unbleached flour with the addition of 2 T vital wheat gluten (I stopped buying bread flour years ago). Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: tsr version of starbucks pumpkin scones by todd wilbur
review: Wonderful! Everyone loved these! I went ahead and used all of the spiced glaze which, on top of the white glaze, was too much icing for my tastes. Next time I'd probably make half the spiced glaze and use as a drizzle. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: Great crust easy to make and nice and flaky.  The only change I made was that I used butter instead of shortening.  Thanks

name: quick yellow cake
review: Great flavor! Used butter and topped with chocolate frosting. I'm giving this 5 stars even though I overbaked the cake, 35 minutes was too long, so it was a little drier than it should have been. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Yummy. Kids loved it with mini marshmallows and choc chips. I'm not so crazy about stuff in my brownies but will try it without another time. Maybe I'll try the suggestion for fudge sauce (17309) and poking holes - can't have too much chocolate!

name: pan release  professional pan coating  better than pam spray
review:
Wow, I'm surprised I didn't review this when I made it a couple months ago. It is fantastic, plus it is a must to keep your non-stick pans gunk-free. I just got a new set of Calphalon non-stick pans for Christmas and they specifically say "do not use spray pan release."

Love finding a better way to do things!

name: old fashioned banana cream pie
review: This is a family favorite, my Mom still make this for special occasions and now I am make it for family and friends.  Thanks for posting

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: GREAT split pea soup!  Made exactly as directed except accidentally used 2 quarts water but it turned out perfectly and I wouldn't change a thing.  This will be a regular at my house.  Perfectly seasoned -- a rich and hearty soup that is so easy to make that it is unbelievable!

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Wow!!  Very good!!  Didn't change a thing.  Next time I will add more garlic . . . I threw them back in the pan with the sprouts and they were just perfect.  Thanks so much for posting!!  :O)

name: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
review: My son called these "amazing".  They always go fast.  I made them once as drop cookies and the second time I formed balls and smashed them slightly.  That was nice.  I also used half chocolate chips and half red and green M & M's for Christmas and those were very pretty.  Very dependable.

name: queso blanco dip
review: My teens and young adults really liked it.  Hubby and I thought it needed a lot more kick.  However, it's an easy, yummy base to add to.  Thanks so much.

name: boeuf bourguignon a la julia child
review: Wonderful!  I only used two cups of broth and would recommend using three.  The meat was so tender!  It is far more work than I'm used to going to but worth it for an amazing meal.

name: the best ever waffles
review: These are exceptional! I love, love, love, the egg-whites that are whipped to stiff peaks and then slowly being incorporated into this mix. These came out perfectly --> and since the "appear" lighter - people ate more, and left none for the cook, (me). Either way, sensational and you know you have a lovely recipe that can and obviously will be handed down to off-spring. Thanks for posting!! The Longmeadow Farm loved this!

name: easy garlic rice
review: This was a quick and delicious rice dish. Just a little something different than plain rice and I'm sure I'll be making it again. I used Jasmati rice but otherwise followed the recipe exactly and we really enjoyed the flavor. I think I'll try adding some toasted almonds next time for a little more of a nutty spin. Thanks for a great recipe.

name: roast turkey
review: Delicious, very moist and flavorful!  I did not find it necessary to brown during the last 15 minutes, but next time I will not cover the legs and wings unless they start to brown too much.  I will definitely make this again.  Thanks!

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: Wow!  Charlotte, I always thought Angel Food Cake was boring - I was wrong!  The flavor and texture of this cake is divine.  Thank you for a true keeper.

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: Tasty pancake! follow the recipe exactly and cook in a nonstick pan with cooking spray. It's light and fluffy, not too oily at all. Served with blueberry pie filling and whipped cream.

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: Forgot to rate this keeper!  WONDERFUL.  Easy to work with, produces light fluffy rolls, my family cannot get enough of these.  I make two full batches every Thanksgiving, one for dinner and one for leftovers!  These are the first thing gone!  Thanks for a great one, have made many many times and always just terrific.  Made exactly as directed!

name: caesar pork chops
review: Delicious!!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: What a way to start off the New Year -- this pie was awesome!  My hubby, who does not like apple pie, had two slices and I am having to ration it in order to keep him from eating the rest of it!  This recipe will definitely be in my "go to" file for great desserts!

name: uncle bill s green split pea with hambone soup
review: I made this last week and forgot to review this.  WONDERFUL...if I could give more than 5 stars I would.  Followed the directions only adding 3 minced garlic cloves and 2 diced potatoes....heaven.  Definately going into my Favorites of 2010.  Thank you Uncle Bill for submitting such a delicious recipe.

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: I'll add my five star review to the list. Great soup. I added the wine, doubled the carrots and celery and used diced tomatoes with green peppers. Thanks for posting such a delicious recipe.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: I've been making the same lasagna for over 50 years - the recipe from Better Homes & Garden.  I've always really liked it.  Rather than dig out my recipe, I looked on Food.com to see if i could find a similar one.  This was really close, but used more meat and more spices.  This was awesome - I won't be going back to my old recipe - this is the one I will use from now on.  Thanks so much for posting.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Excellent! I caramelized the carrots along with some celery and baby potatoes, quartered and added before the final simmer. We both loved this stew. The hoisin gives the dish a bit of a different flavour that would be hard for anyone to pinpoint. We didn't find it too sweet at all.

name: best baked potato
review: These potatoes were good.  I did notice they needed a bit more time than 1 hr in the oven, so I will remember that next time.  We used large ones, but... they just weren't as soft as we like them.  Also, next time, I will definitely be using Kosher salt.  Thanks for the great recipe!

name: cheat n  eat vietnamese chicken soup
review: We really loved this!  I think it is as close to Pho as I'll be able to get at home.  I made some minor changes - added 2 small, thinly sliced leaks, and didn't use cilantro (just because the cilantro at the market was old and wilty).  I thought that the broth seemed a little too chickeny flavored - it was sort of overpowering the ginger - so I added some water (about a cup or so) and that really made it good.  At the end, I added some napa cabbage.  We also topped it with some sambal oelek and plum sauce.  Loved the flavor, but I think it would be even better if I let it sit overnight, so I'm thinking that next time (probably later this week) I'll do a double or triple batch of the broth, then freeze half of it and other half in the fridge overnight.  We'll definitely be making this a lot in the future!  Thank you for posting!

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: This was delicious, and pretty easy to put together.  The wine did add a nice depth of flavor.  Next time, I may use my stick blender to puree a bit of the veggies, but I'll definitely leave some alone for texture.  Thanks for sharing!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: Excellent!  What can I say that hasn't been said already?  A definite keeper!

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Family lore tells that my first sentence was I demanding my slice of pizza pie.  Becoming creative, I used this with recipe #223590.  Made for Soups and Breads Recipe Tag.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: I saw this recipe on the weekly newsletter and knew I had to try it.  I used a nice English chuck roast.  I quartered two onions and put them on the bottom of the pot.  Seared the roast on all sides (seasoned with some garlic pepper).  The I put the roast in the crock pot and topped with the gravy/dressing mixture.  I poured a cup of water around the roast so that I would have more gravy.  Cooked on low for 8 hours and mmmmmmm...was rewarded with a tender, yummy, mouthwatering roast dinner.  Thank you so much for sharing, yooper.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: Great casserole!  Used some leftover shredded chicken, about 2 cups, and 2% velveeta, only had 6 oz so I also added some shredded sharp cheddar to the top of the dish last 10 minutes of baking, after stirring to mix.  Son and DH enjoyed it, hubby said 4 stars, wish I could give 4 1/2 just becuase the hardest part of this meal was waiting for the pasta water to boil.  Will absolutely make again, good stuff!

name: the most wonderful gingerbread cookies
review: We loved this recipe.  We included these in our 2010 holiday trays for family and friends.  What I liked the most from these cookies is they stayed soft even after a couple days.  The kids had a blast decorating them, we used both a boy and girl cookie cutters.  The flavor of these are delightful and just screams the holidays.  Also, the house smell so wonderful when baking these.  Thank you for sharing this gem of a recipe.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Made this for the gazzillionth time for Christmas Eve.  Took a few ideas from another recipe and used chicken broth in place of water,and added 1/2 cup melted butter.  I started them in the oven at 375* covered with foil, for 40 min, then increased oven temp to 425*.  Baked them another 40 min uncovered.  It is a VERY forgiving recipe when you must accommodate times and temps to make everything come out together.  Thanks so much, Evelyn -- a real keeper !

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: We included these cookies in our 2010 holiday trays for family and freinds.  They looked so festive with the dried cranberries and they tasted wonderful.  I couldn't quit nibbling.  Thank you for sharing this tasty recipe with us.

name: easy  festive chocolate holiday pretzels
review: Oh I LOVED LOVED LOVED these little gems.  We included these in our 2010 holiday trays and everyone loved them.  I really like dipped pretzels but these are so much more festive looking, they are my go to from now on.  We used regular kisses and hugs, but next year the kids want to experiment with the different flavors.  Thank you so much for sharing this recipe with us.

name: enchilada sauce
review: This is a very good enchilada sauce. I made as directed except for two things - I was short on tomato sauce by 2 ounces so I made up for it with 2 extra ounces of salsa. I also cut the water to one cup after reading other reviews that it was thin, and thought it was just right. I'm looking forward to using this on some spinach enchiladas and over frijoles refritos. Thanks for sharing!

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Cant remember how this tasted but I did make it so I wanted to flag it as such.

name: peppermint candy cane bark
review: Oh what a lovely treat.  We included these in our 2010 holiday trays.  This is such an easy recipe to make but tastes like it took much more work.  These added such a festive look to our trays, thank you so much for sharing this with us.

name: cheat n  eat vietnamese chicken soup
review: It does not get much more easy than this - the soup is very versatile and you could almost add whatever has your fancy or is in your fridge, but still not quite like Pho - but good.

name: long john silver s fish batter
review: This was perfect light batter for fish and chicken! We thought it was pretty darn close to LJS but like another reviewer stated, the oil has something to do with it also. We enjoyed it, and it was nice and easy to put together too! Thanks for posting.

name: hawaiian chicken kabobs
review: We loved these kabobs.  The marinade reminded me of a teriyaki sauce and we really like that.  I omitted the cherry tomatoes (personal preference) but added some onions.  I let the chicken marinate for about 2 1/2 hours before skewering and then brushed it on while grilling.  I also saved some to serve on the table.  We served this with some rice pilaf and dinner rolls.  Thank you so much for sharing this yummy meal with us.

name: old fashioned corn and potato chowder
review: This was very good. I felt like it was missing something but I can't put my finger on what. It was better the next day for lunch; maybe it just needs some time for the flavors to blend.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: My daughter and I decided to try these in place of our traditional cut-out recipe this year. The reviews were mixed.  My son liked the cookies very much. My daughter and I thought they were OK but nothing great.  My husband said we didn't have to make them again.

name: mean guy s general tso s chicken
review: I had read all the reviews before making this and listened to doubling of the sauce and I am so glad I did.  This was the most delicious General Tso I have had..it was the perfect blend of flavors. Not too sweet but sweet enough, spicy hot but not overly and not salty at all. I didn't find a problem with any of it.  I followed the recipe but as I said I doubled the sauce, I did add in some spring onions, a little garlic and fresh ginger and sprinkled some toasted sesame over the cooked dish. After I did the second stage cooking  I took the chicken out of the pan and kept warm and then cooked the sauce till it caramelized then re-added the chicken and mixed then served. This worked out perfectly, with the chicken having a nice crispiness to it. I give this recipe high praises and will do this restaurant quality recipe again. But I too will definitely recommend to anyone making it to double the sauce minimum.  Can't wait till I make it again, I served mine with some spring rolls I had made, perfect for a lunch. Thanks Kirstin for adopting this recipe and to keep sharing it.

name: kittencal s perfect prime rib roast beef
review: This made for a perfect Christmas Day Dinner for my Daughter and myself, Kitten !!  This was perfection on a plate. Oh so tender and juicy with such a delicious flavor. The roast had a perfect amount of fat that I loved. I was very generous with the garlic cloves, I am sure I used all 8 or perhaps 10. When I opened my fridge in the morning after it being in there overnight all I smelled was garlic, maybe I should of put it in a ziplock bag in the fridge.  I was so impressed on how easy it was to prepare and cook. Although I realize now I need to buy a new meat thermometer.. I think it was off a little bit, but it still worked out great. The au jus was such a wonderful addition to this dish, which my DD loved over her mashed potatoes. Thanks so much for recommending this recipe Kitten, it was the best ... A definite keeper that I will make again soon..

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: i really enjoyed this alot. it was full of flavor. love it! this will go into my favorites file. i forgot to spray the pan w/ cooking spray so i was nervous about it all sticking but luckily i used glassware and it was alot easier to clean compared to if i used a roasting pan of some sort. all i had to do was drench it w/ hot water for a couple minutes and the brown bits that stuck was easy to scrub away. next time i may try parchment paper at the bottom. LOVE parchment paper, i use it for everything if i'm in fear of anything sticking.

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: My husband thought that calling this the Best Chili You Will Ever Taste was a little presumptuous.  But after eating it I think he might agree. At least One of the Best Chilis You Will Ever Taste.  I omitted the brown sugar, as so many reviewers seemed to be cutting it back so much.  Next time I might try adding a little bit, but we thought it was delicious without it as well!

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: Kitten this has to be the first recipe of yours I have done where you say don't add more than 2 tsp of garlic..LOL......I followed the recipe except I used about half the package of the chopped spinach, I am surprised my DD didn't notice it. She actually had 2 of them with your recipe of Caesar Salad and Garlic Croutons. WOW...and she is still a size 2 !!! Also with the 1 1/2 cups of Mozzarella, it was a blend of mozzarella and 4 other cheeses that I used. And it was just mozzarella that I sprinkled on top when it was cooking along with a bit of parmesan. I had made 10 manicotti. I also had them for lunch on the Monday with the salad again because they were just so good and I froze some of them for later lunches. We had this for New Years Day Dinner and it was absolutely the best. Wonderful way to bring in the New Year, with my Daughter and a Yummy dinner. Thanks for sharing this great recipe of yours Kitten..

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: We thought this was a very good dish. I didn't use celery and I only used 1 pie crust.  I also used skim milk instead of half and half because that was all we had on hand. After we ate this, I quickly made another one to put in the freezer.  This really doesn't take much work using the fresh veggies. I did add some peas to it though, as I thought it needed more veggies. Thanks for sharing this delicious meal.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: yummy! used russets as thats what i had. bout 5 or 6 cloves of garlic, used mediterranean spiced sea salt in place of regular and added just a touch more regular salt to make up for the addition of the few spices. omitted parm chz and added 4 more Tbsp of butter. went very well with salisbury steak!!! thanks mizz nezz!!

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: I would give this more than five stars if I could.  I've been making this for years now and it just gets better and better!  My hubby and stepfather LOVE this and request it often!!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Good, easy, fast healthy.  Needs a bit more spice for our tastes though.

name: gumbo
review: January in Louisiana is perfect gumbo weather.  (Cut my finger while chopping the veggies, but who needs 'em anyway?)  Made for Soups and Breads Recipe Tag.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Love this recipe!!!  DH is a HUGE fan of pulled pork and he wanted this several days in a row.  I made as posted and it is very easy.  Thanks so much for posting a keeper!!

name: creamed ground beef sos
review: This was good.  I made this and served with some whole grain rotini.  My family liked this very much.  Next time I would like to try it on mashed potatoes.  We liked mincing some fresh onion on top for more flavor.  Thank you for sharing with us.

name: cheat n  eat vietnamese chicken soup
review: I was in a pinch for time and didn't have anything out for supper.  I found your recipe and thawed a couple chicken breasts out and made this for our meal.  I doubled the recipe and we ate it all.  My kids kept coming back for seconds (and thirds)!!!  DH and I really liked the green onions and cilantro for the garnish.  They really added alot more flavor.  Thank you for sharing this quick and delicious soup recipe with us.  We will use again.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Perrrrrrrrfect!  Ate so many while cooling that I dont think the kids will get many.  thanks for sharing!

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: My husband said this is THE BEST DESSERT he's EVER had! Better than any donut! That is the ultimate compliment in his book! Thanks for the recipe!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Easy and enjoyable!  I used a jar of black bean and corn salsa, reduced fat cream cheese, and frozen corn.  We had the first batch served in taco shells served with chopped lettuce, tomato, onion, avocado, and cilantro as toppings.  It was great!  I plan to try the leftovers over rice next.  Thanks for sharing!

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Quick and easy.  I liked that it wasn't too sweet and there was lots of great apple taste.  Will make again.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Amazing. The sauce is great on salads, so make double.

name: tzatziki
review: Great, served with kibbeh over spinach salad as a dressing.  We made it without olive oil.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Just like mom used to make except now we have pre-grated cheese! I thought about making it with just milk after I found my cream was chunky, but I used a heavy cream substitute (1/3 cup melted butter whisked into 3/4 cup milk). I did add 1/4 tsp dry mustard and used Panko on top. Had to broil it a little to get the Panko to crisp up.

name: pizza dough and sauce
review: We made this last night and it was great.  I used my Kitchenaid to do the mixing and the kneading and that made it so easy.  And the sauce is fantastic. We really liked this pizza, we added sausage, canadian bacon, pepperoni, green peppers, onions, mushrooms and black olives.  Mmmmmmmmm  delicious, thank you for sharing your recipe with us.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: I have made this several times and my boys love it!  Quick, easy and delicious!  Thanks for sharing!

name: oreo balls
review: these are yummy...and so no diet friendly  :-)  but, you must must must use a food processor to get the right consistency.  these are in my permanent collection of recipes

name: monterey chicken rolls
review: Oh my goodness....this is so good.  I made this for our supper tonight and we loved it.  The breading on the chicken was super yummy and how can you beat chicken stuffed with cheese??  Thank you so much for a meal my family ALL loved.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: YUM!!!  No wonder this was one of the top five recipes of the year!  So easy and so moist, tender and flavorful.  I will be making this one again!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: Somewhat disappointed in the taste.  Doubt I will make again.

name: perfect turkey in an electric roaster oven
review: Excellent turkey!  It was hard not to peek, but it turned out great!  I used a leave-in thermometer that beeped when done.  The turkey looked a little overdone, but it was really moist and juicy... everyone including my turkey shunning guests loved it.  Thanks for sharing!

name: tilapia al ajillo  garlic tilapia
review: We thought this was delicious and will make this again.  I really liked the garlic flavor in this.  I used fish with the skin still on so it got nice and crispy......so good.  We all enjoyed this very much and we all thank you for sharing with us.

name: awesome baked ham
review: Wonderful ham.  It was easy and had wonderful flavor.  DH loved it.  Served with Sweet Potato Souffle.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: These brownies were so easy and oh so good!  I had all of the ingredients on hand. Much better than box brownies.

name: thai coconut rice
review:
I loved it. Great simple flavors. I did add almonds, but I toasted them. And I didn't add the crystallized ginger, but would of. It just - it worth going to the store for just the garnish. If I had company I would of, and I know it would of been very good.

1 change and 1 suggestion.
- I did add a bit of cilantro for a little color and a bright flavor with the rich coconut milk. Just 1 1/2 teaspoons. I enjoyed the bright flavor.
- I would of added maybe just a scallion diced, but didn't have any. Just a bit of fresh bright green color to me is all I needed.

Second, I followed cooking directions for the rice that was on my package. I used basmati. I checked my long grain, basmati and jasmine and they all had different times, so I think maybe that is why people said it took longer to cook. My package direction said 25 and that is just about how long it took.

I think it is just common sense to check. Not all stoves or pots cook the same. As is no rice directions are the same. I just cooked until tender. Cooking times to me are a guideline and should be used that way.

Also, follow the ingredients as is. A recipe like this really benefits from fresh ginger and the red pepper flakes. That is what sets this aside from other rice dishes.

Very nice dish. I served it with a Thai chicken and loved it. Have just a bit leftover for lunch tomorrow. I sliced up the little bit of leftover chicken for a perfect light lunch.
Thx for a nice recipe
Kim

name: caramelized butternut squash
review:
I made this for dinner tonight and loved it. I didn't have a problem pealing the squash, so didn't heat or boil it to soften.
I made 1/2 the recipe (had only 1 squash) and it made a whole large sheet pan full.I used 4 T. of butter and it was plenty. The only thing different from the recipe was adding a handful of walnuts to the mix. My DH is not the greatest fan of butternut squash but the walnuts really gave it a nutttier and mellower taste. (He ate all of his serving, so guess he was happy with it.)
I really loved it, so will make this again.
Thanks to Chef1532306 who suggested adding the walnuts, and to you Pianolady for posting. Donna

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: Very good.  Made as directed.  Will make again.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: Fabulous cinnamon rolls!!

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Very good meatballs. So simple yet delicious! Thanks for sharing.

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Awesome low-fat recipe. My changes: used 1/2 cup buttermilk (because my bananas weren't super ripe), only 1/2 cup   3 tbsp brown sugar, 4 tbsp semi-sweet choc chips, 2 tbsp macadamia nut. I baked it in a loaf pan at 350F and it's done in less than 40 mins.

name: boeuf bourguignon a la julia child
review: My sister made this a few days ago and told me I NEEDED to make it.  (I think she used a recipe off Oprah's website - same thing, right?)  I may make a couple of procedural changes next time I make it, as I found the meat to be a tad underseasoned (easily remedied by salting before hand).  And I think I'm going to make my own beef stock next time, as I think that will improve the flavor, as well.  I used a Merlot as the wine, left the onion slices and carrots in because I was too lazy to pick them out.  I also used already cut stew meat to save time.  Don't think I'll do that again, either, as I don't think it has as much flavor as a whole roast you cut yourself.  The mushrooms and pearl onions were sublime, and I loved the smoky undertones from the bacon.  I will be looking forward to the next time I make this, in order to follow the recipe more closely and taste the differences.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: Yummy potatoes. This was really simple and delicious. Thanks Mimi for a nice keeper. Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: This was a really nice broccoli recipe.  Came out perfect and I loved the ease and simplicity.  The only change we made was to use olive oil instead of vegetable oil.  We served as a side to the Bon Appetit recipe, Steak with Stout Pan Sauce.  Thanks!!

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: This is a delicious sauce recipe! It is so simple and full of flavor. I let mine simmer all day long until dinner time. My family loved it. I used 1 pound of hot Italian sausage and I made "Recipe#92095", too, and just dropped the meatballs in the sauce to cook. A great meal and I will freeze the leftover sauce to enjoy another time. I will probably be trying your lasagna next! Thanks for sharing.

name: josephinas
review: Sorry,  we found these a bit grease for our taste.  Thanks

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: Delish! Much better than store-bought and easy, too!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: These were AMAZING!!!!!!!!!!! I mixed in almost 2 cups of peanut butter chips. Moist, delicious. I could go on. My 9 yr old (whose birthday was y'day!) said these were the best brownies he ever had! TOOOO easy to make too. Very impressed. Thanks for sharing! WILL make again. The possibilities are endless!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: I could eat this often and as a matter of fact I ate the leftovers for breafkast. I sauteed a garlic clove, celery and the onion then added the rest of ingredients to the same iron skillet, including a handful of peas and carrots, half and half and stirred before I popped in oven. Added the grands biscuits after about 15 minutes and the cheddar when I pulled it out of the oven and it was everything I knew it would be .DELISH!! The mayo gave it a slight tang which I loved and I will use the reg milk next time as the half and half thickened up a bit much and It  did not have  the gravy effect that I desired, nonetheless good, just wanted it looser. Love the fact that I made everything in my 12in iron skillet and just slid it in the oven.Simple and good, will make again

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: I doubled this too.  Great aroma while it is cooking! Subbed brocolli for zuccini and added some greek seasoning and extra dill.

name: microwave poached eggs
review: These were so easy to make and very good. It took about 54 seconds in my microwave to set the white but keep the yolk runny - just the way I like them. Thanks Paula for another keeper. Made for I Recommend Tag.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: So good. Great way to have alfredo without all the fat and calories! I highly recommend!

name: gingerbread  for cookies or a  gingerbread house
review: Tough enough to make a sturdy gingerbread house, yet snappy and delicious. Made one large gingerbread house and about 12 cookies. This is going in the permanent Christmas file!

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: What a wonderful dish!  It did bring back memories and I will definately make this again.  Makes for a quick meal.  Made for Zaar Cookbook Tag.

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: wow this was delicous.I took another reviwers suggestion of adding some cumin I  used 1/4 tsp. and did 1/4 tsp. garlic powder.This was perfect for our tastes and easy for an afterwork thought for dinner.Thanks for posting.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: This is a great meatloaf recipe. Our entire family loved it! I was surprised at the amount of liquid that I poured out of the pan after it cooked. The meat seemed a little mushy from the 1/2 cup of half and half, but the meat had plenty of texture after it cooked and I am glad I did not add more meat to the mixture. I cooked it for 1 hour and 15 minutes and it sat on the stovetop for about 15 minutes before I sliced it. Had to be a bit careful slicing, but did get nice slices. The leftovers made awesome meatloaf sandwiches! Update: Doubled the recipe tonight and it was still wonderful! 1/13/11 Made a double batch again today! So yummy!

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: We had a busy night planned with running with the kids so I opted for this recipe so it would be ready for when we all got home.  I started this at 10:00 am and we were ready to eat at 8:00pm, and while it was ok the carrots and celery were still crunchy.  DS liked it more then the rest of us, I hate to be the "odd man out" but we just didn't care for this.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I used a boneless, trimmed pork shoulder, and I thought this turned out fantastic.  I also used Jack Daniel's Original bbq sauce.  I will definately make this one over and over again!

name: panda express orange chicken
review: Wonderful! Adults in the house enjoyed it but the kids had to bribed to eat it for some reason.  I thought it best to describe the "sauce" as a glaze.  It shouldn't be drenched in a syrupy sauce IMHO.  Flavorful and restaurant quality!  My dh doesn't even like orange chicken usually but really enjoyed this.  I don't have a wok or deep fryer so this was very tricky!  I only looked at reviews and ingredients so didn't even notice I didn't have proper equipment.  Doing batches of chicken in a small saucepan filled w oil was messy and very time consuming...I don't recommend that method. Lol

name: almost white castle hamburgers
review: These were so good and very easy to prepare.  I did use 2 lbs. of meat but otherwise followed the directions exactly.  I only baked for the 10 minutes and they still turned out perfect.  Thank you so much for this quick and easy way to prepare burgers, this is perfect for those "game" nights or when your running the kids to practices.

name: soft  spicy  heavenly ginger cookies
review: Made this to use up extra molasses...they come out a good consistentcy and the raisins were a good addition.  I don't taste the fresh Ginger much at all and they don't come off as "spicy".  They DO have a persistent aftertaste for some reason.  I can't stand aftertastes.  I still gave it 3stars because I figured perhaps something was wrong w the quality of ingredients  I used.

name: softest ever bread machine bread
review: I hesitated to make this as written, since the yeast is usually added last, but was encouraged by some of the reviews. The yeast didn't get terribly foamy and the bread did not rise at all -- perhaps I should have used a different kind of yeast. I may try it again following the bread machine's instructions instead of these.

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: The monsters really enjoyed this. I made it with hamburger and I think they'd have eaten the whole pan if I'd made it with shredded chicken instead. Will be making these again.

name: chicken stroganoff   crock pot
review: We loved this, it is absolutely delicious!  I used fresh chicken and cooked it on high for 4 hours.  Then, I shredded the chicken and let it sit uncovered while finishing the sides, maybe 10-15 minutes.  It thickened right up and was served over plain baked potatoes.  Next time I might add some onions and pepper, but I would eat it again with out changing a thing.  Thanks for this keeper!

name: spiced pumpkin waffles
review: Great taste, perfect balance of pumpkin and spices. As written, there is too much milk which makes for a thin and soft waffle. We enjoyed them, but next time I'd start with 1 cup milk and add more as needed to make a thicker batter. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Followed the recipe exactly. It's awesome.

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: These were very very good and DH devoured them in 2 days. I gave them 4 stars instead of 5 because we couldn't get the middle to set up properly and I think it might have been because of all of the chocolate chips (added 2nd time). The edges were great. It was a bit too sharply chocolate for me (and I LOVE chocolate), so I might try adding less chips if I make it again. Thanks Kitten!

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: Very good soup!  I used frozen gnocchi and added them frozen when recipe states.  I only had 8 oz of heavy cream, so I made my own "half and half" (6oz milk and 1 1/2 Tbsp melted butter) and added that along with the heavy cream, used the cornstarch also and the broth came out nice and smooth; not too thick and not too thin.  I also did add about 1/2 to 1 tsp of chicken boullion powder while simmering, which I think brought the flavoring together well.  Followed rest of all ingredients/directions exactly as written.  My 10 y/o enjoyed this as well.  Thanks for posting; I have eaten this soup at OG and it's right on the money.

name: cheat n  eat vietnamese chicken soup
review: Wow! What a fantastic soup! We were impressed with how quickly, inexpensively and easily it went together and then The Taste :) I didn't have peanut oil and it was kind of expensive, so I used a little sesame oil and the rest olive oil. I only needed one chicken breast and it was plenty. I used jarred minced ginger and garlic for ease and the flavor was spot-on. I'm so excited to have found this, we feel full and healthy after a long month of heavy holiday food. I will make this often, thanks Sue Lau!

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: I won't rate this until I try it again.  Perhaps my shrimp were at fault, but this wasn't very good, I used thawed frozen shrimp, maybe that's why.  I might try some of the other suggestions next time, maybe marinate the shrimp.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: My daughter loved this. I soaked the chicken in the dressing for a little while to give it a little marinade effect. Skipped the drizzled butter.

name: aloo gobi
review: Very good!  I would make this again!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Ditto all the other reviews - this is fantastic!

name: romano s macaroni grill rosemary bread
review: I thought I had reviewed this recipe before, but I guess not - sorry! This is a great bread and it smells so good. I used my bread machine on the dough cycle as suggested by others and oiled my hands to shape the dough. I made one large loaf and it baked in the time allowed. I used butter and sea salt for the top when finished baking and we really enjoyed it. Thanks so much. Carole in Orlando

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: This was enjoyed by me and my family. I used boneless, skinless chicken thighs. Threw in a couple cloves of garlic with the chicken and onion. Gave it a few good grindings of black pepper. For me, the sauce is what makes this so delicious. Very nice.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: These were very tasty.  I felt like mine turned out a little flat, I'd be happy to try them again to see if I could get a better result though!

name: pumpkin gooey butter cake   paula deen
review: Not that this recipe needs ANOTHER 5 star review but I just could'nt not sing my praises! What a great and easy fall recipe - a wonderful way to spice up a cake mix!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Proud to be the 740th reviewer for this super recipe, I can only echo all of the previous wonderful comments. Besides the flavor, the ease in making these tender morsels was the best part. I used one pound of lean ground beef and one pound of lean ground pork. I didn't have dry bread crumbs, so used crushed crackers instead. This is definitely company worthy. Thanks Kitten!

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Absolutely fabulous!  I've given this recipe out many times.  You'll be surprised at how much the cauliflower cooks down.  My husband and I can eat a whole head of cauliflower cooked this way because of the shrinkage.  I'd recommend making two full heads to feed a family.  This is INCREDIBLE tasting.  The cooking is spot on.  I sometimes add some crushed red pepper or a shake or two of garlic powder...but it's perfect just as it is.  A very requested veggie in my house.

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: I've made this soup a number of times and it is easy and delicious. I sometimes add protein, usually italian sausage,  mini meatballs or ground beef. My DH will often request I make a batch so he can take it to work for lunches all week. It's nice to have a little of control over the salt content and as previous reviewers have said "hiding the veggies". One of the fastest dinners in my quick fix repetoire.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Really good! I used corn tortillas instead of flour (personal preference) and they were good!

name: skylike chili   skyline chili copycat
review: Yummy recipe!  When I first started this I was a little concerned about the amount of cocoa ~seemed a little much and when I tasted it before it simmered I didn't like it.  But, it definitely needs to simmer for an hour and then the bitter chocolate taste goes away.  Don't be put off by the long list of ingredients ~ it is really easy to put together.  Thanks for posting this ~ will definitely make again! Made for Zaar Chef Alphabet Soup.

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: We loved this!  I used freshly grated ginger in place of the powder.  Our grill is covered with a foot and a half of snow so I baked this at 350° for 15 minutes, basting once halfway through.  It was perfect!  Thanks Mirj for the lovely recipe!

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: Delicious! I did make some changes, one of which was to make this stovetop. I used 3 boneless/skinless chicken breasts that I diced and sauted in butter with the diced carrots. Left out the onion and celery so I seasoned the chicken with onion powder. Also seasoned chicken with poultry seasoning, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Added the chicken broth, covered the pot and simmered the chicken for about 15 minutes. Then I threw in the uncooked egg noodles and the peas and simmered covered for another 15 minutes. Then I stirred in 2 cans of cream of chicken soup and left out the herbes and heated the soup until it was steaming hot. Everyone raved about how delicious this was and it was also easy so we will have this soup often!

name: chicken pesto
review: Amazing. So simple and SO good!

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Perfection in a bowl! Love, love, love, the red peppa' and the lemon - so unique and so welcomed! The seasoning was right on, with the addition of the cumin - and also used some homemade veggie broth. This is so yummy - you should be selling this to Panara - I bet they would love it too!

name: quick soft breadsticks
review: Awesome recipe! These are so easy and taste great too! I made my dough by hand, using 3 cups of all-purpose flour. I combined everything except the water (which I made sure was about 110 degrees F) and the oil, then I stirred the water in, followed by the oil. I did knead the dough a few times before I rolled it out, too. It didn't really take much more flour. I let them rise about 30 minutes, and I found that 15 minutes was a perfect amount of baking time. I got 12 breadsticks, but I didn't measure how big I rolled my rectangle out. I brushed them with butter when they came out of the oven, I dipped mine in marinara sauce, and my husband had honey on his. This is a keeper! Thank you!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: This was great. I used a touch less honey and some cayenne for some spice. Thanks!

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Made to go with our chicken wings. I think next time we will exchange at least 1/3 of the cup of water for more soy sauce. Not that it was watery, but would've liked a stronger flavor. Also, the ginger was a bit overpowering for our tastes, so we'll decrease that as well.

name: tsr version of carrabba s bread dipping spice by todd wilbur
review: This goes great with the recipe for Macaroni Grill's Rosemary Bread! I added a little sea salt to mine, but kept everything else the same.

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: Winning recipe Lennie!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: I'm not going to rate this dish because DH and I thought it was bad and very bitter, so I'm wondering if the broccoli was bad. Not sure if it was that or the lemon.

name: oreo balls
review: Not that these need another review, but they were great! I wanted something easy to make as  gifts for my childrens teachers, and I made about 100 plus of these. You NEED a food processor. With my food processor I whipped them up very quickly and with no problem at all. ( the "dough" looks disgusting but is so delicious).

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: I loved this. I followed the recipe other then I didn't add the celery as I didn't have any. I also used black beans and northern beans as that is all I had on hand. I added the optional tabasco sauce. I topped mine with parm cheese. This was so good. Great flavor.

name: romano s macaroni grill rosemary bread
review: Very close to the real thing! I brushed mine with butter and sprinkled garlic salt and Italian spices on top and served it with Macaroni Grill Chicken Marsala over angel hair pasta. I will definitely be making this again!

name: almost white castle hamburgers
review: I have tried the frozen white castles, but only had "real" Krystals.  These were sort of close, but not quite there....I missed the rehydrated minced dried onions they sprinkle across the meat.  Also, I don't remember ketchup at all....just mustard.....but those may be Krystals and not White Castle.  I enjoyed these very much, but I was thinking of the mustardy onion taste that I know and love.  I will make this again, but delete the ketchup.  Thanks so much for sharing this....I'd never thought of doing this at home...only do burgers on the grill!  Fun to relive old memories.  Thanks so much!

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: This was enjoyed by most of the family. I thought it was a nice easy meal to throw together. I just thought it was lacking some flavor.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: I did not add all the cayenne and red pepper flakes to the water when boiling and should have cut down on the salt also.  However, this is a fabulous method and produced wings that tasted char broiled.  So so good!  I mixed 4 tablespoons melted butter with 1 teaspoon of cider vinegar and 1/3 cup of hot sauce and brushed it on before broiling.(Perfect amount of sauce for 14 individual sections of wings.)  Less than 10 minutes per side and they were perfect!  My quest for a great wing recipe is over.  Thanks so much for sharing.

name: soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: Made a batch last week...they are gone.  I love soft chocolate chip cookies and these are definately some of the best.  I used 1/2 and 1/2 white and semi sweet chocolate chips.  I used my small cookie scoop to get smaller cookies in hopes they lasted longer but they just ate more of them at once.  Thanks for a great cookie and a keeper!!

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review: What a fabulous treat, easy & delicious.

name: magnolia bakery s vanilla birthday cake and frosting
review: Meh. My husband gives this a 2 stars. This is really a shame because I had very high hopes. I made a birthday cake from it. It was very VERY plain. No frills and not really that great. I really didn't like the icing, though it seems like it should have been great. Maybe it was my powdered sugar? I dunno. Just really nothing special. I will not be making this again.

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: I give this recipe, as written, 3 stars because we thought it was a little bland and didnt quite have that chowder consistency that we like.  I did add chopped celery and carrots in the beginning.  After letting it sit in the crock for about 5 hours on high and adding in the cream cheese, I tasted it and started adding to what I thought would make it better.  I added about 8-9 oz. of velveeta cheese, garlic powder, paprika, dash of hot sauce, italian seasoning, and corn.  It was a little thin so after the cheese melted and leaving the top off it thickened a little better but it still wasnt as thick as I prefer my chowders.  But it was very good after those additions.  Like some others have said, this would be very good with some smoked sausage in it as well.  Thanks for the recipe!

name: weight watchers general tso s chicken
review: I don't think this tastes like General Tso's chicken, that said it was good.  I added some red bell peppers, chunks of onion and sliced water chestnuts to give it more texture.

name: traditional english cheddar cauliflower cheese   gratin
review: Very nice accompaniment to our pork chops for tonight's dinner.  :-)

name: boeuf bourguignon a la julia child
review: Love this recipe.  I have Mastering the Art of French Cooking and this is one of our many favorites from it.  Also good over rice.  The best part is that it tastes just as good if not better reheated as leftovers.  I like to make a full batch on a Sunday afternoon and divide the leftovers into individual serving containers for lunches for the upcoming week.  Yum!

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: Want this  chowder to be really over the top? Make recipe as stated but add these spices: 1 1/2 tsp. white pepper, 1 tsp. dried basil, and 1/2 tsp. thyme. We garnished ours with: bacon, sour cream, shredded cheddar cheese, and lots of sliced green onions (the green part) YUM!!

name: lemon baked cod
review: I thought this was pretty good. Instead of dredging the fish, I put it in the pan, brushed it with the lemon mixture and sprinkled breadcrumbs over the top. The top got crispy and solved the soggy bottom dilemma. I'll be making this again.

name: buttermilk pancakes
review: These are excellent. Easy to follow directions. The kids loved them! (Six-year-old said, "these are better than dad's!")

name: auntie s delicious soft pretzels  amish recipe
review: My bread recipes are always disasters; I'm not much of a baker without my bread machine! I may have to try finding a BM pretzel recipe. Even this simple one simply would not rise for me. The dough was very flaky so I mixed it a little longer than I think I probably should have to get it all to combine. The vanilla and cinnamon-sugar variation sounds great, too! Oh, well.

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: Oh my goodness, these are good.  We have not had the ones at Taco Bell but we really loved these.  I made enough for one a piece and it was more then plenty, they are very filling.  Thank you for sharing this easy meal.

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: I made this using a chuck roast and it turned out wonderful.  I cooked mine for about 9 hours and it was perfect.  The kids scraped off their salt and pepper crust on the outside but they ate it up.  Thank you for sharing this smokey delicious roast recipe.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: Had 1/2 rotisserie chicken left-over, and MOST of recipe ingredients.  Sauteed fresh mushrooms with onion, used sour cream-no mayo, about 1/2 can chicken and broccoli soup -- did add peas.  Now I have MORE leftovers !  Since no seasoning was listed, added a shaker of Greek seasoning and some seasoned salt.  Made up quickly and made a satisfying dinner for DH and me.  Thanks for posting, Potsie.

name: beth s pizza crust
review: Excellent!!!

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: I made a vegetarian version by subbing the beef for black beans. So good! This will be my go-to recipe for fajita/taco nights from now on.

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: Only used 1 lb beef, but that was plenty. Put it in a crockpot and took it skiing with us. Finished every bite!

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: WOW - we don't ever eat cauliflower but this was fabulous!  Must make this!

name: cake batter ice cream
review: Quick, easy, delicious. This was very sweet as written, but I have a crazy sweet tooth! The second time I made it I used lower fat ingredients - 1 cup of half and half, two cups of So Delicious brand coconut milk (much lower fat than canned). I also added two teaspoons of vodka, which worked well. With a lower fat content, the alcohol helps keep it from freezing into a solid brick once you place it in the freezer.

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: OMG! This is so good! Panera's soup is what got me started eating broccoli and this is almost identical except better texture.  You know you are biting into something with this soup.  Thanks so much! I will never go to Panera again!

name: yummy baked potato skins
review: 10 stars - what more is there to say........

name: chinese pot stickers
review: These were amazing! Very forgiving, too as I subbed out a couple ingredients I didn't have for something close. A new favorite for sure - thanks for sharing!

name: super peanut butter filled brownies
review: Delicious!!!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: Who knew something this easy could be so good?? We added andouille sausage which I think really gave it some great flavor.  Put only 1 tsp Tony Sach's in because we have toddlers, but then added about 1 tsp to our own after the kids were served.  We've made it with half & half as well as with heavy cream and both work great.  Thought the sauce was a little thin, so I added some corn starch---WOULD NOT recommend that.  It was too thick after putting in the parmesan which thickened it as well, so I ended up adding more cream.  GREAT recipe.  Thanks!

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: Absolutely delicious...I did make a few alterations because of what I had on hand. I did not have beef gravy, so I used a pkg of roasted chicken gravy mix and added a little dry beef stock to the rest of the pkg items. I also added a can of cream of mushroom soup to 1 can of water for the liquid. Any gravy leftover from this is going in the freezer.....This is a definate keeper recipe. Thank you soooooo much!!!

name: microwave poached eggs
review: What a fabulous recipe!  I made corn beef hash yesterday and DH loves poached (runny yolk eggs) on his.  This was fast and really no sticky clean-up.  It takes about 55-57 seconds in our micro but ohhhh soooo easy.  Thank you for submitting this recipe.

name: southern fried chicken
review: This is excellent fried chicken.  I followed the recipe but adjusted the preparation method.  I first tossed the chicken into flour, then marinaded it in the sauce mixture for a few hours, mixed the seasoning and dredging mixture together and then tossed the chicken through it.  I was concerned about the sauce mixture washing away the seasoning.  Turned out great.  Thanks.

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: Great recipe!  I used Asiago cheese (because it's what I had) and added a can of french style green beans before  topping it with stuffing.  Next time I'm going to try it using Fat Free Soups.   Thanks for a great recipe!

name: kittencal s extreme chocolate brownies
review: Kittencal does not disappoint, EVER!  These were delicious--used both white choc chips and a mixture of semi-sweet and chocolate chips.  Baked as directed for appox 40 minutes.  Only issue was they caved in when I took them out, but I could overlook that for the taste.   Can only imagine the yumminess if this were topped with vanilla bean ice cream.....

name: pan release  professional pan coating  better than pam spray
review: Another great review here...it's really pretty amazing how it whips up, just like you said it would!  I like having this around as I never buy anything spray. Thanks Kittcencal!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: I have made one whole chicken, using your recipe/cooking method, and loved it!  The other whole chicken I made, using your recipe/cooking method, I cooked sitting on a beer with limes in the beer.  This one I also loved.  Thank you for teaching me this!

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: I have never had black bean soup at Panera, so I don't know if this compares or not. I also liked the mix of lemon and red pepper.  I also found that the soup did not puree well.  I think the veggies needed to be cooked longer.  I like my black bean soup a little spicier which is why I did not give it a five star rating.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: these were really nice.  I used the amount of garlic that was recommended and it was the right amount for us.  I had to bake for an addition 20 minutes to get that nice browning on them.  Thanks

name: creamy garlic chicken
review: Didn't care for this at all...

name: ww 5 can soup
review: So good for you, easy and quite delicious.  I also used Progresso Minestrone, diced tomato with jalapenos, and 10 ounces of frozen corn and mixed veggies.  Since the soup was too thick I added about 1 1/4 cup of vegetable broth.  Served with cheddar cheese on the side and rolls for dipping.  Will make it again.  Picked for a day in which I only had a few minutes to put supper together.

name: chipotle roast for tacos   sandwiches
review: This was great! I used a pork butt instead of beef and vegetable broth instead of beef, but otherwise made as written. Served on corn tortillas for taco filling.  UPDATED 1/25/11: Made directly as written(with beef and beef broth) and loved it even more. Cooked on high for 5 hours and came out tender and flavorful. Served on french bread rolls.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: great chili! i found out i was having company for the game about 2 hours before they showed up so I couldn't make a crockpot chili. I improvised a bit off the recipe but I used the spice combination and it was the perfect flavor. Thank you!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Great recipe!  I love Buffalo wings but always feel guilty eating them, due to the fat content.  I felt much less guilty with these, though I was a bit unsure about boiling (boiling???) them.  I went ahead with it, followed the directions exactly and was thrilled with the results.  I served them with a killer blue cheese dressing and crisp celery sticks.  Wonderful!  Thanks WhoDat for this clever recipe.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: Just made this but used Casar dressing and cornflake crumbs.  Came out crispy and kids liked it a lot.  Next time I hope to use Ranch...thought I had it but I was out so I improvised. Thanks Kitten!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: VERY VERY GOOD!  Made exactly as recipe directed but used 1T dried chopped onions.  The only reason I'm not giving this 5 stars is that it just felt overly-oily to me. I'm definitely going to make this again, but will cut the olive oil in half.  Thanks for sharing!

name: crazy crust pizza
review: This was pleasantly surprising.  I tried it because I was intrigued by the concept, and I wasn't disappointed.  It is definitely not my favorite crust, but for the time it takes to make it's a great option.  I will likely keep this recipe and use it when we decide we want pizza but I don't have time to put a crust together.  The middle was a bit underdone for my taste (not crispy) even though I baked it for 5 more minutes than the recipe called for, but not so doughy that we wouldn't eat it.  Thanks for this recipe!

name: good eats roast turkey
review: Used this recipe basically but changed a few items ... all in all best turkey we ever had.

name: tilapia
review: Made this for Zaar Cookbook Tag and I'm glad I did!  I followed the directions except for adding some parmesan cheese to the bread crumb mixture and adding some garlic powder to the herb mixture (we love garlic) and using all the lemon/butter mixture to the pan when cooking the fish like a previous reviewer did.   Served with Saffron Couscous with Herbs #428285 and broccoli. Definately a keeper!

name: whole wheat honey banana muffins
review: Followed the recipe exactly and they turned out great! I was nervous that using all honey might effect the texture and rising capability of the muffin, but it wasn't a problem at all. Very moist too which is key to any good whole-wheat baked good (might add a couple extra bananas next time to bump up the moisture factor). A keeper, thank you! FYI- Another of my favorite "doesn't taste like whole-wheat" recipes is Manuela's Fruity Whole Wheat Oat Bread (Recipe #44674). Also excellent.

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: Made this last night and it was a big hit with everyone.  I cut the recipe in half and the salt a little but followed the rest of the instructions.  I am putting this into my Favorites of 2011 book.  Served this with Tri-tip steak, green beans, paprika/butter fried potatoes and the Realtor's Italian Salad Dressing#384154/salad.  P.S.  I will add a little more brown sugar for my own sweet tooth.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: Perfect...thank you

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: This has become one of my favorite meals. I've made it probably 5 times now and never changed one thing from the original recipe. (Well I might be a little more generous with the cheese, but that's all.) No changes or additions are required. It's very easy to put together and taste fabulous. Highly recommended.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: This was such a great way to make cauliflower. I used 3 whole heads of garlic and it was wonderful even left over the next day. Thanks for posting.

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Very easy and good way to make a whole chicken. The meat turned out tender and juicy and my whole family enjoyed it. Thanks for posting.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: great recipe

name: uncle bill s whipped shortbread cookies
review: Great tasting little cookies.  Very light and airy.  Can't beat a good shortbread cookie.  Thanks for posting this wonderful recipe.

name: classic baked ziti
review: I scaled it down to 2 servings and baked in an 8x8 dish and still had enough for 4 people. I swapped out the meat for olives (being a vegetarian) and used pizza cheese and sauce. It was okay, definitely a recipe I can build a good vegetarian version from. Thanks for sharing.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: I've never been a fan of non-boxed-mix cakes before, because they generally didn't turn out very good.  But this..this is my new go-to for chocolate cake!  I baked in 9" round, then split each layer (to end up with four layers).  The bottom three layers each were pricked with a fork and brushed with a little chocolate syrup and then filled with Whipped Chocolate Cream Icing, which was used to ice the top and sides as well.  Topped with a few chocolate curls and a drizzle of chocolate syrup, I thought we'd died and gone to heaven.  This got rave reviews too...thanks so much for posting.  I'm off to make another one right now!

name: hot dog hamburger buns rolls cinnamon buns dough cycle a b m
review: These turned out great!  My mom is on a low sodium diet so I decreased the salt to 1/4 t with no ill effects.  I then divided the dough in half, made hamburger buns (8) with half and (12) cinnamon rolls with the rest.  The cinnamon rolls were good even though I didn't use the larger amount of sugar.

name: hard boiled eggs
review: I have always boiled eggs leaving the flame on till they are finished but when I saw this technique I just had to try it. It worked perfectly! Beautiful hard boiled egg without using all that gas. I will use this method often. Thanks for sharing.

name: mean guy s general tso s chicken
review: Another 5 stars.  This was mouth watering excellent.  We certainly didn't need it, but we did wish for more sauce.  Also, I found this much easier to make than I had expected.  This will definitely be made again.  And again, and again, and again.

name: french dip roast beef for the crock pot
review: Excellent flavor and so easy! The broth was so good I could eat it alone. I added some chopped onions on top of the meat, but otherwise made as written. Served on rolls with melted muenster cheese. I will definitely make this again since everyone loved it and it was so simple. Thanks for posting.

name: cauliflower cheddar soup
review: Soothing, warming comfort food at its best!  I used fat free milk and you would have thought I'd used cream!  Used an extra sharp cheddar.  I feel so healthy AND happy!  Thanks for sharing!

name: whole wheat honey banana muffins
review: Very good!  I halved the recipe and got 8 regular and 12 mini sized muffins.  Added about 1/2 tsp cinnamon and vegetable oil instead of canola.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: I made this last night and enjoyed every bite to the max!  I opted to use half mayonnaise and half low-fat sour cream with excellent results.  I loved the idea of putting the cheese on top of the casserole before adding the biscuits as another reviewer did.  Came out just great Potsie!  Thank you for sharing this recipe with us.  I will be making this many more times.  It's a great belly warmer during this cold weather, but anytime is good with me :)  Linda

name: frizzled cabbage
review: MMMMMMM!  This is such a wonderful way to prepare cabbage!  I used just salt and pepper to season and it was perfect!  Thanks for sharing!

name: shrimp  cocktail sauce
review: I was using up some prawns from the freezer and I knew that I would find a recipe here.  I wasn't disappointed!
