What was I waiting for? 5 stars from my boys! Used brown sugar instead of pickle juice and did add some fresh garlic. Used cream of mushroom soup, but left out the veg itself. Super tasty and will definitely make many times over! Thanks Jellyqueen for a keeper!

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: Easy and delcious!  Took 50 minutes in my bundt pan.  Next time I may add lemon zest to the batter.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: I topped it with an assortment of italin spices, olive oil, and feta.  It was pretty good.  The dough was great though.  I like a crunchy crust sometimes and that is exactly what this was.

name: world s best cinnamon raisin bread  not bread machine
review: This is really good! I scaled it back to make one loaf and DH and DS have just about devoured the whole thing! I used 1/2 bread flour and 1/2 white wheat flour, and that seems to have worked fine. I am not fond of raisins so I skipped them, and I decided to make a longer squat loaf on a cookie sheet so I only baked about 35 minutes. I thought there might be too much cinnamon/sugar for the filling so I used about 2/3 of it and I wish I had used it all; don't be fooled by how it looks before rolling. DS had a great idea; he asked me to make it into french toast for his lunch yesterday LOL. It really worked! Thanks for posting! Made for Best of 2010 tag.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review:
This is soo good. This is the second time I have made. Be sure and reduce sauce. I saw on tv that if you reduce a sauce it will have more flavor but if you only do it a little bit it will be bland. The second time I made I took that knowledge and used it I am so glad I did this is much better if you reduce sauce.

Oh I used 1/2 and 1/2 instead of heavy whipping cream. yummy

forgot to add the show I saw reduced sauces by half

name: yummy crispy baked fish
review: A good simple breading recipe for fish.  Made this tonight with flounder, and I like the crunchiness of the corn meal.  The ingredients are basic pantry items so no need to make a special trip to the food store.  The cayenne pepper is a must have ingredient for me, and it lends a nice zing to the recipe.  Not a show-stopper recipe, but hey, how much of a wow factor can breading have?  It's a solid recipe that goes together fast using basic pantry ingredients, and dinner can be on the table in a snap.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Really great potpie! I cut back a little on the celery & onion and added chopped mushrooms & peas.  I also added a little parsley, basil & a decent amount of garlic salt.  When I was ready to pour it into the dishes, I felt mine had turned out a little too thick and so added some more half and half as well as chicken broth to make sure it wouldn't dry out too much during baking.  I used rotisserie chicken and also used store brought pie crusts and only needed to bake it for 30 minutes.  Very versatile & easy!!  Thanks!!

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: While living in Texas I fell in love with Tex-Mex food.  Now in Rhode Island my only choice is to try to duplicate it at home.  This hit the spot, I made exactly as listed and can't wait to try it again with green enchilada sauce instead of the salsa.  So easy and so good!  Thanks!!!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Very tasty, we loved the strong garlic flavor. I think my taters must have been small because there was way too much oil for the amount of potatoes. My error, not yours. I made this dish, as it was recommended as one of the 2010 best recipes submittted by Sharon123.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Oh My, this was the best fish ever!  I could eat the entire pan!  Every one loved it and that is saying a lot since my family is not big fish eaters.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Here's one more 5-star review for these terrific brownies!  I made them for an after-dance party for my daughter and her friends and every last one was eaten.  We just added milk chocolate chips.  They are very rich and fudgy and a great easy way to make brownies without a box mix.  Thanks for posting!

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: I think some people have nothing better to complain about than other peoples recipes. This turned out wonderful for me. I added some seasoned salt and made sure to put seasonings between the skin and chicken (as well as on top) before I baked it. I didn't use Kikoman soy sauce and I had no problems. I baked it at 375 for 1 hour on the middle oven rack and the skin got crispy and delicious. I will be making this again and again. Thanks for posting.

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: so easy! I used 1 cup of milk 1/2 cup water.  It's like hot chocolate made with water and hot chocolate made with milk -- you can't compare!

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: I really enjoyed these. They kind of taste like eating oatmeal in pancake form. I cut the recipe into thirds to make one decent sized pancake for myself and topped it with bananas and peanut butter. These pancakes have a great texture, thanks!

name: blue ridge mountains chocolate chip cookies
review: Great cookie recipe! Just tried it tonight and had to give out the recipe. Thanks!

name: 5 minute vegan pancakes
review: These are officially adopted as my pancake recipe. These are the best I've ever had, hands down. They're SO light and airy! And pretty and quick. Perfect! Thanks for sharing this!

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: YUM-O! Excellent and easy. I served it with "lemony quinoa" and green veggies. it's totally going into the monthly rotation.

name: vegetarian  meatballs
review: These are fantastic! Even DH liked them. I added these vegetarian meatballs to a mushroom sauce this time. I'll probably try the vegetarian broth next time. Thanks for sharing!

name: fresh orange muffins
review: Not only are these light and fluffy and full of fresh orange flavor but it is so cool that you use the entire orange in these, peel and all!  It really doesn't get much easier than this!  I topped some of mine with a bit or orange decorating sugar before baking and added chopped pecans.  Everyone loved them!

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: My kids loved this and it's so easy. Thanks!

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: We thought this was a very good Chicken and Dressing.  Only thing I would suggest is one might use the lower sodium soups.  It tends to be a little salty tasting.  Will make again soon.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: kale chips
review: My husband and I absolutely loved this recipe.  I only had one bunch of Kale, so I cut back to 1 tsp of salt but used full amounts of the other ingredients.  Just because of his personal preference I will cut back a little more on the salt (I personally thought it was great).  Loved the flavors and texture.  I did over bake mine a bit even on 350, that was my own fault (and my oven bakes a little hotter) and it still had great taste, I just need to be more careful next time because over baking does make the Kale a little bitter.  We will definitely be making this again with 2 bunches and have plans to add this to our garden this year if possible!  Thank you for a great, healthy recipe!  Can't wait to have this again.

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: WOW - who knew it was so easy to make chocolate pudding!  We've made it twice now and the last time put mind extract in it for a different flavor combo - both ways are lovely.  Thanks.

name: alton brown s baked brown rice
review: LOVE LOVE LOVE this recipe - reheats well too.  Made it with chicken stock and will reduce the salt next time as it was a tad salty but great flavor and texture.  Thanks

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: This is a fabulous recipe!  Simple to throw together for the newest of chefs. Most ingredients readily on hand.  The 1/2 cup of sugar and dash of raisins lends a kiss of sweetness and the best of compliments to your corned beef supper.  I served with corned beef, carrots and steamed cabbage. Thanks so much for sharing this, 1Steve!

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review: Made this tonight and it was great.  I did make one change, I used pork chops instead of chicken!  They came out very flavorful.  I do think next time I will use "hot" salsa instead of mild.  I was afraid of too much "heat" for my taste.  Next time I'll marinate the pork or chicken for several hours in the mixture.  We loved the flavor and it was very quick and easy. Thanks.

name: crock pot chicken vindaloo
review: I made this for my family only used the stovetop instead of the crock pot.  It was really good.  I used chicken legs instead of breasts and it worked great.  Then sauce clung to the chicked great and it tasted really good with the buttered noodles I served this with. Thank you for broadening our palates with this dish.

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: I made this for my DD and her BF and they both really enjoyed it.  Next time I will add a little more lemon.  thanks

name: fish tacos and cilantro coleslaw  20 minutes max
review: These were excellent, thanks for sharing this great recipe.  I made a written except I didn't have corn tortillas so I used flour and they were still great.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: This was a huge hit at my house.  My son said "This is good enough to put on Recipezaar", and my husband is talking about how he's going to parade around the office with his leftovers on Monday.  I cut the oil to about 2-3 tablespoons, and baked uncovered for about 35 minutes at 350, then turned the slices, added (a lot) of shredded parmesan, and turned the oven up to about 425 for another 10-15 minutes.  Will definitely make this again.  Thanks for sharing.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: Perfection! Exactly what I was craving, great batter that stuck to the cod.  I went easy on the salt in the batter thinking I would salt when done frying, but it does need it in the batter as stated in the recipe.  I'll have trouble keeping hubby from begging for this again tonight, LOL, thanks for a keeper.

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: I am giving this 5 stars I loved it!  The flavor was to die for even though my better half did not care for it...the ras el hanout spice makes it pop and of course the saffron...I bought the spice on amazon and it was fabulous and not that expensive...

name: sweet bacon wrapped venison tenderloin
review: We enjoyed this one.  My husband isn't a big venison eater, so I wanted something that toned down the 'game' flavor of the meat.  I had tiny tenderloins, so I cut the marinade in half, and I did cut the amount of sugar down as well.  I didn't put the extra sugar on the meat, but I did baste frequently as this cooked.  To crisp it up, I turned on the broiler for about 6 minutes at the end, turning the meat halfway through.  Will make this again the next time I can talk Dad out of some venison!  Thanks for sharing.

name: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
review: These are really good.  I love peanut butter cookies and add in the chocolate chunks......delicious.  I was a little concerned with how undone these looked when coming out of the oven but they we good once cooled down.  When we tried eating them right out of the oven they fell apart.  No worries, these are too good when cooled to not make again.  Thank you P4

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Looks like this might be the 100th review!.. not that it needs yet another glowing review, but lets add one anyway because these wings are amazing! Fun to make and fun to eat; I broiled them in the toaster oven so I didn't even need to use the large oven. For the sauce, I mixed together hot sauce, chili garlic sauce to make it even more spicy, and a smokey bbq sauce just for a bit of depth. I tossed the wings in the sauce and broiled them for another 10-15 minutes, and they were perfect. The wings were so good, crisp on the outside and super tender inside. Definitely will be making my wings like this again! Thanks!

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: I've made this several times!  Thanks for a great recipe

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: I cannot get enough of this cauliflower.  The flavor is very reminiscent of the battered, fried variety my mother used to make back in the day when frying wasn't a no-no.  I actually go out of my way to make sure I overcook it a bit, I prefer the flavor when the cauliflower begins to be a very dark brown color and is a bit crispy.  This is delicious as is, but once in a great while, I will sprinkle bread crumbs lightly over the cauliflower prior to roasting.  Thank you so much for giving me this very healthy option to an old favorite!

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: The only thing I did differently was to add some fresh mushrooms.  I think with that being said, I would use canned mushrooms instead or sauté them first, because it added a bit of water to the sauce.  Oh, I also used artichoke bottoms instead of heart (what I had on hand).  Per some reviews, I think I will try ½ mayo and ½ sour cream next time just to see how it turns out because I think it broke a bit.  Very yummy!

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: The recipe I've been using for years, tx for posting.

name: chewy granola bars
review: Love these bars. They are so delicious and so easy to make -- and truly nicer than anything you will ever buy commercially. We forgot to reduce the brown sugar to 3/4 cup, and will probably do so in future. Our only changes were to use crushed mini-wheat cereal (instead of a rice cereal) and an almond/sunflower seed combo for the nuts. This will go straight into my Top 100 cookbook. Thanks so much for posting.

name: delicious homemade egg noodles
review: Used this to make homemade creamy chicken and noodles.  I also used my KitchenAid mixer with the dough hook to knead the dough and a pizza cutter to cut them up. Didn't even break a sweat it was so easy! I also did not wait for them to dry and just tossed them in my soup.  They were very tender and perfect.  Thank you so much for posting this!!

name: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
review: Easy and good.  Just what you are thinking of when you think oatmeal cookie.  I followed some other reviewers suggestions and used .25 cup less sugar and half an egg less.  Would be good with any dried fruit or chocolate chips.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: This is a keeper, for sure.  I'm not one to usually say this, but it could use just a little kick...maybe 1/4 tsp red pepper flakes?  Very very good though as is!!

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: This was good but didn't knock my socks off. I'll probably use this as my go-to recipe from now on though since it's so simple and inexpensive to prepare (have everything on hand already). Even though a can of enchilada sauce is about $1.50 this is still cheaper! And it yields a lot. I only used half for about 12 enchiladas.

name: potato salad with chipotle peppers a man s salad
review: ooooo! thanks for a new twist on tater salad! goes great with steaks and cant wait to try it with smoked meats too! eeeee!! omitted bell peppers, swapped 2T shallots for scallions, used 2 stalks celery, 1T dried cilantro, added a bit more mayo, 4 chipotle peppers with some of the sauce and onions in the can, omitted bacon, 1t celery salt, 1T regular mustard, and used russets instead of reds and kept every thing else the same. LOVED IT! thanks Rita! the boyfriend didn't even hafta add anything (with everything else he ALWAYS adds SOMETHING!) so i take that as a huge compliment! oh my mouth is watering!

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: These were a nice healthy change from usual enchiladas. I did sub corn tortillas for flour. Thanks for posting!

name: black bottom banana bars
review: yummy, yummy! made this at my boyfriends' grandmothers house and she couldn't stop nibbling on this! but neither could we! really delicious!! used a 9x9 pan and shoulda used a 9x13. they turned out good, just took forever to bake!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: This is definitely a keeper of a recipe!  Made this with our Sunday dinner and it was a huge hit!  I am going to have to share this recipe with my DD as she loves brussel sprouts and I know she will love this take on them too.  Found this recipe through the I Recommend tag game.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: thanks mizz nezz for a wonderful, easy recipe! these turned out super moist and yummy! used oats in place of nuts for the topping and made a little too much. put the leftover topping (moistened with a little extra butter) in empty muffin spaces instead of throwing away. the boyfriend thought just the topping alone tasted like an oatmeal cookie! bonus! will keep this recipe near by for those nice brown bananas!!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: Surprising good.  I was in a bind and needed buns NOW!  This worked fine, is good the second day too.  Had to add more flour.  Made it in my Kitchenaid mixer.  Marie, thanks for posting . . . Janet

name: brown sugar meatloaf
review: This did not disappoint us. It was a great meat loaf!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: So, so fabulous!  I tagged this in I recommend and I'm so glad I found this recipe!  A definite keeper.  I did add garlic to the water mix, and used a bit more water.  Loved this!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Fudge-y good deliciousness! We added some chocolate chips as an afterthought after the batter was poured. Topped with a Bailey's icing for St. Patrick's Day. Wonderful, but you know that already :) Thanks for the keeper!

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: I've made many soda breads and this is the best by far! The highlight of my St. Patrick's Day dinner!

name: french toast sticks   oamc
review: Mmmmm....these are so good.  We had "breakfast for dinner" last night and these were a BIG hit.  I loved the cinnamon in these.  I had little cups for our syrup so the kids could dip.  thank you for sharing these little gems with us.

name: mexican casserole   6 5 weight watcher points
review: I didn't use low fat ingredients, so it had more calories, but it was very good.

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: This is by far my favorite way to eat cauliflower, not a favorite veggie of mine, unless its prepared this way! One full head of cauliflower will serve DH, myself and 3 year old.  I follow the ingredients, but have found after making it a few times, I like the results better when I let it cook at the high 450 degree temp for about 20 min, then turning down the oven to about 350 for another 30 or so.  Really lets the garlic soften and get sweet.  Plus, easy to throw in some chicken breasts after turning down the temp and have your dinner ready at once.  I will generally serve with garlic butter chicken breasts and couscous.  Thanks for posting, this is a regular at our house!

name: easy pizza pasta casserole  oamc
review: Awesome stuff! I cut it in half and made it healthier by using turkey sausage instead of ground beef, lowfat cheese and smart taste rotini! Dh loved it as did I! Thanks for sharing.

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: Totally awesome bread.  This recipe is so easy to make, the instructions are easy to follow -- but he easiest part of chowing down on this amazing bread.  I used currants instead of rasins and I soaked the currants in some Irish whiskey for a couple hours to let them soften and absord some of that yummy flavoring.  Thank you for adding such a great finishing touch to our St. Patrick's Day dinner -- it was enjoyed by all.

name: corned beef and cabbage in guinness
review: We enjoyed a super Corned Beef and Cabbage St. Patricks Day dinner last night thanks, in part to this wonderful recipe.  I soaked the brisket for about 3 hours prior to cooking and I went ahead with the reduction of the broth.  We did not find it salty at all.  We might have had 10 servings of the veggies -- but the 4 of us ate all the corned beef!!!!!  Thank you for a wonderful recipe.

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: I'm really excited about this recipe. Made it tonight as written and it was very good. I'm not a vegitarian, but like to eat healthfully. I'm looking forward to adding grated carrots, celery and experimenting with seasonings. Thanks so much for posting!

name: n  y  c  corned beef and cabbage
review: This was perfect!! Everyone loved it. Thank you for every detail, I learned things I didn't know! Would give this more stars if I could. This is the only recipe I will use from now on.

name: hot dog hamburger buns rolls cinnamon buns dough cycle a b m
review: I used 2 percent milk & it wasn't missing anything.  It smelled so delicious and made excellent sandwich bread, I just baked as directed for the hamburgers.  I just wish it would keep its freshness longer because I want to make the full recipe but I don't want to be eating that many sandwiches each week.  I guess I'll look into freezing them.  I'm certainly going to be using this recipe frequently.

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: This was my first time eating bruschetta so I can't give a very experienced critique.  I liked it, but didn't like how soggy the bread got, despite my having toasted it.  Tomatoes kept falling off the top too so I'm thinking I'll toast a layer of cheese onto the bread next time to separate the moist tomatoes from it & I'll probably mix some shredded cheese into the tomato mix before I put them on the bread and toast them. Hopefully that cheese being melted in will hold things together better.  I didn't have balsamic vinegar so I used wine vinegar and didn't regret the substitution.

name: finger licking chicken marinade
review: That's a great name for this.  I had no trouble with the mixing as Geca complained of.  Maybe the disappointed people's mistake has been marinating only 30 minutes because I marinated for a couple nights and my chicken was full of flavor. Maybe less time would've been equally as good, but I made the marinade ahead of time because I had my week's meals planned out. It was so good it made the pain of trying to stove cook chicken on the bone worth all the work.

name: soft italian breadsticks  abm
review: two thumbs way up!  Whole family loved these- perfect, soft, delicious!

name: bev s sauteed yellow squash
review: I wanted more.  It was great.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: This was a fabulous beef stew!! I used a little less hoisin sauce than called for, and followed another reviewer's suggestion of placing the stew into the oven after adding the wine and herbs. I put it in at 250 for a little over 3 hours, then finished the rest of the recipe on the stove. I added celery and potatoes along with the carrots, cooked it for another 25-30 minutes, and it was perfect. I will definitely make this again. Thanks!

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: It was good, but tasted like it would've been better with something else.  It either needed more flavor or a different type of meat.  Maybe spicy Italian sausage would've been better.

name: n  y  c  corned beef and cabbage
review: This was a smash hit.  We're making breakfast with the leftovers right now.  Can't wait to try that too.  Loved the abundance of parsley on the potatoes and the meat turned out perfectly.  So easy to make.  Thanks!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: perfect.

name: softest ever bread machine bread
review: I must've missed something.  I baked as directed but just got this plain boring bread.  I can make some pretty good toast out of it, but I wouldn't eat it plain.  It's a big disappointment after spending all day smelling the bread and anticipating what these people have been raving about.  With simple ingredients I might try it again, but I've had so much success with bread recipes that have turned out good, that it would need to take just the right conditions for me to want to put in the time if the result is likely to be what I got this time.

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Loved it! Followed the recipe very closely but made a couple changes...instead of green pepper, I used frozen peas. I put the frozen peas in the colander and then drained the noodles over them. I used two 5 oz cans of white tuna (they've downsized; cans aren't 6.4 oz anymore!).  I used 1% milk. I will *definitely* be making this recipe again.

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: I have had this recipe in my "want to try" file for a long time.  I finally made it when I needed a quick sauce to put over some frozen burritos for a meal for my kids.  My teenage son commented that it was really good, which is a complement because he usually eats things so fast he hardly notices how they taste.  I'm sure I will make this often since it is so tasty, easy and uses common ingredients. Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: I know it doesn't need another review, but we did it tonight and it was the moistest chicken I ever made.  Fantastic!  Personally I'll use about half the butter/oil mixture and half the spices.  They were almost caked on the skin.  Made great gravy though.  Thanks for a great dinner!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: Very easy and very good!!  I do my prime rib for Christmas every year using this method  Stress free cooking!!

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review:
Not that this recipe needs another review....I just want to put my 2 cents in. This bread is terrific!! I really wanted to purchase a loaf of Irish Soda Bread at a local bakery (and they make great soda bread)... but I figured I would give this recipe a shot since it had so many terrific reviews. I am so glad I did. This bread is so easy to make especially with my Kitchen Aid mixer and it so moist. I did adjust it slightly. I soaked the raisins in Irish whiskey (hey --St. Patrick's Day is almost here!!) and only put in 1 Tbs of caraway seeds and used light sour cream. I'll be baking this bread for St. Patty's Day instead of buying it!! Thanks for a great recipe!! Happy St. Patrick's Day to all!!

UPDATE --I made this again ---in fact I made 2 loaves. I almost bought the irish soda bread at my local bakery because I was getting lazy! I didn't. This bread is so easy to make!! I added 2 T of caraway seeds in each --so glad I did. I again soaked the raisins in Irish Whiskey --- YUM!!. When I made the second loaf I didn't have any sour cream and I didn't want to run to the store so I used 2% greek plain yogurt instead. SO SO glad I did. My second loaf turned out even better. I don't know if this was a fluke but I will try it with greek yogurt again. I also made homemade butter - all I can say is YUM!!! This is one of my FAVORITE recipes.

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: I went for a run this morning. When I got back, DH had made these for breakfast and I barely got in the door before he started raving about them. He included half a banana (will probably use a whole one next time) and used 2 eggs instead of egg whites (dbl batch). He got 4 pancakes out of the recipe and only ate 1 because it was so filling. I plugged everything into the WW pts calculator and came up with 4 ppv per pancake. This is a definite keeper in our house! Thanks for sharing!

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: Very good wings.  I used oil instead of butter and the wings came out nice and crispy.  I would add a bit more salt the next time.  Keeper recipe.  Thanks for posting it.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Very good! I think it was better the next day. Next time I'll toast the walnuts. So easy and quick. Perfect snack cake.Thanks for posting!

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: This was good just served with French bread to mop up the sauce, but I have a feeling it would be very good served over pasta or rice.    Super simple to make.

name: lemon baked cod
review: Easy and Great flavor!  I only cut back a little on the butter and didn't miss it!  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: Excellent way to fix broccoli. I used fresh broccoli and cooked it in my steamer (rice cooker).  I did not add any salt or red pepper flakes, but I did let the mixture sit while the broccoli was steaming.  The garlic flavor really came through and made other seasoning unnecessary (for me).  My kids weren't overly impressed, but my husband and I both enjoyed it very much!

name: tsr version of applebee s oriental chicken salad by todd wilbur
review: This recipe was created by Todd Wilbur from his book "Top Secret Restaurant Recipes" (Penguin /Putnam 1997)

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This gets five stars for easy.  I added garlic, oregano and paprika as per other suggestions.  My husband loves it, my kids and I are OK with it.  But it is great for an easy crockpot dinner.  Thank you.

name: stuffed green bell pepper soup
review: This was really good, we all enjoyed it. I used some leftover diced flank steak and reduced the water to 4 cups and it was still too watery for what we like. After letting some of it boil off, the flavors were very nice. Thanks!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: This recipe was created by Todd Wilbur for his book entitled "Top Secret Restaurant Recipes 2" (Penguin/Putnam 2007)

name: creamy ramen noodles
review: These were very tasty and creamy. Do over recipe:) I will use less of the flavor packet next time. My 9 yr old enjoyed as well.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: This was very convenient to make and made exactly one crust. I found that my crust did need a little extra milk to get it smooth enough. It worked well though I didn't really like the 'oily' aftertaste of the pastry. I will say though that I have only ever made crusts with butter before and that is why I could really notice it. Perhaps the vanilla essence some others have added in their reviews might make the difference.

name: corned beef in beer  crock pot
review: Made this for St. Patty's Day and it was so delish. I used the spice packet and a 12 oz. bottle of pale ale. Cooked on low for 8 hours.The meat was very tender as were the vegetables. Great flavor, so easy, and the leftovers do make great sandwiches. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: This recipe was created by Todd Wilbur for his book entitled "The Best Of Top Secret Recipes" (Penguin/Putnam 2003)

name: easy way lasagna
review: This Lasagna was WONDERFUL!!  When I told DH that it was an "easy" lasagna recipe, he said he was surprised and would never have guessed.  The only changes I made was to add 1/2lb ground beef and onion to the sauce and increase the cottage cheese to 16 oz.  I also wasn't sure if I should cook the noodles or not, so I used no boil noodles and cooked covered for 30 minutes and uncovered for 25. It was perfect!  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: oreo balls
review: I made these for a birthday gift, and everyone loved them. They are intensely sweet, so it's easy to be satisfied with just a couple. I made them in the food processor, coated them with chocolate bark, and drizzled them with white baker's chocolate. They looked impressive presented in paper mini-baking cups.

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: Very good manicotti recipe.  I usually just throw together my ingredients but decided to follow a recipe this time. It was very easy to make and turned out delicious.  I find that when I undercook the manicotti noodles by a minute or two, they are easier to stuff and they soften up fine as they cook.  They were still slightly stiff as I stuffed them.  I liked the addition of the cream cheese and the spinach.  The version I usually make has egg instead of cream cheese.  I used a canned marinara sauce this time but next time I plan to make Kittencal's Marinara that looks wonderful.  I expect it will make this even better!

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: The best ever? maybe not, but pretty darn good! After reading other reviews I grated the apple and wished I hadn't as there were not any discernable apple bits but still lots of apple flavor. I added nutmeg and cinnamon to the batter and topping. After consulting other apple muffin recipes, I used 2 1/2 Tsp of baking powder and 1/2 tsp baking soda -they rose perfectly. I used the fresh butter milk, and softened rather than melted butter in the topping and had exactly the right amount for my 18 muffins. I sprayed my pans and the muffins popped right out, nice and tidy. I baked for 22 minutes and 20 would have been better. I found them a little oily and will sub some applesauce next time. These were a big hit at work. Made for Best of 2010 Tag.

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: Okay, for me this is great recipe and everyone in the family liked it.  I wish I could give it  4 1/2 stars.  It's very pretty and healthy... it has enough flavor that I would like to try it with brown rice (since brown rice is so good for you... maybe the combination of flavors will cover up the thing about brown rice that make my family not like it very well... if they do, I'll change my rating to 5 stars).  Thanks for posting!

name: brown sugar bundt cake
review: This is a wonderful cake to make.  It is so moist.  We love the sugary outside of the cake.  I had this for a get together.  The people just rave over it.  Thanks for posting this yummy recipe.

name: fish tacos and cilantro coleslaw  20 minutes max
review: These are great!  They are so easy to make and they taste delicious.  I added some taco seasoning to the coleslaw mixture as I forgot to purchase some jalapenos.  I loved the cumin and cilantro.  I know I will be making them again.

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: This was awesome and easy. A great, simple side dish! I've made a variation of this by adding thyme and smoked paprika which also gave the dish an extra pop of colour. I'll be making this again. Thanks!

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: These were really good and tasted just like the ones from Red Lobster.  Easy to make and everyone loved, definately a keeper!!  Thanks!!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Made without crumb topping and reduced sugar by 1/4 c, which still yielded a very sweet, moist (and delicious muffin). I also added some cinnamon, nutmeg & vanilla to make it even more special. Thanks for sharing, these were the best banana muffins I've made thus far.

name: the perfect burger
review: The ooohs and ahhhs said it all. Not that this recipe needed another review, but this will be our go to recipe from now on. Looking forward to making these on the grill this summer! I actually broiled them indoors with perfect results, made per the recipe with no add ins. Delicious!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Very good and flavorful.  I tried cooking it on a rack in a pan (I used my cooling rack) and they came out nice and crisp.  Cooked thick chicken breasts for 40 minutes and they were juicy and perfect.

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: This definitely wasn't what I was expecting, but in a good way. First off, I used pork chops. I figured they would stay a bit more solid, but they wound up being so tender that they fell to pieces as I was trying to get them out. I also thought the stuffing on top would get crunchy but it wound up being soft. I loved it so much because it reminded me of a cheesy chicken (or pork, I guess) corn chowder (I added corn, too). It was great! I think next time, I will try it with chicken and pray that it turns out the same consistency! Thanks for posting! 5 stars all the way!

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: These shrimp are deeeeeeelicioussssssss!

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: This recipe was created by Todd Wilbur for his book "Top Secret Restaurant Recipes 2" (Penguin/Putnam) www.TopSecretRecipes.com

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These are great! I bought extra lean ground beef (95% lean) and doubled the recipe. I used Italian-seasoned breadcrumbs, garlic powder, regular salt, and dried parsley. I also added the optional oregano. I baked them at 350 degrees F for 20 minutes on a foil-lined jelly roll pan, and then finished them in simmering spaghetti sauce until we were ready to eat (probably about 30-ish minutes). I wore gloves (which I already have for cutting jalapeno peppers) when I mixed up the ingredients, and I used my cookie scoop to make uniform-sized meatballs. After they were all scooped out, I just rolled them a bit (still with the gloves on) so they were more round. From the doubled recipe, I got 72 meatballs. I used some for dinner and froze the rest. They were the perfect amount of "Italian meatball" spicy-ness. My husband said, "Where do you think the saying 'That's a spicy meat-a-ball!' came from?" Hehe. :) These would be great on a meatball sub. Now I just need a perfect spaghetti sauce recipe. Thanks for posting these, Kittencal!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Perfect biscuits!

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: Excellent recipe that gave great results. Nice thin, crispy pizza dough that held up to major toppings. I did prebake like the instructions said. I topped mine with chicken, tomato, onion, and mushroom. No trouble with it. Thanks for sharing, and we will definitely use this again.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Wow, very simple and very very good!

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Really good, simple bread recipe that doesn't use dairy and is still very moist and delicious. 4 stars, DDW! Thanks for the keeper

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: I have made this several times now and it is always a hit.  The only change I made was to mix onion, garlic, or whatever into plain cream cheese.  Thanks for sharing!

name: peanut butter no bake cookies
review: These were excellent.  My first time making no bake cookies and they turned out just perfect.  Made them for my daughter's baby shower cookie tray and they got rave reviews by all.  Thanks so much for sharing.  I really appreciate the detailed directions on the rolling boil.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: My husband and I both enjoyed this.  I made the sauce separately so I could double the amount.  I did not use all the sauce, so had some leftover to make another stir fry.  Thank you for the very good recipe.

name: sweet  creamy coleslaw
review: This turned out well. I used 4 carrots. Used the food processor to shred everything. My husband came behind me and added some cider vinegar, so I don't know how it would have tasted in it's original form. Maybe next time I will just use the cider vinegar alone. There is nothing fancy about this - it is just simple and easy (and inexpensive).

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: Great recipe! The grocery store had all the ratatouille veggies half price so I had to buy them and then threw them in the crockpot. This is definitely the way to go with this. No more stovetop ratatouille for me. I followed the recipe except I cut the recipe in half. It was delicious. I served it over noodles. YUM!!

name: fajita seasoning mix
review: This was really an excellent recipe!  I love being able to control the amount of salt in the seasoning.  This was just right - not too salty and full of flavor.  We really loved it!  Used to make shrimp fajitas and couldn't have been better!  Thanks for sharing.

name: linda s cheesecake stuffed strawberries
review: These turned out so beautiful, very elegant looking and tasted wonderful.  I used an 8 ounce package of cream cheese and scaled the rest of the ingredients accordingly, including double the amount of sugar as suggested by some of the other reviewers.  I went to the farmer's market to get the strawberries so that I would have the freshest available.  I piped the filling using a #32 tip, and sprinkled ground dark chocolate over the filling.  I used a deviled egg tray as a serving platter so that the strawberries wouldn't roll around.  I made these for a celebration of life gathering for a dear friend who passed away.  That friend had given me a strawberry huller as a gift some years ago and it was always a little joke between us.  So I wanted to do something with strawberries as a personal tribute.  Her family was so touched, and I'm so glad this recipe turned out so well for us.

name: our daily bread in a crock   weekly make and bake rustic bread
review: This is really very good bread for the effort involved. It's not bad if baked immediately, but the flavor just deepens and grows more complex over time. When I knew I wasn't going to be using it the same day, I've used sourdough starter instead of yeast. It worked just fine. I've also added starter in addition when I was running short of yeast. Thanks, French Tart! I'll never go back to tasteless bread from the supermarket.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: I order this soup at Panera and thought that this version was just like it. It is really great. I used vegetable bouillon cubes instead of chicken, so it was vegetarian. I will make this soup often. Thanks!

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: These were a nice change from our regular sloppy joes.  I had to use a nonstick skillet, and didn't need the additional Crisco.  Used toasted buns, and served with chips and veggies and dip.  Thanks for sharing.

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: Very delicious; but needs tweaking. The cream cheese doesn't stir in well and the soup is much too thin, so I run a stick-blender right in the crockpot after adding softened cream cheese, which takes care of both problems. Then, to add texture back into the soup, I put in canned corn.

name: cherry pie filling bread
review: We loved this bread, and we're picky about our bread. I used a scant cup of oil and 1/2 cup of unsweetened apple sauce. Also used splenda instead of sugar.I used self rising flour instead of regular and it turned out great. We toasted it for breakfast, and really enjoyed it. thanks.

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: Very good and will definitely make again. Like others, I sauteed the chicken with onions and garlic in olive oil rather than boil it. Thank you!

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review:
Very good and very moist
here are the changes I made because of the reviews I read. I melted 1/8 cup and used 1/8 cup just regular temp of the butter for topping and I added to topping 1/3 cup oatmeal
for muffins I used in place of all white flour 1 1/2 cup white and 1 cup whole wheat flour
I used 1/3 cup oil and 1/3 cup applesauce
I added 1 tsp baking powder to the 1 teaspoon of baking soda
I used 2 cups grated apple and 1 cup diced apple or 2 large granny smith apples
I added 1 tsp cinnamon and a sprinkle of cloves to the muffin dough I would have used nutmeg in place of the cloves but because of conflicts with medicine I cannot use nutmeg in my cooking
It made 24 mini and 12 regular size muffins. as always each and everyone has a different temperature for there ovens so mine took 27 min for large muffin and 25 for minis it may take less time or more depending on your oven temperature.

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: Made these to go with some chicken soup and my daughter said they were even better than those at Red Lobster.  The only change I made was to add some fresh minced garlic in place of the powdered. (99)

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This was an enormous hit at my house! We were having several folks over and they are used to me using them as guinea pigs for tagged recipes. Everyone loved, loved, loved it. Thank you for posting.

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: This marinade is fantastic and so easy to make. I have everything on hand (I just used bottled lime and lemon juice, and it turned out fine). I marinated chicken tenderloins overnight (about 19 hours, total) and fried them off in a pan on the stovetop. I served them over a salad for a light dinner and it was delicious. I used dijon mustard instead of coarse grain (because it sounded good) and mixed everything up in a gallon size zipper bag (because I'm lazy and didn't want to wash another bowl. I cna't wait to try this out on the grill--I'm sure it will be even better!

name: quick n easy quiche crust
review: Not as nice looking as a rolled crust but very fast and easy. Thanks for posting!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Made this recipe as given, using one of the BBQ sauces I'd made during this Spring's PAC event, & the cooking times for me were considerably different! After 6 1/2 hours on low, I added the sauce & cooked it another hour or so, but that was about it, & it was absolutely wonderful! After a meal for the 2 of us, I kept enough out for one more meal, then portioned the remaining BBQed pork into 2-serving packets & froze 'em! The only way to go, in my opinion! Thanks for sharing this great recipe! [Made & reviewed in Zaar Stars Tag]

name: basic batter waffles
review: It's been a while since a recipe made me smile. I agree with another reviewer that there's the perfect amount of leavening to make these waffles fluffy without tasting like baking powder. I LOVE, LOVE, LOVE that this is a no-fuss recipe. There is no beating of egg whites, no separate mixing of yolks with butter, no warming everything so that butter won't clump from other cold ingredients. Recipes like this make it possible to enjoy waffles on a weekday. We ate ours this morning with strawberries and everyone left for the day in a good mood.

name: chickpeas with spinach  greek
review: Great dish!  Nice and easy to prepare; reheats well.  I sprinkled with the recommended feta cheese.  Thanks for sharing!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Have to say, I'm with the masses on this one! I followed this exactly, except used lard in place of the butter, and talk about flaky.....you couldn't ask for more then this. These were perfect, the directions very concise, pushing lightly down on the dough instead of using rolling pin, all the advice makes a perfect biscuit. Very light and fluffy~ a must try for any and all!

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: All of my kids loved this recipe.. even the pickier ones. I want to live at Kitten's house!!

name: white fish in herbed butter
review: Simple and good.  I like fish simplly done and I love dill.  It is possible to go lighter on the butter here.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Not that this needs another 5 star review but I just can't help myself!

name: french bread rolls to die for
review:
Delicious Recipe! Easy Peasy~ Browned beautifully and was a great addition to the Mahogany stew I made!
Recipe made 16 for me, baked in 16 minutes (my oven is running hot though)
Thank you for a winning roll recipe Marie!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Made this minus the meat and it was still pretty good! Tossed in some vegan eggplant "meatballs" toward the end. I liked the addition of the mushrooms too. Thanks!

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: These were pretty good, but they didn't keep very well.  Rolls that were leftover the next day were harder (even though I had kept them covered) and putting them in the microwave for a little bit helped soften them, but didn't fix it 100%.  I recommend only making these if  you have a big enough group to eat them in one sitting.

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: A good and easy recipe. The spice combination is very nice and the meat turned out tender and juicy. Thank you.

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: This was so easy to put together.. and tasted great!  The chicken cooked perfectly and tasted wonderful along with the jasmine rice.  I used broth instead of water and only 2 boneless skinless breasts.  I used a dish with a tight fitting lid AND tinfoil under neither and it still took 1 hour and 5 minutes to cook.  The rice was still crunchy and hadnt absorbed the liquid after 45 minutes.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Great taste and texture. Thanks x0xMandYx0x :)  Made for cookbook tag game

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review:
I made a triple batch of this when the whole family stayed at our florida house. I put it in the crock pot to stay warm and added some hot dogs on top in case any of the kids didn't like sloppy joes.
Well, the adults discovered that a hot dog with this on top is a real taste treat!! These are the best sloppy joes I've ever made or eaten. I used ground turkey

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: Light, buttery, divine!  And though it has been several years since I tasted the real thing (no Red Lobster in AK...sadness...), I would have sworn I was sitting in one of their nautically-theme booths.  I used lowfat buttermilk mixed with a 1/2 tsp baking soda in place of the whole milk as it was either that or skim and I do love a buttermilk biscuit.  Otherwise, made as written and wouldn't change a thing!  Thank you so much for posting!

name: chili s spicy garlic   lime shrimp
review: Really good shrimp, super quick! I planned to serve this on pasta so increased the butter to 4TBL , and used 5 medium cloves of garlic with 3/4 of a lb of shrimp. For the seasoning I only used a 1/8 of a tsp- my pasta water was well salted, but even without that I never would use this much salt. I subbed red pepper flakes for the cayenne and fresh parsley instead of dried. We really liked the seasoning - it had a nice zing without being too spicy and the lime was a great finishing touch. I don't like tough shrimp so rather then worring about browning I cook it at a much lower temp to try and get it to absorb the flavors, and pull it out off the pan when it's just barely done since it will continue to cook. This make for tender flavorful shrimp.   The whole thing was perfect with pasta we added a sprinkle of fresh parm - perfect! Made for Photographing National Garlic Month

name: jambalaya for the crock pot
review: this did not go over very well at my house.  The chicken was REALLY dry and we could not even eat it.  The shrimp however, were really good.  I think I might try it again and leave out the chicken and double the shrimp...maybe add some smoked sausage in the place of the chicken.  I love the idea of one pot and everything in it.  The kids were so excited that they only had the one pot to clean up.

name: spanish chicken   rice bake
review: We made this while taking the "United Way Hunger Challenge."  For the challenge, as a couple we had to live off of $12 per day for all our meals/drinks.  This was a very economical and easy recipe.  I cut up the chicken into chunks and mixed it in with the rice and everything else.  Also, we used a can of diced tomatoes instead of salsa and didn't have any chili powder.  Still it was very tasty and was our lunch for most of the 5 day challenge.

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: Delish! I made a few small changes - canned diced tomatoes (drained), switched the amounts of cumin & chili (I find cumin can be overpowering), parsley not cilantro, and whole wheat flour instead of corn tortillas. I do not have a 9x9 baking dish so used an 11x7; my layers were a bit thin as a result, so next time I'd probably use an 8x8 instead. Rather than spray the dish, I spread a bit of tomato juice from the canned tomatoes over the bottom. As I mixed this up yesterday, I got a phone call with an invite for dinner out, so I finished assembling the dish then stuck in the fridge overnight. Pulled out today 45 min. before baking, then added an extra 10 min to the covered bake time - worked great! This was tasty with a little sour cream on top. Thanks for sharing!

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: I liked this but the rest of the family didn't. I made the sauce but only put some on the top and didn't put any on the bottom of the pan. I did use the garlic but only 1/2 teaspoon and the rest of my family said that was all they could taste. I did omit the seasoning salt and only used 1/2 cup of cheese in the filling. It was something different. I also had to cook mine for 50 minutes to get the dough cooked.

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: Wowza!  This was SO good!!  Big hit with the teens!

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: Forget about impressing your guests with this one,it impressed me and I made it!  ....lol...it was just what I wanted,thick and rich and absolutely delicious!I reduced the serving size to 2 people.I added 1 chopped chicken breast,fresh parsley and about 3 slices of crispy bacon also.Excellent recipe,thanks.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: A great way to keep the pork tender and allow its natural flavor to shine through.  I doubled the sauce to allow for dipping.

name: aloo gobi
review: It was very nice but I had the same problem as another reviewer of my potatoes not cooking when I just simmered the dish.  I put in two garlic cloves and about a tablespoon of grated ginger in.  I used sambel oelek instead of fresh chilis, at first only 1 1/2 tsp, and then I added another to get it to the spiciness I was expecting.

name: any fruit fast fat free cobbler
review: This gets five stars for being so easy and so healthy. I used frozen blackberries and baked in a 9x9 pan and it was really too thin. Would increase the recipe or use the correct pan size next time. With a tablespoon of light vanilla ice cream, this was decadent and delicious without being bad. The kids loved it, too. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: cheesecake factory cheesecake
review: Everyone LOVED this! I used graham crackers instead of nilla wafers. I put a pan of water on the bottom rack and had no cracks. Used a 10 in springform pan.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Awesome! The family really enjoyed this! Easy to put together, and I love that it contains no creamed soups which always tasts a little off to me. Will definitely make again. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: puppy chow or monkey munch
review: Yummy! Only change I made was to use Cascadian Farms multi grain squares, any similar cereal would work. Made a similar recipe that omitted butter, so I'm thinking I could reduce the butter to 2T without affecting the recipe too much. Just to make it healthier:) Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: Good recipe!  Since they changed the layout of the recipes, it's easy to miss the crockpot directions on the side of the screen.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: Nice broccoli dish. I love broccoli and make lots of it so this was a nice, simple change of pace. I added a little squeeze of fresh lemon juice at the end and it was yummy. Thanks Roxygirl for a nice side dish. Made for I Recommend Tag.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: I've never had the Olive Garden version, but thought that this was a lovely and comforting soup for a satisfying weeknight meal.  I did not use the bacon bits, and added some red pepper flakes for some zip.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Great classic lasagna casserole.  I doubled the sauce portion of the recipe because I like my lasagna on the saucy side.  Didn't quite use all the extra sauce, but really liked it this way.  I used the ricotta option.  Great for a buffet or potluck.

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: I am rating on the technique, not necessarily the combination of spices because I added 3 T of Famous Dave's Roast Chicken Spice and 1/4 fresh rosemary to enough butter and oil for 2 chickens.  The skin was wonderfully crispy and the meat was moist.  Great, quick method for cooking whole chickens!  Ance again a great Kittencal recipe!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Add me to the growing list who enjoyed this recipe.  While tasty, I can't really describe the meatballs as melt-in-your-mouth.  They were easy to make and tasted like....meatballs.  Nothing extraordinary.  Since there are only two of us here, I used leftover raw meatball mixture as hamburgers the next day, as Kittencal recommended.  If you like hamburgers that taste like meatballs, go for it.  We prefer traditional hamburger flavor, and won't do that again.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: My husband said these were the best meatballs he has ever eaten. Wow, that is incredibly high praise. I made a half recipe. I got 19 meatballs that were 1.7 oz. each.   Not only did they taste good, but they were very tender.  I froze the unbaked meatballs for a week, defrosted them and cooked them in sauce and then froze them again for a month before we ate them.  After all that, they still tasted delicious.

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: This is very delicious spaghetti sauce! I made it just as stated and it turned out perfectly. My family enjoyed it immensely. I had plenty left over so I am freezing it to use at a later date for lasagna or stuffed shells. Thanks for sharing another wonderful recipe, Bev.

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: The flavor was fantastic, but mine came out soggy...  I'm going to play around with different ways to crisp it up a bit...  Keeper for flavor for sure though!!  Thanks!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: So good!  I think this has replaced our old creamy enchilada recipe.  I didn't have canned chilies so I chopped up some pickled jalapeno slices and it was perfect with just a hint of heat.

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: These are great beans!  Thanks for such an easy and delicious recipe.  I made it as written using seasoning salt.  I served this over rice seasoned with a bit of lemon (out of lime) and it was great. BF fried an egg to put on top but I enjoyed this vegan/gluten free dish as is. Thanks!

name: skillet parmesan chicken
review: This is great!  It's easy, yet seems like you spent hours on it.  My 2 and 4 year olds love it.  Thanks for a great recipe!

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: These are excellent! I made just as stated only I had to triple the recipe for my family. They turned out deliciously crispy and flavorful. A definite keeper for us! Thanks for sharing.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Very very good.  I followed the directions only using half-n-half and adding some red pepper flakes.  Definately a keeper.  Going into my Favorites of 2011.  Thank you.  Made for Zaar Cookbook Tag.

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: I was anxious to try a variation of my standard spinach salad and this one hit the spot!  Loved the sweet and sour flavor of the dressing.  I sprinkled a little pepper on the salad and Ooh La La the salad was brought to life!

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Wonderful.  The only change I made  was to add 1/4 t cinnamon to the topping along with the nutmeg and sugar.  Baked in 25 minutes.  Thanks for sharing.

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: DS15 and I really enjoyed these.  I used the 1/2 pound ground beef and soft taco size tortillas.  And the result was 2 servings.  I used a cheddar jack blend of cheese which is what I had on hand. I probably only used about 1/2 cup for both pizzas and would definitely use more cheese next time. I used much less oil when I fried the tortillas. Next time I would use more tomatoes and try taco seasoning in place of listed spices.  I also like the idea of mixing ground beef and beans together before spreading on tortillas. Thanks for sharing.

name: better than olive garden alfredo sauce
review: When I make this again, I will make one significant change.... I will DOUBLE it!  This was awesome!  I didn't think I liked Alfredo sauce. But I do, definitely made me fall off the diet wagon.  We had it plain on Fettuccine and it was exceptional!  Next time, we will go with chicken, and the time after that, shrimp and by Friday this week.......

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: These were fantastic!  Thanks for posting.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Best chocolate frosting recipe ever! Replacing my old stand-by recipe from the back of the hershey's cocoa can. I used this on a chocolate cake I made for a friend's birthday and it disappeared fast. Even my son who isn't a fan of tons of chocolate ate a piece & went back for more!

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review:
This was a very nice soup. Was it Olive Garden Minestrone ... NO. There was a few flavors off, not enough tomato flavor and depth of flavors. Spinach, MY OG does not add spinach, but ...
Yes, this was a very nice soup. And I did enjoy it. And yes, there is a little red wine vinegar at the end of cooking, but also red wine in the broth. NOW, everyone has to remember, that a lot of their ingredients are commercial, so we can't duplicate it exactly. But this was very nice.
I added a bit of tomato paste for a little richness, and as I said ... it is close, and very good which is why I gave it 5 stars. I just can't say it is just like OG's recipe.
But definitely worth making!

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: Does this recipe need another 5-star review? No, but it deserves one, so that's what it's gonna get! I added about 1 Tbsp. butter to the chocolate mixture to soften it up a little, and it was golden. I cut these in tiny squares, but kind of defeated the purpose by eating one square after another. I made this for a work function, so thanks for making me look like a rock star with my boss! :-)

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review: This has unanimously been my kids favorite for years now but I keep forgetting to review it. Both the noodles and the chicken are great. My kids prefer not to have green onions in it (they're suspicious of any bits of green in food) so I use onion powder in the noodles instead. I also cut the chicken into strips about 1" by 4" before I marinade it. This way the flavor is infused through even more of the chicken, it also cuts doen on the marinade time by at least an hour.

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: Great Soup!  I did make a few adjustments.  I did not chop my celery, I sliced it with leaves.  I did not add my garlic or zucchini (sliced) until I added my spinach.  I hate mushy zucchini and I wanted the garlic punch.  I did not drain my tomatoes.  After reading the reviews about adding tomato paste I thought why toss out all that good juice.  Due to the added liquid and the fact that I cook my pasta per servings in a separate pot (due to freezing) I only added 2 cups of hot water.  I did add the 1/2 cup red wine and about 1 T. red wine vinegar with about 15 minutes to go.  I topped it with grated asiago at the table.  I'm in soup heaven!  Thanks for posting!  Di ;-)

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: This was very good and so easy to make.  I only made up 2 porkchops for this.  I washed the chops then a good shake of garlic salt and black pepper, dredged in flour and fried til brown on both sides.  I cooked the chops, covered with foil, for 40 minutes in my toaster oven, then added the sauce ingredients.  I made the whole recipe for the sauce.  While this was cooking I put a pot of water on to boil and made Recipe#30358 to make egg noodles.  Looking forward to the leftovers tomorrow.  Can't wait to try this on chicken.   Thanks, yooper for posting this recipe.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: As good as Restaurant chimichangas for sure!

name: homemade pie crust
review: I halved the recipe and used it with recipe #64149.  It was fantastic.  Thanks for posting.

name: funky chicken with sesame noodles
review: I loved this because I love sweet and savory together.  Or maybe I just like sweet.

name: perfect pasta with no watching and no sweating
review: Wonderful cooking method.  Works everytime!  Have been using this recipe for several years and have not thought about rating it until I made it again today, using egg noodles, to go with recipe#34499.  I love that you can just set the timer after you add the pasta, forget about it, and have it come out perfect.  Thanks, Margaret3, for posting

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Fantastic!  This went over really well at the potluck I recently took it to.  The only alterations I made was to add in a few red chili flakes, a tablespoon of brown sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon of fennel seeds.  Otherwise, made as directed using ricotta.  Thanks for a wonderful lasagna!

name: wholly guacamole
review: This was really good!  I think either more tomato & onion or one less avocado might be better and some cumin would definitely take it to the next level.  This will get the job done though - thanks!!

name: dunkley s famous macaroni salad
review: I successfully quartered this a few wks ago. WOW, what took so long for me to try this??  It has such great flavors and I have been asked to repeat this.

name: poverty meal
review: I didn't care for this very much..

name: southwestern stuffed bell peppers
review: This is a great recipe!  I have made it twice now, and once with barley instead of rice.  Thanks!

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review:
I needed a Lenten Friday night meal and this was what I decided to try. I used cream of mushroom soup, a 5 oz can of tuna, and monterey jack cheese because that's what I had.
My family had mixed feelings about it. My husband and I both liked it a lot. Only 1 of my 4 kids liked it, but I have a feeling he just really wanted a cupcake for dessert so ate all of his dinner!
I guess maybe it's not that kid friendly with the chunks of celery and onion, and my kids don't really love tuna anyway.
But, it gets 5 stars from the grownup set!!
Thanks for posting.

name: tsr version of starbucks pumpkin scones by todd wilbur
review: This is a very easy to throw together recipe!!  I used the food processor for the dry ingredients (adding butter was a breeze)  then I used the KA with the dough hook to incorporate the wet and dry.  Very quick!  These are treats to take to work this morning, Thank you for posting!  (I doubled the recipe and make small triangles..at least 2 dozen great for a crowd!)

name: crispy ginger beef
review: This was really good!  My batter didn't really want to stick so it wasn't all that crispy but the flavor is fantastic; I LOVE all of the ginger!  Thanks for posting!

name: broiled tilapia with thai coconut  curry sauce
review: Made this for my sisters family, my neices 6 & 2 devoured it. My sisters friend and I went back for seconds. I used about a tsp more of the curry paste and spices, and cubed the fish and just cooked it in the sauce. I forgot the bell pepper, so I subbed a jar of roasted and it was still amazing. This was a hit, and not too unhealthy! Thank you for posting a great recipe that our family loved.

name: taco bell mexican pizza copycat recipe by todd wilbur
review: Yummy! I've never had a Taco Bell pizza before, but my grandson and 5 of his friends thought that this was even better than TB's. Simple and really good. Thanks for the great keeper Mysterygirl. Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Easy recipe. Turned out far too salty for our tastes (and we love salt!), then I realized that the seasoning in my frozen chicken breasts probably contributed to the salt. If you were using unseasoned chicken, it would probably be about right. I will use this again, but instead of cutting down the ingredients, use 6-8 chicken breasts (we also like leftovers!) and use fresh garlic rather than garlic powder.

name: simple caribbean jerk chicken
review: This was a taste bud explosion!  Wow and loved the smells!  Grill was out of gas so had to do in the oven and was very good!  Can't wait to try on the grill.  Nice to have a versatile recipe.  Thanks for sharing.

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review:
Made this today......very good. I didn't have room to put it into the freezer, so just used the refrigerator for about and hour.
I used 2 smaller pans (I think they are about 8x10) so that I could take one to the grandkids.
Because of this, my cakes were done in about 50 minutes.
The icing made a lot since I didn't ice the sides of the cakes (I iced them in the pans) and sprinkled the one for the kids with mini-chocolate chips.
The remaining frosting I took to my grand daughter to use when she makes cupcakes.
Thanks for a delicious recipe.
Donna

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: Quick and easy... loved the garlic flavors. Made for My review tag; Dreamer in Ontario.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: This was great.  Even better the next morning.  I'm not a fan of basil, so I used my garlic salt with parsley.  Drank the juice the next morning, it was fantastic.  Thanks Malriah!  Made for ABC Healthy Tag game.

name: our daily bread in a crock   weekly make and bake rustic bread
review: FT-  I made this bread recipe last week and all week long.  It is FANTASTIC!!  If I could give you 5 stars for each day of the week I would.  I made a baguette for dinner Sunday, Rolls for pulled pork on Monday, a mini loaf for 2 Tuesday, a baguette Thursday and used ther emainder of dough to make rolls for the weekend.On each the insides were soft and fluffy, not dense or heavy at all as my DS said.  He finished the baguette off after dinner with slathered butter.  For the rolls I wanted some crusty and some soft tops.  For the soft tops I brushed on melted butter as they came out of the oven and they were soft but not squishy.  PERFECTION>  I have a bowl ready to go in the firdge right now for dinner tomorrow and the remainder fo the week more breads.  I may even try some in a loaf pan for sandwich bread but I am having so much fun just taking out a softball doughball and cooking up a storm.  It is the best smell in the morning.  I also plan to incorporate some freh herbs from my garen this week into the loaves. I cannot wait!  Thank you again. edited April 9, 2010.  I have to say I use this recipe all the time now!  If I want a change I change the flour additions to rye or wheat with the white.  I love it, DH loves it and now FIL comes over for some fresh made rolls.Today's dough ball is going to be used to make cinnamon bread for DH.  He mentioned it has been a while lol.  FT you have saved me an enormous amount of money on yeast and an enormous amount of time.  I rarely use my bread makers anymore and I have 2 because I could always have fresh bread baking.  Now I just pull out your recipe on Sunday morning, get it going and I have bread or rolls for the week and each day fresh, resh, freash!  I can't wait til my summer herbs are ready to make herb bread again. Tomorrow with my new batch of dough will make rosemary foccaccia as my rosemary plant made it through winter and is ready for plucking!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Great dressing! I didn't think it'd be so easy :) Thanks so much.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Wonderful!  I used 1/4 hoisin, added peas, baby potatoes and button mushrooms.  What great flavor.  I also coated the beef in flour before browning, that way I didn't need to add the cornstarch.

name: basil pesto
review: This is a wonderful pesto recipe.  I have used it several times and it is definitely in my favorite file.  Love the flavor and it was so easy to make.  Thanks very much for posting.

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: Excellent!

name: intensely chocolate cocoa brownies
review: Loved these! I actually baked them on top of a peanut butter cookie dough. It took about 25 minutes to cook but oh so very good!

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: I made the recipe as written with no adjustments except my fillets did not have skin.  Hubby really liked this, so I gave it 5 stars.  I did really enjoy the taste of the sauce with the salmon, however I really prefer fish to be baked rather than seared, as searing tends to dry it out.  However, you couldn't make the sauce without searing in this recipe.  This was a really easy and fast recipe to do, and that's a plus in my book.  Give it a try, you will enjoy it I'm sure.

name: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits copycat
review: I just love these biscuits! To me, they really are pretty dang close to the ones from RL. I love that in about 2 minutes, I can have these in the oven! (<<--and I did.) Simple and delicious...2 winners, in my book! Thanks for sharing, ThatJodiGirl!

name: buttery bread machine rolls
review: The smell was driving me nuts.  The texture was soft and moisture.  I brought out some butter cos I thought the buns needed them. No way they did!  Very tasty.  Definitely a keeper.  Gave them a melted butter wash before baking them.  Will bake them at 330.  Baked them at 350 but they browned kinda quick.

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: Simple and yummy!

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: This has become one of my favorite soups.  Love it!  Have never had the Olive Garden minestrone, so I can't compare, and I did make a few changes to this recipe.  Did not drain the tomatoes, used chicken Better Than Bullion rather than veg broth, did not add wine or pasta.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Wonderful! We enjoyed every last bit. Made as written. Thanks for the post.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Great!  I used skim milk which worked fine. I would def double the sauce next time and maybe sweat the onions a bit before adding them to the meat mixture.  Tx for the recipe.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Love these!  They are great to stash is the freezer.  I will just throw them frozen into the sauce and let it simmer until they are done.  Thanks for sharing!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Very good.

name: best banana bread
review: I loved how high this banana bread rose. It was very moist and the banana flavor was nice and strong. I would probably eliminate one banana next time so the bread wouldn't be as moist. I like mine a little bit drier (personal preference). Thanks!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Not sure what all the hub bub is about.  I doubled the sauce as other reviews recommended, did everything according to instructions, I even used home made chicken broth, but it didn't turn my crank.  DH said he liked it.  Was it because I doubled the sauce? It didn't seem to flavor the chops much.  Sorry for the review.

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review: Fantastic.  I used all strawberries and added in one mashed banana.  I also cut the sugar down to about 1/3 c, used applesauce in place of the oil, and used whole wheat flour.  These were so moist and delicious.  For me this recipe made 14 regular muffins (cupcake size).   I love them and my kids did, too.  NOTE: DO NOT USE the paper liners.  We lose about 1/3 of the muffin as it sticks to the liner.  However, the mini-muffins I made and sprayed with non-stick spray came out perfectly.

name: spicy shrimp in coconut milk
review: Yummy, I did adjust according to reviewer's suggestions.  I used only one can of coconut milk and no water.  I didn't add salt but did add some lime juice. It was flavorful but not overwhelming considering the amount of spice added. You could pump up the spice if desired.

name: vanilla scented granola
review: Keeper recipe.  The only thing I would change is to reduce the sugar to 1/4 cup because it is on the sweet side.  I did not stire during baking and the granola clumps beatifully.

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: easy! doubled the recipe and used 2 whole eggs.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: Soooo good!! I had planned to make them into pot stickers but I got too lazy. I just served this delicious pork/shrimp mixture over chinese rice. I also considered using it for lettuce wraps. I think the pot stickers would be great when made properly, but I was totally satisfied with my easy version. Don't leave out the fresh grated ginger. It makes it so much better

name: reeses squares   5 ingredients   no bake  reese s
review: These are so good, just like what you'd buy at the store. Next time I will have to half the recipe for the sake of my waist line!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: We all enjoyed our dinner last night. Had no wine so subbed apple juice. Served with couscous and garlic broccoli 132765

name: southern fried chicken
review: Fantastic!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Followed everything to the 'T' & it was a huge hit w/ the fam. Sweet, but not cloying. Perfect. Will make again!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: This will become our newest fav broc recipe. Quick and tasty!!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: Well this was fast and easy! I will use this recipe for those rushed dinner nights (with sports nights, that happens a lot!). I used the garlic powder. Thanks!

name: should be illegal oven bbq ribs
review: Followed this recipe except I cooked at 325 for 3 hours, and didn't seperate all the ribs but cut them into four serving sizes. I turned them three times during cooking. They were so tender and delicious! Thanks for posting this amazing recipe!

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: These are delicious! I used a little less sugar, using a third brown sugar and two thirds white sugar, also used half butter and half oil. I also cut the topping amounts in half and it was just enough for the dozen muffins. They baked up beautifully and were perfect in exactly 20 minutes! I'll definitely be making these again. Thanks!

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: We loved this recipe.  The pork had a wonderful taste.  It was perfect.  It gave a lot of sauce.  Which was perfect to go with orzo.  Thanks Nimz :)  Made for I recommend tag game

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: These potatoes were so yummy.  So nice an cheesy.  Browning the sausage before putting it in the potatoes really helped it not be so greasy.  Thanks for posting this recipe.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: Really good.  I think the sage and Parmesan made these so good.  I sliced a pork  loin into 1/2 inch slices, so mine cooked a bit more quickly.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: We felt it a little bland. I did enjoy the step of using the stems. Made for I reviewed tag.

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: Made this for my mother's birthday luncheon today and it was a hit. I did make some changes. I only used 1 TBL lemon juice, omitted the dill seed and used a TBL of prepared pesto sauce instead of parsley. Will make again!

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
