I used skinless boneless chicken thighs because that is what I had on hand.  I highly recommend you try this recipe, I know I will be making it often.  Thanks so much for posting!

name: soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: These were the best chocolate chip cookies I've ever made! They didn't spread out like the tollhouse recipe and they didn't get that slightly chemical taste like the pudding recipes. Wow! I had 2 sticks of unsalted butter and 1/4 stick of salted, so I added 3/4 tsp of salt instead of 1/2. Next time I'll make it with unsalted and add 1 tsp of salt because I like it slightly less salty. Soooo good, thanks for the keeper!

name: vegetarian  meatballs
review: Excellent! I ground the walnuts pretty fine and followed the recipe to all the way down. I know I'll be making these again and next time I won't use the whole pack of onion soup mix or even bother with baking them in the oven in broth. I might even try to do something different with the cheese either using less or lowfat just to cut back on fat and calories. Thanks so much for this recipe!

name: white chocolate chip cranberry oatmeal cookies
review: Loved these cookies...they're awesome...I used cherries instead of cranberries and they turned out beautiful...gave as gifts for xmas. Thanks for posting!

name: cheat n  eat vietnamese chicken soup
review: I served this last night to my DDS they both loved it and want me to make it again, I added a bit of soy sauce and some sesame oil. thanks

name: easy peezy pizza dough  bread machine pizza dough
review: Super easy.  Started the ABM early, then put the bowl in the fridge after the extra rise time.  I did change the order of ingredients, which is extra important if you're going to set it on a delay timer (liquids first, flour, yeast in a well in the flour).  Worked beautifully.  We'll use this recipe again for sure.

name: easy enchiladas  beef or chicken
review: I absolutely loved this. I made it with ground beef and green enchilada sauce. I loved frying the tortillas, it gave them texture and developed the flavor better. I will never skip that again, no matter how I am tempted. It was also my first time using corn tortillas and I must say I will always use them for enchiladas.

name: shrimp  cocktail sauce
review: Excellent!  Needed a small portion (I halved the recipe) of this because I rarely buy cocktail sauce and when I do it usually doesn't taste good after it is in the refrigerator too long.  Very nice taste and you can make it as spicy as you like it.  I did add some tobasco sauce as we prefer a little extra spice. Yum!!

name: cajun sauteed shrimp
review: This shrimp was delicious and flavor-packed.  Enjoyed for our Christmas Eve dinner and it went well with a rich cheesy rice dish and sweet glazed carrots.  Great entree for a special occasion, also easy enough for a weeknight!

name: poverty meal
review: We grew up with this too, except we called it Goulash here in Michigan. Sometimes we added a can of kidney beans too. Still one of my fave meals, and brings back so many good memories!

name: grilled cheese  diner style
review: Authentic. We made this tonight as a quick supper. We subbed in cheddar cheese because family members prefer it to American. Made as written otherwise. The mayo does a nice job. They do come out diner style. Thanks for posting Dawnab.Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: kittencal s spinach parmesan rice bake
review: Lovely flavors here and a great special occasion addition to the dinner table, but whoa is this ever rich.  I cut back on some of the heavier ingredients, too.  Reheating the next day it was swimming in butter and fat, not too appealing.  I chose a lean entree (pan seared shrimp) to accompany this rice bake; can't imagine it with anything heavier.  In the end, I'm afraid this is just too rich for our tastes.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: My husband really liked this soup. We both love black beans, but I wasn't as crazy about this as he was. I did follow the recipe and didn't add anything or make changes. The cumin was a little much for me, and it tasted more like vegetarian chili-which isn't a bad thing. But when I make this again, I will play with some different ingredients

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: My daughter made this recipe at her house and she used honey barbecue sauce! The pork was very tender and delicious! She served it on potato rolls with coleslaw on the side! Yummy! Thanks for posting!

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: Simple Simple recipe!  I followed directions exactly as stated.  I did not have to chill the dough.  The sugar stayed on top, wonderfully!  I am thinking it might have to do with the time of the year?

name: betty white s chicken wings
review: I used low sodium soy sauce for these, and they were wonderful.  Even with that, they were still plenty salty, but not overly so.  I failed to turn them during baking, but did put the skin side up.  The skin browned up well, which may not have been the case if I had turned them.  I also marinated them overnight, so the color of the chicken changed to very dark - no problem there, just FYI.  They were tasty, tasty, tasty.  I couldn't stop eating them, and I'm not a big chicken wing fan.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Delicious, fork-tender chicken recipe.  My son is blessing you to the skies for posting a parmesan chicken recipe without a heavy breading.  This is beyond good.  Thanks for posting!

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: I realy like this recipe.  I had to add a bit more milk than the recipe called for.  It turned out fluffy and perfect for my cupcakes.  I made a vanilla bean cupcake using #372246.  It turned out really well.  My goal is to fatten up my friends so I don't have to go to the gym - this way I will look thinner than them.  This recipe will help me with that.  Thanks for a keeper!

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: Great recipe! The only thing I did differently was to blend a bit at the end w/ my hand blender. Thanks for posting!

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Very good and easy.  Needed to add a bit more vanilla/milk to get the right consistency, but it worked well.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: I'll add my small voice to the "Greek chorus": Yummmmm!  I'm going to serve these to our supper club this Friday (Epiphany) with Kittencal's moussaka.  As for the sticky "mess" in the pan---just line the pan with foil and put a sheet of parchment down.

name: split pea soup  crock pot    dairy free
review: Followed this exactly, and let me tell you, what a soup! This was terrific, and you have the reviews to prove it too! I also used left-over spiral ham ~ with large ham bone. I almost didn't even need anything else but the bone, ham, and peas. This is a real gem, and you should try it! Made for Diabetic Healthy Month! 2012

name: mahogany beef stew
review: This was the best stew I've ever made.  I had to half the recipe (not enough meat) but it ended up being enough for my husband and I with some (rationed) leftovers.  I used tiny cubes of beef sirloin (sold as fondue style meat) and browned them in batches to make sure they had lots of colour.  Removed the meat from the pan and carmelized my onions.  After adding the wine (all at once) and everything aside from the carrots I simmered for 3o minutes, then transfered the pot to the oven and cooked at 250 for 2 hours with the carrots added.  At this point the meat was falling apart tender and the flavour was so rich. I skipped the cornstarch as it was thick enough without. I served this over mashed potatoes, and tomorrow I will serve the left overs of whole wheat egg noodles for lunch.

name: soft  spicy  heavenly ginger cookies
review: These cookies are awesome, and true to the title!  (soft, spicy, & heavenly!)  They were such a hit, that I've had to make them twice in a week.  Thanks for the recipe, pollen!  :)

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: I microwaved the spaghetti squash to save time.  First I pricked the squash all over with a fork to let the steam escape, then microwaved for 10 minutes.  I let it cool, then cut it in half and took out the seeds.  I thought this could use a little braised onion after tasting it, but my DH loved the recipe.

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Delicious. I made the recipe as directed.I willbe making this again.

name: amazing chicken tortilla soup
review: I have tried several tortilla soup recipes and this is the best so far. I made two changes that I'll share, for the tomato sauce I used El Pato which is a Mexican Hot Style Tomato sauce, you can find it on the hispanic foods aisle in most grocery stores. Added a nice kick. Also, I let my simmer for a few hours to really let the flavors meld. That's it! Thanks for sharing.

name: new york style pizza crust
review: This turned out great. Perfect texture and thickness. It was easy too, well from where I sat sipping my wine it looked easy while my husband was making it. :)

name: grandmas sloppy joes
review: I usually use another recipe to make my sloppy joes, but wanted to try a different one just to make sure there wasn't a better recipe out there.  Although these were good, I still prefer my other recipe and will stick with that one.  I made as directed, but added a little bell pepper for personal preference.  Thanks, Miss Diggy, for sharing.

name: best cream of broccoli soup
review: A great soup!!

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: Delicious soup!  I love all the added veggies in the background and the black beans were great (should eat them more often.)  I subbed Knorr's Homestyle Stock for the chicken stock (as I was out) and just made up the rest with some leftover beef stock in the fridge.  The cayenne proved too much for my youngest (7yo), but that was somewhat expected.  I maybe could have decreased the cayenne by a tiny amount, but not by much as I found it great as is.  I forgot that I had the green onions and sour cream, but honestly, it wasn't missed and was great with a sprinkling of cheese alone.  Oh, and it was absolutely fantastic for lunch the next day, served over rice!  Thanks so much for sharing.

name: perfect rump roast
review:
Perfect is the perfect name for this rump roast recipe! It was delicious.I have never thought of a rump roast as a piece of meat to be roasted, I thought it needed braising but now I stand corrected, thanks Gone Fishin, this has made my little family very, very happy!
**We continue to enjoy this wonderful recipe, years later! And I always take care to use a "roasting pan" on all my "roasts"!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: This was the most amazing Chicken Pie we've had!! After reading the previous reviews that it seemed a little on the bland side, I added a few things to perk up the flavour.  Sauteed about 1 tsp of garlic paste with the vegetables, and added 1 tsp parsley, 1 tsp oregano, 1/4 tsp of paprika, 1/8 tsp of nutmeg and 1 tsp of chicken powder (added this one time, and left it out the second time..) . Also threw in some bell peppers and mushrooms. This went straight in my favorites folder!! I may try it with puff pastry also next time instead of pie crust.. just to experiment :) Thank you for an amazing recipe!!

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: Awesome!  I was actually (pleasantly) surprised at just how much flavor this simple dish has. I subbed a can of diced tomatoes for the fresh but otherwise kept the same.  I will definitely make this dish again.  Thanks for posting!

name: vegetarian  meatballs
review: We used this recipe all the time when we weren't eating meat. It is awesome and really easy. They also freeze great. I would make a double batch and freeze them to use as needed.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Made this for dinner this evening, very good and I most always have the ingredients.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: I recommended this recipe to Lucky in Bayview and then realized I had never reviewed it myself. It is a delicous way to prepare salmon, we love it!

name: zesty italian crescent casserole
review: This was so quick, easy and flavorful. Of course I doctored up the spaghetti sauce with beef boullion, basil, garlic, celery seed, vinegar. Sorry this will not accept any stars. I will have to imput that later.

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: I made this on 1/5/12 for mine and my SO's dinner. Since there was just the two of us and due to shortage of time, a few changes were made to the recipe. I saute'ed  half the amounts  of onions and celery in a bit of margarine until softened. Then 8 ounces of  sausage was added and lightly browned. For the beans, 2 15 ounce cans of red kidneys beans ( one was drained) were used. And as for the green peppers, 1/8 cup of freeze dried was added in along with the beans. I wasn't sure were the bay leaf was supposed to be added,so it was added along with the beans and freeze dried peppers. After letting simmer for a few minutes,then half of all the seasonings were added and simmered for another 25 to 30 minutes.I served this over rice, with cabbage as a side.I do think that if I make this again and only make half is made, the full amount of seasoning will be added.Thanks for posting a pretty good recipe and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: thai coconut rice
review: We really enjoyed this Thai coconut rice last night.  We served spice rubbed snapper over it for a really tasty complimentary meal.  The only change I made was to add a little bit of chopped cilantro that I had left over.  We added the optional almonds (very nice).  I will be making this again.  Thanks!

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: Loved these! So easy to make.

name: chocolate eclair dessert
review: Very yummy! Made it for a barbecue and everyone loved it. I didn't use chocolate frosting because I forgot to buy it. Instead, I melted some dark chocolate chips with some heavy cream over a double boiler. The dark chocolate was a bit heavy for this dessert, so I'd probably use semisweet morsels or the chocolate frosting as written when I make it again.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Excellent muffins.  What a surprise to come home and find that DD had "used up" those old bananas and made these muffins - what a wonderful daughter and a wonderful muffin.  Only change for next time, I would consider is using a little less sugar and try adding some whole wheat flour - to make them a little healthier.

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: Easy and delicious, so much better than anything in a can!  Will make this from now on.

name: awesome baked ham
review: Excellent

name: quick soft breadsticks
review: These turned out so soft, light and tender and so much like Olive Garden's breadsticks that I love.  Not sure why mine took so long to rise.  But when they did...boy are they good.  After baking, I brushed them with olive oil and sprinkled garlic powder on them...So good. I can't make these a lot because I will eat them all up.  LOL.. Thanks for sharing.

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: Great dairy-free bread Kitten! The proofing method produces a super soft, light & soft-crusted bread. Thanks for the keeper!

name: auntie s delicious soft pretzels  amish recipe
review: This is the best soft pretzel recipe, I've found so far!

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: Loved it!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: My house smelled so good while this was cooking, ummmmmm.  I followed the recipe exactly and we loved it.  I didn't have trouble with the coating sticking at all. I did have to bake for about 35-40 minutes as the breasts were quite large. This will definitely be made again and again.  Thank you.

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review:
So delicious! I salt and peppered the meat before browning in a dutch oven, so I could just transfer it to the oven. I didn't have any beer but used a bottle of hard cider that wasn't very sweet.
To my horror, half way through the cooking I realized that I was out of BBQ sauce. I made a double recipe of "Bobbie-Q Sauce" recipe #59772, which was quite tasty! I only cooked it for 30 minutes uncovered with the sauce, mainly because I needed to use the oven to cook the rest of the meal. My husband gave it a rave review. It's a great way to cook those county style pork ribs!
Thanks!!

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: We enjoyed this broccoli.  I used olive oil, but followed the directions exactly.  I think next time, I might add some garlic.  Thanks for sharing this great recipe.

name: magnolia bakery s vanilla birthday cake and frosting
review: Best cupcakes ever! We made self-rising flour and were 1/2 cup short, so we used less milk. They are sooo good. Nothing tastes better than real butter in bakery. We had enough batter for 12 cupcakes and a small 8x8 cake. We made half the recipe for frosting and it was plenty. Wow! Thanks for the keeper!

name: uncle bill s green split pea with hambone soup
review: What terrific comfort food on a cold, blowy, wet winter's day.  I used two smoked ham hocks for the hambone and beef stock concentrate instead of the bouillon.  Big hit!

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: I used this recipe for my dinner idea tonight. I omitted the oil in the basting mix and used a mesquite chicken seasoning that I had with the seasoning salt and garlic powder. I also put carrots, parsnips and potatoes under the chicken on top of a grate so that the fat would drip over them and to the bottom. This produced a moist delicious chicken!! Thanks

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: This didn't WOW me, but my husband loved it. It's basically sausage gravy with tomatoes added!  I don't keep cream on hand, and would rather cut down on the fat anyway. So after step 4, I added 1 Tbsp. butter to the meat mixture. When it melted I stirred in 2 Tbsp flour. Then I slowly added 3/4 cup milk, stirring until thickened. It seemed too thick as I stirred in the tomatoes, but after I added the cooked pasta, the teeny bit of water still on the pasta made it perfect. Add enough salt and pepper and you'll have good flavor.

name: grilled shrimp with garlic   herbs
review: Good shrimp.  I made half a recipe and it was very good.  May try it with pasta and garlic aoli next time.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: This soup was good but the recipe is a little confusing, you should read the other reviews before attempting.

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: I really enjoyed this for breakfast this morning with a wholemeal toasted English muffin.  Similar to how I usually make my scramble but with the addition of baking powder and have to be honest in that I didn't notice much difference, I used olive oil spray and did not use the optional cheese.  Will definately try again but follow Faux Chef Laei's suggestions (read her review after making) and see if that makes any noticable difference.  Thank you kittencal and to catnip46 for the recommendation, made for I Recommend Tag game.

name: crunchy granola
review: A great basic recipe. I added herbs (ie cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg...) to mine. Will play around with it, using different fruits and nuts and spice combinations. Very easy and fun. Getting tons of compliments on this. Fantastic!

name: homemade rice a roni
review: Knocking off 2 stars because cooking time was NOT 10 minutes (took about 5 to 10 minutes just to brown the rice and pasta) and because it lacked flavor written as-is.  I used ORZO pasta instead of cutting up spaghetti.  Next time I will brown the rice first, then add the pasta and brown it sencond.  Did everything as written except I added extra water and added boullion to the water for more of a chicken flavored rice.  Brought the liquid and rice/pasta to a boil, lowered heat, covered and simmered for 30 minutes - liquid was nearly gone.  The rice was still not cooked entirely.  Could have cooked another 15 minutes or longer.  Thankful I added the extra water and boullion.  Gave it so much more flavor - can't imagine just using chicken broth.

name: baked balsamic chicken
review: I made this using boneless skinless chicken breast. Love the balsamic vinegary flavor and seasoning was just right. Wasn't quite as moist as I would wish for, so think I will try next time with bone-in breast or thighs. A solid family pleasing dinner. Thanks, Barb.

name: meatball sub casserole
review: My step-daughter picked this out as the weekly meal that her and I cook together and I'm glad that she did! I made the meatballs as instructed but cut them in half when I put them on the casserole so we had more. I followed everything else as written. The spaghetti sauce that I used was a very thick and hearty sauce so it needed the extra water but I would suggest using less (or none at all) if you have a thinner sauce to avoid the bread getting soggy. I used an Italian loaf that I cubed and let sit out overnight and the next day until dinnertime and the bread on the bottom actually got pretty crispy. I also made sure that I completely covered all of the bread with the cream cheese/mayo mixture to keep the sauce from dripping down onto the bread. Everyone really enjoyed this meal and it is now in our "Make Again" file. The only thing that got complaints was that my husband said when he heated it the next day for lunch, the bread had soaked up the spaghetti sauce and gotten soggy and doughy. It was great the night of but I would suggest making only as much as your family is going to eat because the leftovers were less than stellar.

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: I swear I have made this before! I must have forgotten to review. I only used about 1/2 - 3/4 c. of onion, which was really plenty, but I left the other ingredients the same even though my roast was almost 2 pounds. I brined the meat first, which I think is essential for pork. (1/4 c. salt in 2 qt water for about 1 hour.) I had a sirloin, which is a little darker, so I used a probe thermometer and cooked to 140. (Temp was 145 after resting.) It took almost an hour. The onions turn out really dark and a bit ugly, but they are yummy.

name: poverty meal
review: This made a really quick meal tonight and everyone liked it.  I thought it was a little bland, but the simplicity was hard to beat.  Thanks for posting.

name: cracker barrel green beans
review: Delicious ! Imade the recipe as directed using frozen green beans.

name: hard boiled eggs
review: Worked for me. And yes, I do need a recipe to boil eggs that don't have the grey ring.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review:
This was was by far the best chicken "pot pie" dish I've ever made. It was easy, but I hesitated on the amount of milk. I used a bit over 1/2 cup of milk, but after it cooled I wish I had added the whole cup.
I do think 2 lbs of chicken seemed a lot, and after cooking 4 chicken breasts and 3 chicken tenders, I still only had one pound. But it looked like a lot for my large baking dish, so I went with it. The outcome really was packed full of chicken !!
I added some peas, but had a bit of leftover potato and some cooked carrots, so I added those too , not enough to take up much space in the dish.
I used flaky baking powder biscuits and added some parsley and salt and pepper, and some garlic (about 1 clove.).
I too subbed 1/2 the mayo with sour cream.
Everyone just loved this, and that large casserole dish was gone in no time.
Thanks for a great delicious recipe. I hope everyone will try it.
The baking time was perfect and the rolls came out just right.
Donna

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: Tender and moist, with good flavor. I will add the shredded cheese at the end next time. I used two large boneless breasts, and had to bake for an hour before it was even close to done. I cooked it on a rack and it did not get very crispy, but it was tasty. This might be even better if the chicken were cut-up into large bites. We enjoyed it and I will probably make again.

name: flawless sesame chicken  restaurant style
review: After reading several reviews, I made the following changes:  doubled the marinade, as I had three fairly large chicken breast halves;  added onion powder and extra garlic to the sauce; tossed the marinated chicken in rice flour before frying, which made for a REALLY crispy crust.  Served with broccoli stir-fried with several cloves of garlic and steamed jasmine rice.  Absolutely delicious!  This will absolutely be a regular meal here.  :)

name: lucky sweet and sour sauce
review:
I'm not going to rate this yet because I used orange juice instead of pineapple juice. Made that way, I'd probably give it 4 stars. It was definitely good and I bet it would be a 5-star from me if pineapple juice is used. I'l try it again and give a rating.
1-2012 Used pineapple juice and everyone enjoyed it! Thank you!

name: balsamic chicken thighs
review: I loved these! Used skinned bone-in chicken thighs and they cooked in about the same amount of time. Served with rice which kind of toned down the balsamic - would add more onions next time as they were very flavorful as well.  Quick, cheap and tasty, love it!

name: easy fried rice
review: When I first made this recipe, I didn't realize it said 1/2 to 1 CUP oleo, I assumed it was Tablespoons! Well anyways, I only used about 1 Tbsp. canola oil to cook the veggies in to make it low-fat. (Cooking in a non-stick pan so the eggs wouldn't stick.) I also skipped the celery. It was very good and I will probably make this again. You could also add a couple drops of toasted sesame oil to add more flavor.

name: cinnamon sugar bread  bread machine
review: This is definitely a 5 star bread....HOWEVER, it isn't very cinnamon-y.  It has an amazing texture and a touch of sweetness.  No butter needed, which is nice, since I always go crazy with butter on sweetbreads.  I've never had a bread machine bread come out with such a beautiful consistency.  I did have to add another quarter cup of flour.  I didn't check the consistency soon enough, so I had to stir it in while it was resting, which made for a tough outside crust.  I'll pay attention sooner next time.  There will certainly be a next time!

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: Very good.  I added 1 tbsp instant coffee which added a nice flavour.  I did find it to be a bit lumpy so I'll have to try sifting the ingredients before adding the milk.

name: famous challah
review: My DH made this at the firehouse and it was good, but he prefers Mirj's breadmaker recipe (made by hand). Thanks!

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: Gotta love these low calorie soups!  I found that 3 cups of broth was not near enough for the amt of veggies in my soup.  I did add the kernels off of 2 small corn cobs.  I also added 1 can of diced tomatoes with the juice and then added about 3 T of tomato paste instead of 2.  I also added red pepper flakes to increase the heat.  Overall it was a nice soup.  Like the addition of zucchini.  Thanks for posting!

name: impossible peanut butter cookies
review: My daughter made these last night for my mom who is sick.  She added mini chocolate chips.  They were so easy and turned out great!  The flavor and texture was right on and you would never know that these have no flour.  Thanks for posting!

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: This recipe got me eating cauliflower again.  I add dry seasonings to taste depending on my mood and I eyeball the oil.  Perfect everytime.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: The family enjoyed this dinner and I enjoyed making it because of the effort it took.  Thanks for a great tasty meal.

name: best pumpkin cookies
review: Yummy.  Enjoyed these with a glass of milk.  I used 1/2 c butter and a whole 15oz can pumpkin. Thank you for a great cookie!

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: Made this to go into the crock pot for shredded chicken sandwiches.  I shouldn't have simmered and then put into crock pot.  I grated the onion and skipped the saute.  Sure was tasty, thanks!

name: stir fry chicken with garlic sauce
review: I tried it and it was fantastic!!  I took the advice of one reviewer and used seasame oil and cut back on the honey by 1/4 cup - I also subbed flour for the cornstarch since I didn't have any -- used my food processor to blend everything. I made a double batch of sauce - didn't want to use the leftover marinade from the raw chicken. We had it over pasta.  Can't wait to try it with rice and maybe even potatoes!  Will make this weekly!  Thanks for posting!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Good.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: Quick and easy method to prepare broccoli.  The time was perfect for el dente results; watch it closely if you attempt to cook it longer.

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: Excellent with rabbit. Needed a little more Ranch with 2 fryers. Next time might thin the dressing with milk a little.

name: easy  festive chocolate holiday pretzels
review: I too, saw these in Parents Magazine years ago. They are so easy and such a hit!  My younger daughter likes this version best.  My older daughter likes the "turtle" version made with pecan halves and rolos.  Delicious no matter what combinations you use!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: These are wonderful.  It is a quick, simple to make dinner, after work.  My husband declared these one of his favorites.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: ummmmmmmmmmmmmm so good Mizz!  Followed directions as stated.  Came out perfect!  1/14/2012 - Just wanted you to know, we are still enjoying this!

name: famous barr s french onion soup
review: Yum! Really enjoyed this! Used recipe #438574 and only 3 32-oz. cartons of organic beef broth (equivalent of 6 cans).  From other reviews I thought this might be a problem but it wasn't overly thick. Froze the remainder in individual servings, along with individual croutons (toasted French bread topped with Swiss cheese and broiled) in a separate bag for a quick meal. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review:
Loved loved this recipe. I did not have a Onion gravy mix so I use a packet of Lipton Onion soup. It worked out great.
I also deglazed my pan with a little wine after the browning. I also added a layer of sliced onions over the steaks before pouring the gravy mixture over them.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: Delicious! Was surprised how moist and tender the pork chops stayed. Took 4 more than one inch thick  pork chops and cut in half. There was plenty crumb mixture to coat my 8 chops generously; in fact, next time I'd reduce the crumb mixture by half. Used recipe #360192 with minced sautéed mushrooms rather than canned soup. Also, I cooked 40 before the sauce and 20 minutes after. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: lisa s swirled chocolate chip cookies
review: ***** Not that this needed another review--but here goes... These were GREAT!  I amde with large cookie scoop and flattened a bit before baking.  Baked at 12 minutes each until almost done.  Let them finish on the cookie sheet at least 15 minutes out of the oven.  these were PERFECTION! I used 2 sticks butter and 1 stick margarine and used semi-sweet choc chips-not swirled.  Would be great for school lunches & bake sales using mini M&M's!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Delish!  We gobbled them up.....thought the oven temp might be too high, cooking them that long, but it was spot on!

name: cracker barrel green beans
review: I made these as a side for Thanksgiving dinner and they were delicious!  I did make a couple of changes.  I used only the liquid from two of the cans of beans and I used half the amount of salt and black pepper.  I will definitely be making these again!

name: best baked potato
review: I used this method to make twice-baked potatoes. My whole family enjoyed it. Thanks for posting.

name: my no roll pie crust
review: mine needed much more time & it turned out that I needed to thin out and even out the areas abit more, but it was good and easy.  I chose it over a box mix because I would have had to half the box mix & I didn't want to deal with that mess.  I think I made a good decision overall.

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: I made the low fat version of this recipe minus the anchovies (didn't have any) and with 1 1/2 tsp of worchester sauce. I thinned it down a bit. Everybody was raving about it! I will for sure make this again

name: blackberry cobbler
review: Fantastic no bowl cobbler. I subbed splenda for the sugar and it worked a treat.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: This is a great-tasting meal that comes together easily meal!  As mentioned in the description, it is very filling, as well.  Next time, I think I would add in a bit more of the onion and bell pepper, as we prefer a bit higher of a veggie to potato ratio.  :)  I also would probably add in some garlic next time, too... because I love garlic and it goes in everything.  :P  Will definitely add this to my recipe box!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Perfect!! I used leftover sauce (recipe #26217) and I left out the parmesan inside the lasagna. Instead I just sprinkled parmesan on top of it after it was done. I used ricotta instead of the cottage cheese and I used no-boil lasagna noodles. Since I used the no-boil noodles, I cooked the lasagna for 50 mins. I covered it with aluminum foil for the first 40 mins so that the mozzarella on top wouldn't get burnt. This was better than any lasagna that I've ever got at a restaurant!

name: no bake rice krispies peanut butter granola bars  lower fat
review: Love this!  I added dried cranberries.  I can't wait to experiment with these.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Like others said the texture of this is amazing but it had a bit too much of a baking soda/bitter taste for me.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: I made quite a few changes to this recipe based on personal preference, ingredients on hand, and a ridiculous time crunch. I brined the pork first (1 1/2 qt water, 3 T salt, 1 hour) which I try to do for all pork dishes. I had economy chops and did not remove any fat; I scored the fat on the edges so the chops wouldn't curl. I used a combination of Italian flavored panko crumbs and regular panko crumbs because I was out of other bread crumbs. I also skipped the parmesan (I know, I know - it's even in the title) because what I had on hand was shredded rather than grated and I didn't want to waste it. (I would have just moved on to another recipe, but by that point I was completely out of time.) Also due to the time crunch I skipped both the flour and the egg steps and just put the wet chops in the crumbs, like you do with commercial Shake n Bake. I baked them on a wire rack over the pan and used a probe thermometer set to 150. I don't know how long they took, but it was quick and might have been close to the stated time. My family members seemed to like them, and they would probably rate my version 3* or 4*; I don't give stars when I screw a recipe up this badly. :)

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Genius!

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: This is a nice reliable coffee cake, nothing fancy but way too easy!  I made this exactly as posted, adding the egg, topping with walnuts and baking in a 13x9-inch pan.  Couldn't have been easier!

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: What else can I say that hasn't been said in the 218 previous reviews?  Easy and tasty.  I used a chicken and prosciutto tortellini, which probably added even more flavor.  A keeper!

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Fantastic pancakes and so easy to make!  Don't know if these are anything like IHOP, but these are delicious!

name: cinnamon raisin bread for the bread machine
review: Delicious!  I soaked my raisins in rum and water which was nice.  My bread machine did have difficulty incorporating the raisins, so next time I will just take the dough out for a second and help it along.  I used about 1/2 tsp more cinnamon.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: These are very easy and simple to make.  It almost takes the guilt out of eating wings!  Great for football viewing, too!  Thanks for sharing.

name: chicken pesto
review: This has it all - ease of preparation and fantastic flavor!  What's not to like?  I took the suggestion of Svetlana's review, using refrigerated pesto, fresh mushrooms and adding artichokes.  Delish!

name: sweet chicken bacon wraps  paula deen
review: These were really good but I think they needed some dipping sauce. Next time I'll try dipping them in ranch dressing or BBQ sauce.

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: Delicious!  I made as exactly as posted and was rewarded with a flavorful and hearty soup.  I've never had this at Olive Garden, so I don't know how it compares, but it's wonderful in its own right.  Thanks for sharing!

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: We loved this recipe. I peeled the eggplant, used panko crumbs that I seasoned pretty heavy with fresh garlic, salt and pepper. I also  topped with mozzarella cheese and broiled the last couple minutes of baking. Served them on top of garlic spaghetti with a dollop of marinara sauce. So, so good! Thanks for posting this delicious and healthy recipe, can't wait to make it again.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: This was great!  Used about 2 1/2 tbsp for 1 lb ground beef with 1/4 cup of water.

name: hot dog hamburger buns rolls cinnamon buns dough cycle a b m
review: I made hot dog buns using 1/2 whole wheat 1/2 all purpose flour and they turned out great!  Can't believe how much they look like store bought, only they taste so much better.  Can't wait to try the cinnamon bun version:)

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: This is an excellent recipe, it's so easy and full of flavor.  I marinated it a little longer and baked in the oven, since it's winter.  Everyone really liked it.  I will definitely make this again.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: I am giving it five stars because its easy and good, but I don't think its great.  Not quite enough flavor came through, but thats probably just my taste buds, hence the five stars.  Easy to prepare, just not enough uummph!!! I too added some white wine to the sauce, and then I did have to add some cornstarch slurry to the sauce to thicken it but it did need alot more spices for my liking.  Meat is good, just needs to be jazzed up a bit, however you choose to do it, it will work with this recipe.

name: amanda s cheese pound cake
review: Wow!, This cake is wonderful! I followed the recipe, it's moist, rich, fantastic flavor, and it's  easy to make. It comes out of the oven beautiful. What more could a person want? Well, maybe for it to last longer. Thanks a bunch Jeff!! It's a keeper!!

name: weight watchers general tso s chicken
review:
This is a little different than General Tso's chicken, but it was absolutely delicious. Am trying to make every dish a little healthier lately and was not expecting such a great flavor in such a simple to make dish.
I didn't change any ingredients, but did cut the sugar down to 1 1/2 T., but after eating it, I think next time I will only use 1 T. (I don't think we will miss the extra sweetness, and it saves a few calories.)
I also almost doubled the chicken broth because the sauce got very thick quickly, and we like ours not quite so "gelatinous", if that is a word.....??
Any recipe that makes my family go back for seconds is 5 stars in my book.
Next time I will add water chestnuts, green pepper strips, and some asparagus.
Donna
.

name: spicy shrimp in coconut milk
review: This was great! It was also a great way to use up leftover coconut milk and cilantro!

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Wow!  This was definitely different than any cabbage I have ever had.  I did add a few things to it though.  I followed the directions except sauteed some mushrooms in with it and added a few bacon bits.  Even my picky husband liked it.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Why would you make chicken parmesan any other way? This chicken was so juicy, tender and perfectly seasoned. I pounded the chicken, and smeared it lighlty with low fat mayo just to keep the breading on. It came out perfect. I'll be making this again. Thanks for posting.

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: I browned the chicken first and once the glaze reduced down, I cooked the chicken the rest of the way in it.  I was short one drumstick so I cooked a boneless skinless breast along with the legs.  I used chicken broth instead of water in the glaze and chili flakes.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: I made this recipe using leftover rotisserie chicken,Ive also used leftover roasted as well as fried and it always turns out wonderful..Also used herbe de provence in place of other spices..Cooked noodles in broth al dente set aside till end of cooking time. Bought chicken broth in the box at the dollar store as this recipe takes 56oz of broth..Ive made this recipe many times,everyone loves it and so good for you....Thank U for this great recipe....

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: Delicious and very easy to prepare.  The baking time was perfect, the eggplant was golden brown and crispy on the outside and creamy on the inside.  Instead of using oil, I lined the baking sheet with non-stick foil and did not have a problem with the slices sticking.  This is going into the favorites file!

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: Another masterpiece from the master chef.  Made exactly as directed and turned out exactly as expected.  Beautiful and delicious!  Thanks, Kitten, for another great one. :]   Made again and it rose so high it pushed the top of my bread machine open.  Best bread machine recipe I have ever made.  :]

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: Super fast and easy.  I would reduce the salt to just a pinch next time.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: This was a good recipe.  I have a similar recipe from Southern Living that I have made for years. I could not find that recipe, so tried this one.  It seemed less crispy than the version I have, and I'm not sure my verison uses honey.  It was a nice meal that is easy and quick to prepare.  Thanks for sharing.

name: shrimp  cocktail sauce
review: This was an easy and tasty recipe.  Next time I might up the amounts of lemon juice and horseradish.  It was a little sweet for my taste and this might help cut that sweetness.

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: Took an extra 15 minutes at 375. I used leftover pot roast and leftover 50/50 salad, but it was still good. Next time, I think ricotta and definitely bacon or ham.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: EXCELLENT RECIPE!  I have tried many different recipes for Shepherd's Pie and this on is THE BEST!  As recommended I used Ketchup but that was the only change I made.  Thanks I will definitely be making this again!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I gave this 4 stars. My family really liked this recipe. Even my picky 9 yrs old newphew ate this right down. When I made this I added some baby carrots and chunked up potatoes in the bottom of the crock so I did add like 1/4 cup water so the veggies wouldn't stick. Our only complaint about this recipe was the amount of Peppers. This was a bit to spicy for our taste. So next time I will cut back on the Peppers. I reserved the juice from the crock and the next day I made chicken n' biscuits. So loved this recipe as it fits as a cook it once it 2 or 3 times meal! I will make this again for sure! Thanks for posting a great recipe! Christine

name: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits copycat
review: These are super easy to make and delicious!  I did make a few changes.  I added in more cheese, probably more about 3/4-1 cup, added in garlic salt to the biscuit dough, and added garlic salt instead of garlic powder into the melted butter.  These had a really nice flavor. The outside was slightly crunchy and the inside was nice and soft.  Will definitely make again.  Thanks for posting!

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review:
5 Stars! This takes just like a Duncan Heintz cake mix, or some other boxed cake mix. INTENSELY chocolatey and moist and rich. And the thing about it is, this cake actually gets BETTER WITH AGE!!! I made it on a Thurs. evening. Didn't touch it till the following evening. And today it is Sunday and it is even better than the previous days! I've also frozen one (frosted and ready to go) with high hope that it will freeze well due to all of the oils and fats! Will try to post back with the results of that in a couple of months or so! ;)

The icing is really smooth and really creamy. It's like a cross between a butter cream and a whipped cream. There is something about it that I don't like...and yet, it works with this cake.I don't know if I would make it again. I might add some more flavor to it by making it chocolate or something. There is a blandness to it but underneith that it is very tasty, so it just needs something else, but I don't know what.

If I need to make a layer cake to impress, I will certainlly go with this one. Espically tasty decorated with cocolate chips!

Thank you Karen!

name: southern fried chicken
review: This was really easy and really good. Thanks, Sharlene~W, for a very satisfying fried chicken recipe. Made for Best of 2011 Cookbook tag as recommended by gailanng.

name: pan roasted broccoli
review: Not much I can add to 161 4-5 star reviews. :)  I buy broccoli florets in big bags at Costco (we eat it a lot) and it doesn't have much in the way of stems, so next time I will buy a stalk at the grocery store and slice bigger pieces of stem.  I think this would be good with some red bell pepper strips also.

name: yummy baked potato skins
review: Absolutely scrumptious!

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review: We saw this on the front page and thought that it looked simple and easy to make.  Didn't need to look any further!  Very tasty, we served with corn, mashed potatoes and a simple cucumber salad.  Thanks Bergy.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: Just a warning, I may gush in this review.  I just made pizzas using this dough and I am overjoyed with the results.  I have had no luck in the past getting the crispy crust I was after and was disappointed time and time again.  I was thrilled to discover this crust is crispy with a wonderful flavor and is sturdy enough to hold an abundance of toppings.  I doubled the recipe and used it to make 3 16 inch pizzas.  The results were exactly what I was looking for.  I highly recommend this recipe.  Like, really, really, really recommend it...

name: blackberry cobbler
review: 1/15/12 I made this using a marionberry pie filling and it turned out great. Just take care not to add to many dollops of your filling.  I will make again with fresh berries next time. Just delicious with a scoop of ice cream. 1/22/12 I made in ramekins and they were just as yummy! I used 1/3 C per ramekin. A little more will work to fill the cups more. Baking time: 30-35 mins. Perfect for dinner guests.

name: really good vegetarian meatloaf  really
review: I've been a vegetarian for over a year now and haven't had a meat substitute that I've liked more than this.  The consistency and flavor are great.  I added BBQ sauce to the top, and that made it perfect for me.  Thanks for a recipe I'll use over and over!

name: amazing chicken tortilla soup
review: Added celery, carrot, and zucchini to up the vegetables in my family's diet and also to add bulk (I'm feeding 2 teenage boys).  Put crumbled tortilla chips and cheddar cheese on the table for each person to add as they like.  Delicious and filling.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: It was my first time making chicken wings and it won't be the last one.  This is a great recipe.  I like that it's not fried.  Unfortunately, when I made them, I didn't know I had just a little bit of louisiana hot sauce left in the bottle.  But it was still spicy.  I omitted the salt.  Thanks WhoDat :)  Made for Best of 2011 tag game

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: So good!  The best chicken breast I've ever had! :)  I used Progresso's Italian-seasoned panko bread crumbs, and that made it nice and crispy.

name: jo mama s world famous spaghetti
review: I have my own special homemade spaghetti sauce that I make, but I have to admit that this is definitely a very strong contender.  I used half hot Italian sausage and half mild, but otherwise made as directed.  This sauce is full of flavor and a bit spicy from the red pepper flakes -- just like we prefer it.  I have been sampling all afternoon, but will have to wait until we return from our meeting tonight -- just hope I can keep my mind on the agenda vs. the delicious spaghetti that is awaiting me. This sauce will provide some great leftovers for this week as well. Made for the Cookbook tag, January, 2012.

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: My husband really liked this meal; I halved the recipe for the two of us and it fed us for two meals, so it makes a lot. I used just the egg white when halving the recipe.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: Delicious! We loved the sauce! We've never had salmon prepared anything like this before.

name: perfect pasta salad
review: I left out the pepperoni and tweeked the dressing a little bit for my taste.

name: momma s fair funnel cake
review: Delicious!  Makes a huge amount, so next time I'll listen to those who made this before me and halve the recipe for my crew.  The kids loved shaking the powdered sugar over these... and wearing it, of course.  Lost a star for us because the batter was way way too thick to go through a funnel, even after adding lots more milk.  Thanks for sharing.  This was really fun to make.

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: Delicious and moist cake.  Thanks for posting.

name: sticken chicken
review:
This was a really tasty way to make chicken thighs. I made the recipe as written except I had a tray of 10 thighs to use up. I didn't need to increase the amounts of the flour mixture or the sauce - there was plenty of both.
After the first hour at 200, there was nothing to drain out of the pan, so I just added the sauce mixture and put it in for the next 2 hours at 250. I flipped them after the first hour.
Once they were done, I poured the liquid into a gravy separator to let the fat float out of them. Adding some cornstarch mixed with water and cooking down the sauce made it perfect for pouring over the chicken and rice.
Thanks for a great recipe.

name: chili s spicy garlic   lime shrimp
review: I've never had Chili's shrimp so I can't compare.  This is amazing.  The only change I made based on other reviews was to use less salt.  I used 1/4 t, otherwise I didn't change a thing.  Served with corn tortillas, diced cabbage and homemade salsa.  I'm typing the review before I've even finished the first taco.

name: tsr version of olive garden pasta e fagioli by todd wilbur
review:
I would make this again! It definitely tastes healthy, but in a good way. I worried that it would be overly acidic/pungent, with all of the tomatoes and the vinegar. But I guess that the long simmer time allowed the sweetness from the carrots to balance out the other sharp flavors, and it was very nice.
*I forgot to purchase the V-8, so I used water instead. It was fine, but I can imagine that the veggie juice would add even more yumminess and nutrition! Will use it next time.

name: homemade hamburger buns  bread machine
review:
I had to come back and tell you I love this recipe and made paninis this morning; great success!
I was so happy to find this recipe.It was great!
I wish my camera was working;they look amazing and taste even better! I made them with 1/2 whole wheat and shaped them into 8 paninis and 8 dinner rolls.Thank you so much for posting this Marie. You made my day!it will be a family favourite.
Rita

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Great recipe and definitely fast which I sure needed this morning. I did use the egg and added the walnuts and some chocolate chips as well as the glaze. It was devoured at my ladies group. It was so quick and easy, I will definitely make again!

name: queso blanco dip
review: I usually end up using milk and it is still great.  I add fresh pico de gallo instead of the chiles.  Way better than the Rotel/Velvetta version of queso.

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: Absolutely fabulous!  I used King Arthur White Whole Wheat flour and added garlic powder, a bit of grated onion, and poppy seeds to the dough.  A winner!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: I had to add my voice to the praise of this recipe.  My son and I made this for lunch, and he loved it (so did I). I was a bit put off by the 'frying' of the beef, but dutifully complied, and now I wouldn't change a thing.  Thanks for posting!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: So easy and so good.  This is a keeper recipe especially for all the working mom. I added 1 tablespoon of garlic chili because my family likes spicy food.  Everything else was the same. Man, is it good. I used the same amount ingredients on 14 drumsticks.

name: honey ginger grilled salmon
review: This was fantastic.  The marinade was very flavorful, with the honey and orange juice tempering the zesty touch of the soy sauce to produce a delightful flavor sensation.  The marinade didn't seem to penetrate very deeply into the salmon though, so I will let the salmon marinate much longer next time, hopefully flavoring the fish a little more deeply by doing that.  Thank you for sharing your recipe, Mirj.  Made for the "Best of 2011" tag game.

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: Halved the recipe and made two massive burgers.  Ooeey, gooey, drippy deliciousness!  A definite do-again.  Many thanks to gailanng for including this recipe in her Best of 2011 cookbook!

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: This was a HIT!!!!! Have made 3 loaves in the past 2 days and they keep disappearing.

name: orange julius smoothies
review:
I tried this only for myself, but next time I will serve this to my family and guests as well!
Thanks for this smooooooothy!

name: roasted broccoli w lemon garlic   toasted pine nuts
review:
I liked the texture of the broccoli very much as same of the combination with pinenuts.
I did not know that was possible to prepare broccoli directly in the oven and I tried out roast the pinenuts together at the same time. Come out perfect and I would do it again!
Thanks a lot for this yummy recipe and teachint!

name: zesty low fat chicken breasts
review: We enjoyed this very tender chicken. It is quite sweet so if you don't like sweet you will want to decrease the honey. My husband liked the sweet, I would prefer a little less sweet but it was still nice. Quick and easy weeknight meal. It did make a mess of the baking dish so be prepared to soak it. Thanks for sharing another very good recipe. Liked it even better second time around. So good!

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: The family enjoyed this! Easy, too.  Used 3 cups of cheese, 8 regular-sized tortillas, and a can of organic mushroom soup. Didn't find the dish dry as some have commented. Didn't add salsa or rotel. You could, but definitely not necessary. Thanks for the recipe!

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: I like enchiladas but they can be gratuitiously calorie laden.  And the sauce you buy inthe store is not that good.  But I had some chicken I wanted to make enchiladas with AND I thought this recipe looked good.  The allowed by to avoid over-fatting the tortillas.  I just drug them through the warm enchilada sauce and made chicken cheese enchaladas with a little extra sauce poored over the enchiladas.  And cheese.  I was short of time so I nuked the enchiladas.  These were surprisingly good nuked.  And since it is just DH and I, I have left over enchilada sauce.  Will be making more.  And I say that with anticipation.

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: The fluffiest eggs I have ever made. Even with my dietary modification it worked. I had read baking soda before tagging this recipe, when I realized it was baking powder (which we do not use because of corn or cream of tartar) I thought my typical substitution wouldn't work. I use baking soda and organic apple cider vinegar for the similar effect. I used canola oil as I didn't have butter on hand, Carnation evaporated milk as that is what was in the refrigerator, sea salt, plus the rest of the ingredients, no cheese. Made for All Aboard the L-O-V-E train! 1/23 - 2/14

name: unbelievably easy potato soup
review: This is the way my mom always made potato soup and I love how wonderful it tastes with so few ingredients.  The only thing I add is bacon bits.  I think it's best with whole milk or half and half.  Love love love this recipe....makes me feel like I'm back home eating my mom's soup!

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: These were great!  I made it with chicken thighs and they cooked at 375 for about 75 min.  They came out tender and yummy!  The sauce was pretty thin but we got a thin layer of carmelization.  This was an easy week night staple.  Thanks for the great recipe djmastermum.....

name: kale chips
review: These are good. They are different for sure, but they are definitely crunchy. I added garlic powder to mine after baking to boost the flavor. I think parmesan cheese would be a good after-baking topping too, in a small amount. Barbecue seasoning would be good also! They probably won't satisfy a potato chip craving, but they are good all by themselves. I will make these again. Thanks for sharing!

name: texas red enchilada sauce
review: Great recipe! When I tasted it in the pan, I didn't like it much and would have given it 4 stars, but on the enchiladas it was perfect! I did add another tsp of chili powder and a half tsp of sugar. I think it would be even better with chicken stock instead of water, so I'll try that next time. Thanks for my new go-to recipe!

name: nutella hot chocolate
review: Dangerously good.

name: crock pot ham and beans
review: These are good and filling and a little different with the cloves.  Thanks!

name: denny s style french toast
review: Great stuff! Did skimp a little on the sugar, and served with strawberries. Nom. Thank you!

name: microwave poached eggs
review: Quick and easy way to poach an egg.  Not sure what the tiny amount of vinegar does, but I followed as written.  I need to cut the cooking time a bit in my microwave, as it is high powered and takes some getting used to :)  I love poached eggs but hate waiting for water to boil and then cleaning the pan, so this will be great for me.

name: baklava salmon  salmon with honey  butter  walnuts  and mustard
review: YUM! What a delicious combination of flavors and textures. The mustard (I used a coarse country dijon), honey and walnuts were sooooooo good with the salmon. Directions for cooking were perfect. The only change I will make next time is to decrease the breadcrumbs  to 1/8 cup and increase the chopped walnuts to 1/2 cup. Thanks for a keeper! I'm putting this recipe into my best of the best file. :)

name: beef roast
review: Pretty good.  Easy recipe.  Cooked it yesterday, sliced meat and stored meat and gravy separate in fridge.  Poured gravy, thinned with a little water, over meat and heated in oven while preparing rest of meal.

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: I made this using part mayo and part sour cream and I sprinkled the casserole with dried basil. The chicken was oh so tender! Good recipe.

name: low carb pizza
review: I really, really wanted to like this, but it was just edible to me. It would be nice to have a low carb substitute for the real thing. The egg and cream cheese mixture just didn't make a good crust. I'm sure some people would like it, but it's not for me.

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: These are delicious.  I did add some Italian Sausage to ours but it was still great.  Tahnk you for shaing.

name: best albondigas soup
review: Absolutely delicious!  We doubled the meatball recipe and froze half to make this a super quick meal next time.

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: This is a wonderfully flavorful & satisfying soup!  I made this exactly as directed, using vegetable broth instead of the chicken.  The spices were right on for our taste.  I served with a French Baguette with olive oil and balsamic vinegar for a complete meal.  Definitely going into my permanent recipe collection!  Thanks for a delicious recipe, justcallmetoni!!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Made this with bone in chicken and it was terrific!  Thanks.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: We really loved this fajita recipe...it was easy, and delicious...I made it with chicken and plan on trying the steak as well...this one is a keeper for us...thanks for submitting.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: I made this last night for dinner and we loved it.  The parmesan is so flavorful when baked....yummy.  I followed the recipe exactly and baked for 22 minutes.  The dish came out perfect.  thank you for sharing this great recipe with us.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: Boy were these YUMMY! My husband just raved and raved. He said to give you 100 stars!  Hee Hee.  :-)

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: This is a great recipe. It is very sweet.  If you want to be sure to have enough to frost, fill and decorate cupcakes or a cake I would suggest making either 1.5 times or 2 times the amount of frosting.  I frosted red velvet cupcakes with this frosting.

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: I really loved this.  My hubby...not so much.  He does not like the texture of spaghetti squash.  The kids all liked it once they removed certain things.  Two removed the black beans , two removed the cooked tomatoes, and one ate everything.  I am going to see how it warms up and maybe make it again for me for lunches at work.

name: orange julius smoothies
review:
I added almost 1/4 cup of coffee mate creamer, per another recipe on food.com. My kids really liked it and so did I.
Thanks for sharing.

name: our daily bread in a crock   weekly make and bake rustic bread
review: I have using this recipe for over a year now.  It is wonderful!  If I have it on hand I use fresh yeast and it makes this recipe even better.  I would add notes or hints on how to make it better but French Tart has really covered all the bases on this perfect bread.  Sometimes, on request of my husband I make it into a thin round like a pizza and cover it with crushed garlic, salt/pepper and then dip into a marinara sauce.  Other times i make smaller loafs and use them for sandwich buns.  Always having fresh bread dough on hand... I think this is quit possibly the best recipe on food.com and has made many of our meals happy ones.  Thank you French Tart!

name: master brine recipe for meats
review: Nice! I used it on a whole chicken I lightly smoked in a BBQ which can normally dry out the meat but this left it super tender and perfectly seasoned.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: Very good! Thanks for posting.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Not that this needs one more review, but this rocks.

name: tilapia
review: Wow, this is flavorful.  I made this for my family and it was devoured.  We like fish (of all kinds) but sometimes it can be a bit bland.  Not this recipe.  We loved it and I will make again, its quick, simple and I always have the ingredients on hand.  Thank you for sharing your recipe with us.

name: vegetarian  meatballs
review: I made these for my vegetarian daughter.  I froze some but the first 5 I added to spaghetti sauce.  She loved them, she took the left overs for lunch.  The next time I made them with a vegetarian brown gravy and served them over pureed cauliflower and she took the left overs home we still had some left for another time.  She told me she craved these.  Very nice recipe, however I think a meat eater sure could tell the difference.

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: Great wings. Simple, easy, and delish. Thanks for sharing. Made for Cookbook Tag.

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: Very good! Not great, I think- The muffins are very good because of the apples. I would like more flavor in the actual muffin- maybe more spices? They weren't too dry and the topping was SUPERB!

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: Very, very good sauce.  I made this to go with your manicotti recipe and we loved it.  I did add the wine and let it cook for about 3 hours (since I had the time) and it was flavorful, thick and absolutely delicious.  I will ALWAYS use this sauce for manicotti, its so good.  Thank you Kittencal for sharing your recipes.

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: My daughter is a vegetarian and when she comes for dinner we make one meal and it is vegetarian, we all loved this and the next day I made a sandwich with the leftovers added onion and Heinz 57.  Very good recipe,

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: 5 stars.  I started the cooking Sat night before bed, and had it ready for dinner and to pack lunches Sunday night.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: The flavor was excellent, and so easy to put together. I used boneless skinless chicken breasts and they fell apart to almost a pulled chicken consistency.  I did end up adding some water as it seemed to be cooking really dry (most likely due to using breasts only). I took half of what I cooked, cooled it and mixed with mayo, celery and chopped onion to make chicken salad for lunch the next day. So flavorful. I would definitely not use more than 2t. of salt, it was plenty salty with just that amount, I would consider reducing the salt more if I made it again. Thanks for sharing!

name: chicken salad for sandwiches
review: This was inspiration for lunch today. I didn't have chicken breasts but I did have canned chicken which I used. I also topped this with a bit of seasoning salt. Tasty - thanks

name: roast  sticky  chicken
review: I was so surprised how well this chicken turned out. The chicken was cooked perfectly and was really fall-off-the-bone tender. We enjoyed the spice mixture, which made the chicken very flavorful and different from my regular roast chicken. Thank you for a great recipe!

name: apple or pear cake
review: Absolutely delicious. I had a small taste and I hope I can stay out of it. It is so rich. Not for the calorie counters that's for sure.  I will definitely make this again.  A real keeper. Thanks for an easy and eye-appealing (no pun intended)apple cake recipe.

name: healthy bean soup with kale
review: Fabulous Recipe!  I halved this for just my husband and I.  After tasting it, I wish I had made the entire recipe.  This is a very satisfying soup and the spices are right on target.  I used fresh carrots and used about 6.  I will definitely make this wonderful recipe again!  Thank you, Barbara Steele, for sharing!

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: Yummy and easy!!!  Added a bit of onion and it was perfect!!  Thanks!

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: I only had a 1.5lb turkey breast so I only got about 1 cup of drippings.  I scaled the recipe back to 2, and added 1 cup of broth.  This was an awesome, quick gravy.  Thanks:)

name: herbed pork tenderloin
review: Very moist and flavorful. Nothing spectacular about the ingredient list, but the fact that it doesn't require marinate time but still comes out tasting great is an excellent reason to get 5 stars! I haven't made tenderloin in a roasting pan before, it turned out very good. Will definitely keep this recipe!!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Excellent flavor but a little too rich with 3/4 cup brown sugar. I used 1/2 a cup and still found it was just too sweet. I may toy with this sauce and add some rice vinegar to balance the sweetness. Also, I stir fried the beef in a little oil instead of the amount listed and I used boneless sirloin steak instead of flank steak. Will make this one again with a little tweaking.

name: easy way lasagna
review: I was looking for a quick lasagna recipe, and this fit the bill.  I added cooked ground beef, and used quick-cook lasagna.  (I didn't boil it beforehand.)  Because of the speed and convenience, I was surprised at how absolutely delicious it tasted!!  This is going to be a staple in our house.  Thanks so much!!

name: doctored up vanilla pudding casserole
review: Yeah it is that good.  I switch up the kind of cookies I use.

name: chinese buffet style donuts
review: Usually I make a powdered sugar and milk glaze for these little babies instead of the sugar.  My brother and I would make these on Saturday mornings growing up after we were allowed to use the fryer.  He has passed the tradition down to his 4 kids.

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: Wow, this is really good.  I wasn't sure about a curry dish but its so good.  I made just as written except used regular raisins (what I had on hand).  We loved it, it was just the right amount of heat.  Thank you for introducing me to a new flavor.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: This is delicious~~I would give it more stars with the exception of the fact that the nutrition values do not match up with MyFoodDiary.com.  I put this recipe in exactly as listed in "Nutritional Facts,"  What MFD came up with was calories 398.75, fat 18.4, carbs 20.23 g, protein 35.33.  So there is a big difference.  So check for yourself but be careful.

name: christina s killer dip
review:
WOW, this is amazing! Sooo creamy and yummy! Mmmm, I could hardly stop myself from eating this, it was so good with crudites and crackers. I totally forgot to add the seasoning, but it still came out flavourful and I loved it. Instead of sour cream I used low-fat yogurt as thats what I had on hand and it worked out nicely.
THANK YOU SO MUCH for sharing this keeper with us, MythThyng.

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: I absolutely loved this!

name: chunky blue cheese salad dressing
review: Delish! And I haven't even let it sit yet.  I can't wait until the flavors blend with this.  I was a little leery of such a long list of ingredients, but I had almost all of it already, so it's all good.  I used my microplane to grate the onion, so I dumped the onion juice into the mixture as well.  Used Frank's Red Hot, since that's what we have, rather than Tabasco, and a packet of Splenda (equals 2 teaspoons) rather than sugar.  I also make my own mayo, so I used that rather than buying any.  The small taste I had was fantastic.  I'm going to have this on a spinach salad tonight, but I can't wait for my SB party to have it with buffalo wings.  Thanks for sharing.  Not sure I'll buy dressing anymore.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: Really good hearty soup.

name: english muffins  bread machine method
review: These were so easy to make. I divided the dough into 8 balls then flattened them for the rise at room temperature.Should have made 10 they do make very large muffins. I did use Recipe #165437 for 1 cup of the flour to 2 cups of bread flour. It did take 6 minutes per side to cook.

name: chicken pot pie with 2 crusts
review: Very good!  Even my husband who thought he didn't like pot pies, thought it was great!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Just what I wanted!  Added in chocolate chunks and used oil instead of butter.  Thank you for a tasty quick treat.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: congratulations on Recipe of the Day. This soup is spot on and the only thing I can eat at Olive Garden (due to an oregano allergy).  If I closed my eyes I would swear I was at the restaurant. The soup is rich and creamy and luscious. I did add Heavy Cream just before serving and did not bring it anywhere near the boiling point. I also used frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry and added it to the soup just at the low simmer point.  Thank you for posting!

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: Yum!  This is most certainly easy and tastes great.  I used about 3 lbs of chicken with the full 18 oz of sauce, which worked out great.  The meat was tender and flavorful and made great sandwiches.  I have plenty of leftovers, which we look forward to enjoying.  Thanks for sharing!  L-O-V-E '12 Event.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Quick, light and easy.  Perfect for a summer meal!  We really enjoyed this!  I used my pamper chef chopper to chop the onion, mushroom, water chestnuts, and fine chopped the chicken with a knife.  I found the process simple!

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: I've made a number of stuffed peppers over the years and these are by far the best.  My DH who doesn't like green peppers and usually only eats the stuffing, ate the whole thing.  This recipe is definitely a keeper.

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: This is the first time I've attempted made-from-scratch biscuits, so I'm not going to rate this recipe. Mine didn't turn out at all. I followed the instructions and tried to handle the dough as little as possible. The biscuits didn't rise from the 1/2 inch I cut them at. I'm not sure what went wrong, but I think I'll stick to frozen biscuits from now on.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Not bad, but the white meat turned out dry rather than tender. Very easy. I found it a bit spicy, but would probably not reduce the spice because I did like it.

name: crock pot chicken taco meat
review:
Great stuff ! Since we have to watch our sodium intake I made this with LOW SODIUM chicken broth and NO taco seasonings.

It is still a fantastic recipe for salads and tacos etc. We just add our own seasonings and love it.
Thanks!

name: unbelievable baked buffalo wings
review: With a chef name WhoDat why did I wait so long to try this recipe?!  I should be slapped.  This will be my go to recipe for wings.  I found broiling on high at 15 minutes made my wings start to burn, so switched to low broil half way through. Otherwise followed the recipe.  I did throw in some bleu cheese dressing, celery and carrot sticks, but otherwise left this recipe alone!! Perfection!  My 2nd quarter wing recipe for Super Bowl 2012.  Thanks for sharing!

name: peanut butter chocolate chunk cookies
review: These are pretty good. The only change I made was to use an all natural organic peanut butter - next time I am going for chunky JIF

name: perfect pasta salad
review: Perfect Pasta Salad, for sure! Loved every bite! I added some sun-dried tomatoes, and some celery, but other then that, stayed perfectly to the recipe. This is indeed, one happy, lovely, and delish pasta salad! Made for Cooking Out of the Pantry 2012 -Canning Forum

name: kale chips
review: I don't know what I did wrong, but my chips got really burnt really quickly. I followed the recipe and baking temp as stated and I omitted the salt and after only 7 minutes, all of the little kale bunches were shriveled up and burnt. It actually set off the smoke detectors in my house. I will try it again tomorrow and in the meantime, if anyone can tell me what I did wrong, I would love to know so I don't waste more good kale and so I can re-rate this recipe with a lot more stars. :(

name: kittencal s perfect prime rib roast beef
review: The title says it all. It really was perfect. This turned out so juicy and tender. Thankyou for posting such and easy mouthwatering recipe.

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: Really good and easy to put together. Thanks for posting!

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: This is good!  I omitted the green onions because I didn't have any...shouldn't have!  I thought it was way bland without them, and can just imagine them doing the trick.  I added some ground beef to this also, which worked fine.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: What can I say that hasn't already been said?  This was wonderful and the aromas were fantastic.  thanks.

name: new york style pizza crust
review: This produces a wonderfully tender and fluffy crust with a nice crisp on the bottom from the cornmeal (I also oiled the pan with a good bit of evoo).  Delicate and flavorful, this is a great pizza crust or cheese stick recipe.

name: best banana bread
review: This is really good bread.

name: christina s killer dip
review: Loved this!

name: fresh orange muffins
review: I made a batch of these up. With a house full of people they have barely been touched.  I bought an orange specifically for this recipe so I wonder if my orange wasn't as flavorful as it smelled.  It's a good possibility considering it's February. Everyone agreed that they weren't bad, they just need something.  I may make up a orange glaze to drizzle over these, next time I think I'll add some mini chocolate chip to the batter before baking.  Looking forward to playing with this recipe. Thanks for a great starting off point.

name: crumb topped banana muffins
review: Moist and delicious, like portable little banana puddings.  The topping really puts it over the top.  I added a teaspoon of vanilla to the batter as per other reviewers comments - thank you all.  We ran out of butter so I used 1/3 cup extra virgin olive oil.  Replaced 1/2 cup flour with whole wheat flour.  I also added 1 cup of blueberries because I love them and we had some on hand.  With that addition, I was still able to fit the whole thing into 12 muffin cups.  They were nice and full.  Yum...I will make more tomorrow because I know I'm going to finish eating these by then.  Thank you.  Yes, it's true, it's been a day and all those muffins are gone.  I'm going to have to make more.  But they taste better the second day, there's more of a banana flavor to it and the texture is a little firmer than when they were warm out of the oven.  THANK YOU.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Oh my goodness this is wonderful.  I made this tonight with some homemade bread and it was delicious.  It had a distinct flavor from the hoisin sauce that is like no other stew I've made.  Thank you so much for sharing this with us.

name: amazing chicken tortilla soup
review: After a 100  reviews what else is there to say.  The recipe was reduced by half.  I did not have the tomato sauce so I added in a couple of tablespoons of tomato paste for richness.  The corn was fresh frozen.  The soup was garnished with green onions and served with tortilla chips on the side.

name: slow cooked bbq ribs  for crock pot
